DOID:0050338.definition: A bacterial infectious disease that results_in infection by bacteria as a result of their presence or activity within the normal, healthy host, and their intrinsic virulence is, in part, a necessary consequence of their need to reproduce and spread.

DOID:10457.label: Legionnaires' disease
DOID:10457.definition: A legionellosis that is characterized by severe form of infection producing pneumonia. Symptoms include fever, chills, and cough.

DOID:0050150.label: Pontiac fever
DOID:0050150.definition: A legionellosis that involves a milder respiratory illness without pneumonia. Symptoms include fever, headache and muscle aches which last for 2 to 5 days.

DOID:14457.label: Brucella abortus brucellosis
DOID:14457.definition: A brucellosis that involves an infection caused by Brucella abortus [NCBITaxon:235] in cattle and humans. The disease has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom sweats, has_symptom weight loss, has_symptom malaise, has_symptom headaches, has_symptom myalgia, and has_symptom arthralgia.

DOID:14019.label: Brucella canis brucellosis
DOID:14019.definition: A brucellosis involving an infection caused by Brucella canis [NCBITaxon:36855] in dogs and humans. The disease has_symptom fever, has_symptom sweats, has_symptom weakness, has_symptom weight loss, has_symptom headache, has_symptom lymphadenopathy and has_symptom splenomegaly.

DOID:14456.label: Brucella melitensis brucellosis
DOID:14456.definition: A brucellosis that involves an infection caused by Brucella melitensis [NCBITaxon:29459] in cattle, goats, sheep and humans. The disease has_symptom fever, has_symptom malaise, has_symptom anorexia, has_symptom limb pain and has_symptom back pain.

DOID:11076.label: Brucella suis brucellosis
DOID:11076.definition: A brucellosis that involves an infection caused by Brucella suis [NCBITaxon:29461] in swine and humans. The disease has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom malaise, has_symptom diaphoresis, has_symptom arthralgia, has_symptom myalgia, has_symptom headache, has_symptom anorexia, and has_symptom fatigue.

DOID:0050398.label: Carrion's disease
DOID:0050398.definition: A bartonellosis that results_in infection located_in endothelial cells or located_in red blood cells, has_material_basis_in Bartonella bacilliformis, which is transmitted_by sandflies of genus Lutzomyia. The infection has acute and chronic phases. The acute phase is characterized by severe hemolytic anemia and transient immunosuppression. The chronic phase is characterized by verruga peruana lesions which may ulcerate and bleed.

DOID:0060345.label: bacillary angiomatosis
DOID:0060345.definition: A bartonellosis that has_material_basis_in Bartonella henselae or has_material_basis_in Bartonella quintana. The disease is characterized by the proliferation of blood vessels, resulting in them forming tumour-like masses in the skin and other organs.

DOID:11258.label: cat-scratch disease
DOID:11258.definition: A bartonellosis that results_in infection located_in lymph node, has_material_basis_in Bartonella henselae or has_material_basis_in Bartonella clarridgeiae, which are transmitted_by scratch or bite of a kitten, or transmitted_by contact of animal's saliva with an eye or through broken skin. The infection has_symptom regional lymphadenopathy, has_symptom headache, has_symptom chills, has_symptom backache, and has_symptom abdominal pain.

DOID:11101.label: trench fever
DOID:11101.definition: A primary bacterial infectious disease that results_in systemic infection, has_material_basis_in Bartonella quintana, which is transmitted_by body lice (Pediculus humanus corporis). The infection has_symptom relapsing fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom shin pain, and has_symptom soreness of the muscles of the legs and back.

DOID:0050035.label: African tick-bite fever
DOID:0050035.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia africae, which is transmitted_by ticks (Amblyomma hebraeum and Amblyomma variegatum). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom eschar and has_symptom maculopapular rash.

DOID:0050041.label: Astrakhan spotted fever
DOID:0050041.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia conorii subsp caspia, which is transmitted_by ticks (Rhipicephalus pumilio and Rhipicephalus sanguineus). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom eschar (usually single), has_symptom regional adenopathy, has_symptom maculopapular rash on extremities.

DOID:0050046.label: Far Eastern spotted fever
DOID:0050046.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia heilongjiangensis, which is transmitted_by ticks (Haemaphysalis concinna). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom eschar, has_symptom maculopapular rash, and has_symptom regional adenopathy.

DOID:0050047.label: Flinders Island spotted fever
DOID:0050047.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia honei, which is transmitted_by cayenne ticks (Amblyomma cajennense). The infection has_symptom mild spotted fever, has_symptom eschar and has_symptom adenopathy.

DOID:0050042.label: Indian tick typhus
DOID:0050042.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia conorii subsp indica, which is transmitted_by ticks (Rhipicephalus sanguineus). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom eschar, has_symptom regional adenopathy, and has_symptom maculopapular rash on extremities.

DOID:0050043.label: Israeli tick typhus
DOID:0050043.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia conorii subsp israelensis, which is transmitted_by ticks (Rhipicephalus sanguineus). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom eschar, has_symptom regional adenopathy, and has_symptom maculopapular rash on extremities.

DOID:0050050.label: Japanese spotted fever
DOID:0050050.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia japonica, which is transmitted_by ticks (Dermacentor taiwanensis and Haemaphysalis flava). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom eschars, has_symptom regional adenopathy, and has_symptom rash on extremities.

DOID:10784.label: Queensland tick typhus
DOID:10784.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia australis, which is transmitted_by ticks (Ixodes holocyclus). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom myalgia, has_symptom maculopapular rash, and has_symptom lymphadenopathy.

DOID:0050051.label: Rickettsia parkeri spotted fever
DOID:0050051.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia parkeri, which is transmitted_by Gulf Coast tick (Amblyomma maculatum). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom eschar, and has_symptom rash.

DOID:0050052.label: Rocky Mountain spotted fever
DOID:0050052.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia rickettsii, which is transmitted_by ticks (Dermacentor variabilis and Dermacentor andersoni). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom abdominal pain, and has_symptom maculopapular rash progressing into papular or petechial rash.

DOID:10921.label: Siberian tick typhus
DOID:10921.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia sibirica, which is transmitted_by ticks (Dermacentor nuttalli, Dermacentor marginatus and Haemaphysalis concinna). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom eschar, has_symptom regional adenopathy, and has_symptom maculopapular rash.

DOID:0050484.label: aneruptive fever
DOID:0050484.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia helvetica, which is transmitted_by ticks (Ixodes sp). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom myalgia.

DOID:14095.label: boutonneuse fever
DOID:14095.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia conorii subsp conorii, which is transmitted_by dog tick (Rhipicephalus sanguineus). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom eschar (usually single), has_symptom regional adenopathy, has_symptom maculopapular rash on extremities.

DOID:11103.label: rickettsialpox
DOID:11103.definition: A spotted fever that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia akari, which is transmitted_by house mouse mite (Liponyssoides sanguineus) found on mice and other rodents. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom headache, has_symptom myalgia, and has_symptom papulovesicular rash.

DOID:11750.label: Bordetella parapertussis whooping cough
DOID:11750.definition: A pertussis that is a milder disease caused by the bacterium Bordetella parapertussis. The disease has_symptom coughing, has_symptom sneezing, or has_symptom runny nose .

DOID:11394.label: adult respiratory distress syndrome
DOID:11394.definition: A respiratory failure that results from diffuse injury to the endothelium of the lung (as in sepsis, chest trauma, massive blood transfusion, aspiration of the gastric contents, or pneumonia) and is characterized by pulmonary edema with an abnormally high amount of protein in the edematous fluid and by difficult rapid breathing and hypoxemia.

DOID:12716.label: newborn respiratory distress syndrome
DOID:12716.definition: A respiratory failure that is characterized by deficiency of the surfactant coating the inner surface of the lungs, by failure of the lungs to expand and contract properly during breathing with resulting collapse, and by the accumulation of a protein-containing film lining the alveoli and their ducts.

DOID:0050481.label: endemic typhus
DOID:0050481.definition: A typhus that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia typhi or has_material_basis_in Rickettsia felis, which are transmitted_by fleas (Xenopsylla cheopis). The infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom myalgia, has_symptom nausea, has_symptom vomiting, has_symptom cough and has_symptom rash.

DOID:0050480.label: epidemic typhus
DOID:0050480.definition: A typhus that has_material_basis_in Rickettsia prowazekii, which is transmitted_by human body louse (Pediculus humanus corporis). The infection has_symptom high fever, has_symptom cough, has_symptom rash, has_symptom severe muscle pain, has_symptom chills, has_symptom falling blood pressure, has_symptom stupor, has_symptom sensitivity to light, and has_symptom delirium.

DOID:13371.label: scrub typhus
DOID:13371.definition: A typhus that has_material_basis_in Orientia tsutsugamushi, which is transmitted_by trombiculid mites (Leptotrombidium deliense). The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom muscle pain, has_symptom cough, has_symptom maculopapular rash, has_symptom eschar, has_symptom splenomegaly and has_symptom lymphadenopathy.

DOID:13521.label: tetanus neonatorum
DOID:13521.definition: A tetanus that occurs in newborn babies when the birth cord stump gets dirty through cutting it with an unclean blade or applying substances containing bacteria to it. The infection has_symptom stiff body, has_symptom muscle spasms, has_symptom difficulty in breathing, and has_symptom exhaustion.

DOID:0050352.label: foodborne botulism
DOID:0050352.definition: A botulism that involves intoxication caused by botulinum neurotoxins (BoNTA, B, E and F), which are transmitted_by ingestion of food contaminated with preformed toxins, has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum A, has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum B, has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum E and has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum F. The infection has_symptom blurred vision, has_symptom diplopia, has_symptom dysarthria, has_symptom dysphonia, has_symptom dysphagia and has_symptom descending muscle paralysis.

DOID:0050354.label: infant botulism
DOID:0050354.definition: A botulism that involves intoxication caused by botulinum neurotoxins (BoNTA or B) in infants, has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum A or has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum B, which are transmitted_by ingestion of bacterial spores, which then grow in the intestine and release toxins. The infection has_symptom constipation, has_symptom lethargy, has_symptom difficulty feeding, has_symptom swallowing, has_symptom ptosis, has_symptom loss of head control, and has_symptom muscle weakness.

DOID:0050141.label: intestinal botulism
DOID:0050141.definition: A botulism that involves intoxication caused by botulinum neurotoxins (BoNTA, B, E and F) in adults, has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum A, has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum B, has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum E and has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum F, which are transmitted_by ingestion of bacterial spores, which then grow in the intestine and release toxins.

DOID:0050353.label: wound botulism
DOID:0050353.definition: A botulism that involves intoxication caused by botulinum neurotoxins (BoNTA, B, E and F), has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum A, has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum B, has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum E and has_material_basis_in Clostridium botulinum F, which are transmitted_by contact of spores with the open wounds, which then reproduce in an anaerobic environment to produce toxins.

DOID:3044.label: food allergy
DOID:3044.definition: A hypersensitivity reaction type I disease that is an abnormal response to a food, triggered by the body's immune system.

DOID:114.label: heart disease
DOID:114.definition: A cardiovascular system disease that involves the heart.

DOID:0050829.label: pericardium disease
DOID:0050829.definition: A cardiovascular system disease that is located_in the  fibrous sac surrounding the heart.

DOID:13035.label: louse-borne relapsing fever
DOID:13035.definition: A relapsing fever that is characterized by relapsing or recurring episodes of fever, has_material basis_in Borrelia recurrentis, which is transmitted_by body louse (Pediculus humanus). The infection has_symptom tachypnea, has_symptom tachycardia, has_symptom hepatosplenomegaly and has_symptom lymphadenopathy.

DOID:13036.label: tick-borne relapsing fever
DOID:13036.definition: A relapsing fever that is characterized by relapsing or recurring episodes of fever, has_material basis_in Borrelia hermsii, has_material basis_in Borrelia parkeri or has_material basis_in Borrelia duttoni, which are transmitted_by soft ticks (Ornithodoros parkeri and Ornithodoros hermsii). The infection has_symptom tachypnea, has_symptom tachycardia, has_symptom hepatosplenomegaly and has_symptom lymphadenopathy.

DOID:0050059.label: oropharyngeal anthrax
DOID:0050059.definition: A gastrointestinal anthrax that results_in infection located_in mucosa of oropharynx, has_material_basis_in Bacillus anthracis, which is transmitted_by ingestion of anthrax-infected meat. The infection has_symptom lesions, has_symptom vomiting of blood, has_symptom severe diarrhea, has_symptom loss of appetite.

DOID:48.label: male reproductive system disease
DOID:48.definition: A reproductive system disease that affects male reproductive organs.

DOID:0050161.label: lower respiratory tract disease
DOID:0050161.definition: A respiratory system disease which involves the lower respiratory tract.

DOID:365.label: bladder disease
DOID:365.definition: A urinary system disease that is located_in the bladder.

DOID:557.label: kidney disease
DOID:557.definition: A urinary system disease that is located_in the kidney.

DOID:14239.label: gastrointestinal tularemia
DOID:14239.definition: A tularemia that results in formation of ulcerative lesions located_in gastrointestinal tract. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom malaise, has_symptom muscle aches, and has_symptom vomiting.

DOID:0050382.label: glandular tularemia
DOID:0050382.definition: A tularemia that results_in swelling of regional lymph glands.

DOID:13226.label: oculoglandular tularemia
DOID:13226.definition: A tularemia that results_in inflammation of eye and swelling of lymph glands in front of the ear.

DOID:2122.label: pneumonic tularemia
DOID:2122.definition: A tularemia that is located_in lungs. The bacteria are transmitted_by breathing dusts or aerosols containing the organisms. The infection has_symptom cough, has_symptom chest has_symptom pain, and has_symptom difficulty breathing.

DOID:0050383.label: typhoidal tularemia
DOID:0050383.definition: A tularemia that results_in bacteremia and has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom myalgia, has_symptom malaise, and has_symptom weight loss.

DOID:11990.label: ulceroglandular tularemia
DOID:11990.definition: A tularemia that results_in painful regional lymphadenopathy and an ulcerated skin lesion.

DOID:754.label: bladder tuberculosis
DOID:754.definition: An urogenital tuberculosis that is located_in urinary bladder, which results in fibrosis of bladder wall muscles.

DOID:9733.label: renal tuberculosis
DOID:9733.definition: An urogenital tuberculosis that results_in formation of granulomas located_in kidney.

DOID:1251.label: tuberculous epididymitis
DOID:1251.definition: An urogenital tuberculosis that is located_in epididymis, has_symptom pain and has_symptom scrotal swelling.

DOID:2148.label: tuberculous oophoritis
DOID:2148.definition: An urogenital tuberculosis that results_in inflammtion located_in ovary.

DOID:0050166.label: tuberculous salpingitis
DOID:0050166.definition: An urogenital tuberculosis that results_in formation of granulomas located_in fallopian tube.

DOID:827.label: ureter tuberculosis
DOID:827.definition: An urogenital tuberculosis that is located_in ureter resulting in ureteral strictures.

DOID:0060056.label: hypersensitivity reaction disease
DOID:0060056.definition: An immune system disease that has material basis in abnormal immune responses.

DOID:75.label: lymphatic system disease
DOID:75.definition: An immune system disease that is located_in the lymphatic system.

DOID:4377.label: egg allergy
DOID:4377.definition: A food allergy that is an allergy or hypersensitivity to dietary substances from the yolk or whites of eggs, causing an overreaction of the immune system which may lead to severe physical symptoms.

DOID:4376.label: milk allergy
DOID:4376.definition: A food allergy that results in adverse immune reaction to one or more of the proteins in cow's milk and/or the milk of other animals, which are normally harmless to the non-allergic individual.

DOID:0060513.label: fish allergy
DOID:0060513.definition: A food allergy triggered by fish.

DOID:0060503.label: fruit allergy
DOID:0060503.definition: A food allergy triggered by a plant fruit product.

DOID:0060495.label: shellfish allergy
DOID:0060495.definition: A food allergy triggered by Crustacea or Mollusca.

DOID:9471.label: meningitis
DOID:9471.definition: A central nervous system disease that is characterized by an inflammation of the pia-arachnoid meninges. It can be caused by growth of bacteria, fungi, or parasites within the subarachnoid space or by the growth of bacteria or viruses within the meningeal or ependymal cells.

DOID:10773.label: bubonic plague
DOID:10773.definition: A plague that results_in infection located_in lymph node producing a bubo, which is an inflamed, necrotic, and hemorrhagic lymphoid tissue. The infection has_symptom enlarged, tender lymph nodes, has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills and has_symptom prostration.

DOID:10398.label: pneumonic plague
DOID:10398.definition: A plague that results_in infection located_in lung, which results from direct inhalation of the bacillus and has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom cough and has_symptom difficulty breathing.

DOID:3481.label: septicemic plague
DOID:3481.definition: A plague that results_in infection located_in vasculature where bacterial endotoxins cause coagulation, which leads to formation of tiny clots throughout the body. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom chills, has_symptom prostration, has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom shock and has_symptom bleeding into skin and other organs.

DOID:0050598.label: extrapulmonary tuberculosis
DOID:0050598.definition: A tuberculosis that occurs at body sites other than the lung.

DOID:401.label: multidrug-resistant tuberculosis
DOID:401.definition: A tuberculosis that is resistant to isoniazid and rifampicin, the two most powerful first-line anti-TB drugs.

DOID:2957.label: pulmonary tuberculosis
DOID:2957.definition: A tuberculosis that is a contagious disease located_in lungs. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom cough, has_symptom difficulty in breathing, has_symptom inflammatory infiltrations, has_symptom formation of tubercles, has_symptom caseation, has_symptom pleural effusion, and has_symptom fibrosis.

DOID:0050117.label: disease by infectious agent
DOID:0050117.definition: A disease that is the consequence of the presence of pathogenic microbial agents, including pathogenic viruses, pathogenic bacteria, fungi, protozoa, multicellular parasites, and aberrant proteins known as prions.

DOID:7.label: disease of anatomical entity
DOID:7.definition: A disease that manifests in a defined anatomical structure.

GENEPIO:0001617.label: subject disease
GENEPIO:0001617.definition: Name of disease in a subject that is related to a given investigation, study and/or specimen.

DOID:7332.label: esophageal tuberculosis
DOID:7332.definition: A gastrointestinal tuberculosis that involves formation of tuberculous ulcers located_in esophagus. The infection has_symptom dysphagia, has_symptom cough, has_symptom chest pain, has_symptom fever and has_symptom weight loss.

DOID:407.label: hepatic tuberculosis
DOID:407.definition: A gastrointestinal tuberculosis that involves infection located_in liver, which results in the formation of tuberculous granulomas. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom anorexia, has_symptom weight loss, has_symptom abdominal pain and has_symptom jaundice.

DOID:13282.label: intestinal tuberculosis
DOID:13282.definition: A gastrointestinal tuberculosis that involves diffuse mucosal fold thickening, formation of ulcers and fistulae located_in intestine. The infection has_symptom abdominal pain, has_symptom gastrointestinal bleeding, has_symptom nausea and has_symptom vomiting.

DOID:402.label: oral tuberculosis
DOID:402.definition: A gastrointestinal tuberculosis that involves formation of painful ulcerative mucosal lesions located_in tongue, located_in palate, located_in maxilla or located_in mandible.

DOID:9801.label: tuberculous peritonitis
DOID:9801.definition: A gastrointestinal tuberculosis that results_in inflammation located_in peritoneum, which results in formation of tubercles. The infection has_symptom abdominal discomfort, has_symptom pain, has_symptom distention from gas or fluid, has_symptom digestive disturbances and has_symptom emaciation.

DOID:9856.label: congenital syphilis
DOID:9856.definition: A syphilis that results_in a multisystem infection in the fetus via the placenta.

DOID:9531.label: latent syphilis
DOID:9531.definition: A syphilis that is characterized as having serologic proof of infection without signs or symptoms of disease.

DOID:4156.label: primary syphilis
DOID:4156.definition: A syphilis that is the first stage of syphilis, marked by the development of a chancre, which is characterized by mononuclear leukocytic infiltration, macrophages, and lymphocytes.

DOID:4157.label: secondary syphilis
DOID:4157.definition: A syphilis that is characterized as the second stage of syphilis which appears from 2 to 6 months after primary infection, and is marked by lesions especially in the skin but also in organs and tissues, and that lasts from 3 to 12 weeks.

DOID:8200.label: tertiary syphilis
DOID:8200.definition: A syphilis that is characterized as the third stage of syphilis that develops after the disappearance of the secondary symptoms and is marked by ulcers and gummas under the skin and commonly by involvement of the skeletal, cardiovascular, and nervous systems.

DOID:0060521.label: cow milk allergy
DOID:0060521.definition: A milk allergy triggered by Bos taurus milk.

DOID:0060522.label: goat milk allergy
DOID:0060522.definition: A milk allergy triggered by Capra hircus milk.

DOID:0060492.label: chicken egg allergy
DOID:0060492.definition: An egg allergy triggered by Gallus gallus eggs.

DOID:4378.label: peanut allergy
DOID:4378.definition: A food allergy that is an allergy or hypersensitivity to dietary substances from peanuts causing an overreaction of the immune system which in a small percentage of people may lead to severe physical symptoms.

DOID:0050589.label: inflammatory bowel disease
DOID:0050589.definition: An intestinal disease characterized by inflammation located_in all parts of digestive tract.

NCIT:C98904.label: Connective and Soft Tissue Injury
NCIT:C98904.definition: Damage inflicted on the soft tissues and their supporting structures as the direct or indirect result of an external force, with or without disruption of structural continuity.

DOID:1287.label: cardiovascular system disease
DOID:1287.definition: A disease of anatomical entity which occurs in the blood, heart, blood vessels or the lymphatic system that passes nutrients (such as amino acids and electrolytes), gases, hormones, blood cells or lymph to and from cells in the body to help fight diseases and help stabilize body temperature and pH to maintain homeostasis.

DOID:77.label: gastrointestinal system disease
DOID:77.definition: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the gastrointestinal tract.

DOID:74.label: hematopoietic system disease
DOID:74.definition: An immune system disease that has_material_basis_in hematopoietic cells.

DOID:2914.label: immune system disease
DOID:2914.definition: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the immune system.

DOID:16.label: integumentary system disease
DOID:16.definition: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the integumentary system comprising the skin and its appendages.

DOID:863.label: nervous system disease
DOID:863.definition: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the central nervous system or located_in the peripheral nervous system.

DOID:15.label: reproductive system disease
DOID:15.definition: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in reproductive system organs.

DOID:0060118.label: thoracic disease
DOID:0060118.definition: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in the thoracic cavity.

DOID:18.label: urinary system disease
DOID:18.definition: A disease of anatomical entity that is located_in kidney, ureter, bladder and urethra.

DOID:2355.label: anemia
DOID:2355.definition: A hematopoietic system disease that is characterized by a decrease in the normal number of red blood cells.

DOID:7426.label: cutaneous anthrax
DOID:7426.definition: An anthrax disease that results_in infection located_in skin, has_material_basis_in Bacillus anthracis, which is transmitted_by contact with infected animals or animal products. The infection has_symptom skin lesion that eventually forms an ulcer with a black center.

DOID:13386.label: gastrointestinal anthrax
DOID:13386.definition: An anthrax disease that results_in infection located_in mucosa of gastrointestinal tract, has_material_basis_in Bacillus anthracis, which is transmitted_by ingestion of anthrax-infected meat. The infection has_symptom lesions, has_symptom vomiting of blood, has_symptom severe diarrhea, has_symptom loss of appetite.

DOID:0050160.label: inhalation anthrax
DOID:0050160.definition: An anthrax disease that results_in infection located_in lung lymph nodes brought on by breathing in the spores of the bacteria Bacillus anthracis. The first symptoms of inhalation anthrax are like cold or flu symptoms and can include a sore throat, mild fever and muscle aches. Later symptoms include cough, chest discomfort, shortness of breath, tiredness and muscle aches.

DOID:6050.label: esophageal disease
DOID:6050.definition: A gastrointestinal system disease that is located_in the esophagus.

DOID:2326.label: gastroenteritis
DOID:2326.definition: A gastrointestinal system infectious disease that involves inflammation of the lining of the stomach and small and large intestines, which is caused by viruses, bacteria, or parasites. Chemicals and drugs also cause gastroenteritis. The symptoms include diarrhea, loss of appetite, nausea, vomiting, cramps, and discomfort in the abdomen.

DOID:5295.label: intestinal disease
DOID:5295.definition: A gastrointestinal system disease that is located_in the intestine.

DOID:9880.label: cardiovascular syphilis
DOID:9880.definition: A tertiary syphilis that is manifested as aneurysm formation in the ascending aorta, caused by chronic inflammatory destruction of the vasa vasorum, insufficiency of the aortic valve, or narrowing of the coronary arteries.

DOID:0050584.label: gummatous syphilis
DOID:0050584.definition: A tertiary syphilis that is characterized by granulomatous lesions, called gummas, which are characterized by a center of necrotic tissue with a rubbery texture. They form in the liver, bones, and testes but may affect any organ.

DOID:9988.label: tertiary neurosyphilis
DOID:9988.definition: A tertiary syphilis that results_in infection located_in brain or located_in spinal cord.

DOID:11162.label: respiratory failure
DOID:11162.definition: A lung disease characterized by inadequate gas exchange by the respiratory system.

DOID:331.label: central nervous system disease
DOID:331.definition: A nervous system disease that affects either the spinal cord (myelopathy) or brain (encephalopathy) of the central nervous system.

DOID:2945.label: severe acute respiratory syndrome
DOID:2945.definition: A viral infectious disease that results_in infection located_in respiratory tract, has_material_basis_in SARS coronavirus (SARS-CoV), which is transmitted_by droplet spread of respiratory secretions, transmitted_by ingestion of contaminated food, or transmitted_by fomites. The infection has_symptom fever, has_symptom headache, has_symptom body aches, has_symptom dry cough, and has_symptom hypoxia.

DOID:0050488.label: early congenital syphilis
DOID:0050488.definition: A congenital syphilis that is manifested during the first 3 months of life. The infection has_symptom skin lesions, has_symptom lymphadenopathy, has_symptom hepatosplenomegaly, has_symptom failure to thrive, has_symptom blood-stained nasal discharge, has_symptom perioral fissures, has_symptom meningitis, has_symptom choroiditis, has_symptom hydrocephalus, has_symptom seizures, has_symptom intellectual disability, has_symptom osteochondritis, and has_symptom pseudoparalysis.

DOID:10039.label: late congenital syphilis
DOID:10039.definition: A congenital syphilis that occurs in children at or greater than two years of age who acquired the infection trans-placentally. The infection has_symptom gummatous ulcers, has_symptom periosteal lesions, has_symptom paresis, has_symptom tabes, has_symptom optic atrophy, has_symptom interstitial keratitis, has_symptom sensorineural deafness, and has_symptom dental deformities.

DOID:10035.label: asymptomatic neurosyphilis
DOID:10035.definition: A tertiary neurosyphilis that results_in mild meningitis.

DOID:0050491.label: meningovascular neurosyphilis
DOID:0050491.definition: A tertiary neurosyphilis that results_in inflammation located_in arteries of the brain or located_in arteries of spinal cord. The infection has_symptom headache, has_symptom neck stiffness, has_symptom dizziness, has_symptom behavioral abnormalities, has_symptom poor concentration, has_symptom memory loss, has_symptom lassitude, has_symptom insomnia, has_symptom blurred vision, has_symptom weakness and wasting of shoulder-girdle and arm muscles, has_symptom slowly progressive leg weakness with urinary or fecal incontinence or both, and has_symptom paralysis of the legs due to thrombosis of spinal arteries.

DOID:0050490.label: parenchymatous neurosyphilis
DOID:0050490.definition: A tertiary neurosyphilis that results when chronic meningoencephalitis causes destruction of cortical parenchyma. The infection has_symptom irritability, has_symptom difficulty concentrating, has_symptom deterioration of memory, has_symptom defective judgment, has_symptom headaches, has_symptom insomnia, has_symptom fatigue, and has_symptom lethargy.

DOID:10027.label: tabes dorsalis
DOID:10027.definition: A tertiary neurosyphilis that results_in slow degeneration of the nerve cells and nerve fibers that carry sensory information to the brain. The infection has_symptom intense, stabbing pain in the back and legs that recurs irregularly, has_symptom gait ataxia, has_symptom hyperesthesia, has_symptom paresthesia, has_symptom loss of bladder sensation leading to urine retention, has_symptom erectile dysfunction.

ENVO:00000012.label: hydrographic feature
ENVO:00000012.definition: A geographical feature associated with water.

ENVO:01000281.label: layer
ENVO:01000281.definition: A layer is a quantity of some material which is spatially continuous, has comparable thickness, and usually covers some surface.

ENVO:00000027.label: spring
ENVO:00000027.definition: A point where groundwater or steam flows out of the ground, and is thus where the aquifer surface meets the ground surface or where there is a fissure.

ENVO:00000002.label: anthropogenic geographic feature
ENVO:00000002.definition: An anthropogenic geographic feature is a geographic feature resulting from the influence of human beings on nature.

ENVO:00000070.label: construction
ENVO:00000070.definition: A feature that has been constructed by deliberate human effort.

ENVO:00000011.label: garden
ENVO:00000011.definition: An enclosure for displaying selected plant or animal life.

ENVO:00000562.label: park
ENVO:00000562.definition: A bounded area of land, or water, usually in its natural or semi-natural (landscaped) state and set aside for some purpose, usually to do with recreation or conservation.

ENVO:00000026.label: well
ENVO:00000026.definition: A cylindrical hole, pit, or tunnel drilled or dug down to a depth from which water, oil, or gas can be pumped or brought to the surface.

ENVO:01000935.label: campground
ENVO:01000935.definition: A part of an ecosystem which may be or has been used for one or more overnight stays by humans sheltering in tents, camper vans, caravans, or improvised shelters.

ENVO:01000985.label: fairground
ENVO:01000985.definition: A part of an ecosystem which has been allocated to host a gathering of people for multiple entertainment or commercial activities.

ENVO:01000987.label: market
ENVO:01000987.definition: A part of an ecosystem where people gather for the purchase and sale of provisions, livestock, and other goods.

ENVO:00000123.label: political entity
ENVO:00000123.definition: A geographical region whose affairs and population are administered by an authority.

ENVO:00000005.label: first-order administrative region
ENVO:00000005.definition: A primary administrative division of a country, such as a state in the United States.

NCIT:C25632.label: Province
NCIT:C25632.definition: A region, district or division of a country; a tract; a portion a state, especially one remote from the capital.

NCIT:C87194.label: State
NCIT:C87194.definition: A constituent administrative district of a nation.

NCIT:C89811.label: Territory
NCIT:C89811.definition: A geographical area under the jurisdiction of a sovereign state and marked off for administrative or other purposes.

GENEPIO:0001742.label: subnational region
GENEPIO:0001742.definition: A subnational region is a type of subnational entity similar to a nation's state, province, or territory.

ENVO:00000563.label: pier
ENVO:00000563.definition: A raised walkway over water, supported by piles or pillars.

ENVO:00010625.label: zoological garden
ENVO:00010625.definition: A facility in which animals are confined within enclosures and displayed to the public, and in which they may also be bred.

ENVO:01000044.label: marine pelagic feature
ENVO:01000044.definition: A prominent or distinctive aspect, quality, or characteristic of environments occurring within the marine water column.

ENVO:00000042.label: drainage canal
ENVO:00000042.definition: Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used drainage.

ENVO:00000022.label: river
ENVO:00000022.definition: A stream which, through permanent or seasonal flow processes, moves from elevated land towards lower elevations through a definite channel and empties either into a sea, lake, or another river or ends on land as bed seepage and evapotranspiration exceed water supply.

ENVO:00000450.label: irrigation reservoir
ENVO:00000450.definition: A reservoir constructed for the purpose of providing water for irrigation.

ENVO:00000014.label: canal
ENVO:00000014.definition: Artificial watercourse with no flow or a controlled flow used for navigation, drainage or irrigation.

ENVO:00000023.label: stream
ENVO:00000023.definition: A watercourse which is linear and flows across the solid portion of a planetary surface.

ENVO:00000140.label: drainage ditch
ENVO:00000140.definition: A ditch that collects water from the surrounding land.

ENVO:00000139.label: irrigation ditch
ENVO:00000139.definition: A ditch that supplies water to surrounding land.

NCIT:C80234.label: Municipality
NCIT:C80234.definition: A political unit, such as a city, town, or village, incorporated for local self-government.

ENVO:01000658.label: dense settlement
ENVO:01000658.definition: A settlement with a high density of buildings and inhabitants.

ENVO:01000617.label: lentic water body
ENVO:01000617.definition: A lentic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, has very little to no directed flow.

ENVO:01000618.label: lotic water body
ENVO:01000618.definition: A lotic water body is a water body in which the accumulated water, in its totality, is flowing.

ENVO:01001319.label: saline water body
ENVO:01001319.definition: A body of water which is primarily composed of saline water.

ENVO:00000073.label: building
ENVO:00000073.definition: A permanent walled and roofed construction.

ENVO:01000486.label: building floor
ENVO:01000486.definition: A building floor is a surface layer which is part of a building and used for walking.

ENVO:01000467.label: constructed barrier
ENVO:01000467.definition: A constructed barrier is a freestanding wall, berm, or fence built to limit movement of entities across a boundary.

ENVO:00000076.label: mine
ENVO:00000076.definition: An excavation in the Earth for the purpose of extracting earth materials.

ENVO:00000469.label: research facility
ENVO:00000469.definition: A facility, permanent or temporary, on land, in air, space or water, where scientific research or measurements can be undertaken.

ENVO:00000565.label: sports facility
ENVO:00000565.definition: A building or region where sports activities can be carried out.

ENVO:00000010.label: transport feature
ENVO:00000010.definition: A construction which enables the movement of humans, their animals or their vehicles.

ENVO:01000965.label: constructed swimming pool
ENVO:01000965.definition: A construction which is designed to hold water in which humans may swim or perform other leisure activities.

ENVO:01000968.label: water intake
ENVO:01000968.definition: A hydraulic-engineering installation which transports water - in specified amounts, of a specified quality, and in accordance with a water-consumption plan - from a source of supply into a conduit.

ENVO:01000417.label: house
ENVO:01000417.definition: A house is a building that provides a dwelling-place for a living entity.

ENVO:00003861.label: industrial building
ENVO:00003861.definition: An industrial building is a building within which goods are produced and, optionally, stored or within which services are rendered.

ENVO:01001222.label: commercial building
ENVO:01001222.definition: A building which is primarily used to facilitate the buying or selling of goods or services.

ENVO:01001480.label: domestic building
ENVO:01001480.definition: A building which is primarily used for the long-term habitation of humans.

ENVO:01000781.label: public building
ENVO:01000781.definition: A building which is publically accessible.

ENVO:00000294.label: fish farm
ENVO:00000294.definition: A facility in which fish are raised commercially in tanks or enclosures, usually for food.

ENVO:00000295.label: fish hatchery
ENVO:00000295.definition: A facility where eggs of fish are hatched under artificial conditions.

ENVO:00000117.label: plantation
ENVO:00000117.definition: An intentional planting of a crop, on a large scale, usually for uses other than cereal production or pasture. The term is currently most often used for plantings of trees and shrubs. The term tends also to be used for plantings maintained on economic bases other than that of subsistence farming.

ENVO:01000627.label: feedlot
ENVO:01000627.definition: A feedlot is a plot of land on which livestock are fattened for market

ENVO:00000266.label: pasture
ENVO:00000266.definition: A grassland ecosystem which is used for grazing of ungulate livestock as part of a farm or ranch.

ENVO:00000111.label: forested area
ENVO:00000111.definition: An area with a high density of trees. A small forest may be called a wood.

ENVO:01000348.label: maize field
ENVO:01000348.definition: A field  used for the cultivation of corn or related crop plants.

ENVO:00000297.label: paddy field
ENVO:00000297.definition: A flooded parcel of arable land used for growing rice and other semiaquatic crops.

ENVO:00000037.label: ditch
ENVO:00000037.definition: A small, human-made channel which has been dug for draining or irrigating the land.

ENVO:01000924.label: plumbing drain
ENVO:01000924.definition: An artificial channel which transports unwanted water or waste liquids away from their source, either to a more useful area, a receptacle, or into sewers or stormwater mains as waste discharge to be released or processed.

ENVO:00000009.label: national geopolitical entity
ENVO:00000009.definition: A political association with effective dominion over a geographic area.

ENVO:00000127.label: badland
ENVO:00000127.definition: An arid terrain with clay-rich soil that has been extensively eroded by wind and water.

ENVO:00000091.label: beach
ENVO:00000091.definition: A landform consisting of loose rock particles such as sand, gravel, shingle, pebbles, cobble, or even shell fragments along the shoreline of a body of water.

ENVO:00000067.label: cave
ENVO:00000067.definition: Naturally formed, subterranean open area or chamber.

ENVO:00000309.label: depression
ENVO:00000309.definition: A landform sunken or depressed below the surrounding area.

ENVO:00000086.label: plain
ENVO:00000086.definition: A region of general uniform slope, comparatively level, and of considerable extent.

ENVO:00002000.label: slope
ENVO:00002000.definition: A solid astronomical body part which is part of the planetary surface between the peak of an elevation or the bottom of a depression and  relatively flat surrounding land.

ENVO:00000508.label: terrace
ENVO:00000508.definition: A step-like feature between higher and lower ground: a relatively flat or gently inclined shelf of earth, backed and fronted by steep slopes or manmade detaining walls.

ENVO:00000292.label: watershed
ENVO:00000292.definition: The separation between neighbouring drainage basins (catchments). In hilly country, the divide lies along topographical peaks and ridges, but in flat country or on a high plateau (especially where the ground is marshy) the divide may be invisible - just a more or less notional line on the ground on either side of which falling raindrops will start a journey to different rivers, and even to different sides of a country or continent.

ENVO:03000117.label: channel
ENVO:03000117.definition: A structure which traverses a mass of one or more environmental materials, and encloses a roughly tubular site.

ENVO:01001275.label: solid layer
ENVO:01001275.definition: A layer which is primarily composed of some solid material, allowing for non-solid parts such as interstitial pockets of gas or liquid.

ENVO:00000395.label: channel of a watercourse
ENVO:00000395.definition: The physical confine of a river, slough or ocean strait consisting of a bed and banks.

ENVO:00000025.label: reservoir
ENVO:00000025.definition: An artificial body of water, often contained by a dam, constructed for the purpose of water storage.

ENVO:00002030.label: aquatic biome
IAO:0000118: A biome which has its properties and composition determined by a water body and within which most members of resident ecological communities have adapted to life in or on water.

ENVO:00000446.label: terrestrial biome
ENVO:00000446.definition: A biome that applies to the terrestrial realm.

ENVO:01000219.label: anthropogenic terrestrial biome
ENVO:01000219.definition: An anthropogenic terrestrial biome is a terrestrial biome which has community structures determined by human activity.

ENVO:01000179.label: desert biome
ENVO:01000179.definition: A desert biome is a terrestrial biome which loses more liquid water by evapotranspiration than is supplied by precipitation and includes communities adapted to these conditions.

ENVO:01000174.label: forest biome
ENVO:01000174.definition: A forest biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its entire spatial extent, densely packed vegetation which strongly limits light penetration to the forest floor.

ENVO:01000177.label: grassland biome
ENVO:01000177.definition: A grassland biome is a terrestrial biome which  includes, across its entire spatial extent, an unbroken layer of grasses (Gramineae), sedges (Cyperaceae) or  rushes (Juncaceae).

ENVO:01000181.label: mangrove biome
ENVO:01000181.definition: A mangrove biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its spatial extent, mangrove plants (Rhizophoraceae). Mangrove plants are able to withstand high levels of salinity as well as regions of anoxia and frequent tidal inundation. Mangrove biomes often occur near tropical and sub-tropical estuaries and depositional marine coastal environments where fine sediments (often with high organic content) collect in areas protected from high energy wave action.

ENVO:01000176.label: shrubland biome
ENVO:01000176.definition: A shrubland biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its entire spatial extent, dense groups of shrubs.

ENVO:01000180.label: tundra biome
ENVO:01000180.definition: A tundra is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its spatial extent, only low-growing vegetation such as dwarf shrubs, sedges and grasses, mosses, and lichens. Tundra biomes rarely have monthly average temperatures above 10 degrees Celsius and have low evapotranspiration ratios.

ENVO:01000175.label: woodland biome
ENVO:01000175.definition: A woodland biome is a terrestrial biome which includes, across its entire spatial extent, woody plants spaced sufficiently far apart to allow light penetration to support communities of herbaceous plants or shrubs living closer to the woodland floor.

ENVO:01000048.label: ocean biome
ENVO:01000048.definition: The ocean biome comprises major bodies of saline water, principal components of the hydrosphere. Approximately 71% of the Earth's surface is covered by ocean, a continuous body of water that is customarily divided into several principal oceans and smaller seas. More than half of this area is over 3,000 metres (9,800 ft) deep. Average oceanic salinity is around 35 parts per thousand (ppt) (3.5%), and nearly all seawater has a salinity in the range of 30 to 38 ppt.

ENVO:01001406.label: laboratory facility
ENVO:01001406.definition: A research facility in which systems of manufactured products control internal conditions and in which scientific or technological research, experiments, and measurement may be performed.

ENVO:00000080.label: mountain range
ENVO:00000080.definition: A series of connected and aligned mountains or mountain ridges.

ENVO:00005749.label: farm soil
ENVO:00005749.definition: A portion of soil which is part of a cropland or a rangeland biome.

ENVO:00002263.label: garden soil
ENVO:00002263.definition: A portion of soil which is found in a garden.

ENVO:00002258.label: loam
ENVO:00002258.definition: A soil composed of sand, silt, and clay in relatively even concentration (about 40-40-20% concentration respectively).

ENVO:00000015.label: ocean
ENVO:00000015.definition: A marine water body which is constitutes the majority of an astronomical body's hydrosphere.

ENVO:00000016.label: sea
ENVO:00000016.definition: A large expanse of saline water usually connected with an ocean.

ENVO:00002018.label: sewage
ENVO:00002018.definition: Wastewater that is contaminated with feces or urine,

ENVO:01000964.label: industrial wastewater
ENVO:01000964.definition: Wastewater which is produced by industrial activity and which contains chemical contaminants other than those associated with urine and fecal matter.

ENVO:00002011.label: fresh water
ENVO:00002011.definition: Water which has a low concentration of dissolved solutes, particularly that of sodium chloride.

ENVO:00000546.label: lake sediment
ENVO:00000546.definition: Lake sediment is sediment which covers the bottom of a lake. Lake sediments are comprised mainly of clastic material (sediment of clay, silt, and sand sizes), organic debris, chemical precipitates, or combinations of these.

ENVO:03000033.label: marine sediment
ENVO:03000033.definition: Sediment which has been transported through the marine water column, settling on the seafloor.

ENVO:00003064.label: drinking water
ENVO:00003064.definition: Drinking water is water which may be consumed by humans with no adverse effects on their health.

ENVO:00000873.label: freshwater biome
ENVO:00000873.definition: A biome that applies to the freshwater realm.

ENVO:00000447.label: marine biome
ENVO:00000447.definition: An aquatic biome that comprises systems of open-ocean and unprotected coastal habitats, characterized by exposure to wave action, tidal fluctuation, and ocean currents as well as systems that largely resemble these. Water in the marine biome is generally within the salinity range of seawater: 30 to 38 ppt.

ENVO:00002001.label: waste water
ENVO:00002001.definition: Water that has been adversely affected in quality by anthropogenic influence.

ENVO:00002222.label: food shop
ENVO:00002222.definition: A shop in which a business offers food products for sale or trade.

ENVO:01000988.label: ethnic food shop
ENVO:01000988.definition: A food shop in which the food products on offer are restricted to those produced in a region and cultural setting other than that of the shop's locality.

ENVO:01000984.label: grocery store
ENVO:01000984.definition: A food shop in which food products are the primary offer for sale or trade.

ENVO:02000022.label: excreta material
ENVO:02000022.definition: A bodily fluid material which is composed primarily of excreta, bodily fluids consisting of matter which contains the waste products of biological processes, including urine or feces, discharged from an organism's body.

ENVO:00003860.label: pig manure
ENVO:00003860.definition: Manure which is primarily composed of pig feces.

ENVO:01000921.label: closed animal house
ENVO:01000921.definition: An animal house which has a complete building envelope.

ENVO:01000918.label: open animal house
ENVO:01000918.definition: An animal house which is only partially surrounded by a building envelope.

ENVO:01000938.label: hot tub
ENVO:01000938.definition: A manufactured product which may hold a volume of heated water suitable for one or more humans to bathe in, usually for the purposes of hydrotherapy or pleasure.

ENVO:01000625.label: manufactured cage
ENVO:01000625.definition: A manufactured structure made of interspaced structural elements such as metal or wooden bars or wires held together such that they may be used to confine, contain, or protect something.

ENVO:01000989.label: plumbing fixture
ENVO:01000989.definition: An exchangeable device which can be connected to a plumbing system to deliver and drain water.

ENVO:01000604.label: vehicle
ENVO:01000604.definition: A vehicle is a mobile machine which transports people or cargo.

ENVO:00003074.label: manufactured product
ENVO:00003074.definition: A material entity that has been processed by humans or their technology in any way, including intermediate products as well as final products.

ENVO:00003864.label: bakery
ENVO:00003864.definition: A bakery is a building in which raw flour-based food is baked in an oven to produce food products such as bread, cakes, pastries, and pies. These products are often sold from the bakery itself.

ENVO:00003885.label: brewery
ENVO:00003885.definition: A brewery is a building in which alcoholic beverages are produced by brewing, that is, steeping a starch source (commonly cereal grains) in water and fermenting the resulting sweet liquid with yeast. At times, the products are also sold from the brewery.

ENVO:00003862.label: dairy
ENVO:00003862.definition: A dairy is a building in which animal milk is harvested and, optionally, processed for human consumption.

ENVO:00003863.label: food processing building
ENVO:00003863.definition: A food processing building is a building in which materials that contain or consist of essential body nutrients - such as carbohydrates, fats, proteins, vitamins, or minerals - and may be ingested and assimilated by an organism to produce energy, stimulate growth, and maintain life are converted alternative forms.

ENVO:00004638.label: sawmill
ENVO:00004638.definition: A building within which logs are cut into lumber products.

ENVO:01000925.label: abattoir
ENVO:01000925.definition: A facility in which non-human animals are slaughtered and processed for human consumption.

ENVO:01000928.label: fish processing building
ENVO:01000928.definition: A building in which fish are subject to a series of operations to prepare them for human consumption.

ENVO:00002191.label: animal litter
ENVO:00002191.definition: Straw or other material strewn in an animal's enclosure (e.g. a stable) for it to sleep on and to absorb its faeces and urine.

ENVO:0010001.label: anthropogenic environmental material
ENVO:0010001.definition: Anthropogenic material in or on which organisms may live.

ENVO:01000018.label: gravel
ENVO:01000018.definition: Gravel is an environmental material which is composed of pieces of rock that are at least two millimeters (2mm) in its largest dimension and no more than 75 millimeters.

ENVO:01000001.label: mud
ENVO:01000001.definition: A liquid or semi-liquid mixture of water and some combination of soil, silt, and clay.

ENVO:01000155.label: organic material
ENVO:01000155.definition: Environmental material derived from living organisms and composed primarily of one or more biomacromolecules.

ENVO:01000017.label: sand
ENVO:01000017.definition: A naturally occurring granular material composed of finely divided rock and mineral particles.

ENVO:00002007.label: sediment
ENVO:00002007.definition: Sediment is an environmental substance comprised of any particulate matter that can be transported by fluid flow and which eventually is deposited as a layer of solid particles on the bedor bottom of a body of water or other liquid.

ENVO:00001998.label: soil
ENVO:00001998.definition: Soil is an environmental material which is primarily composed of minerals, varying proportions of sand, silt, and clay, organic material such as humus, gases, liquids, and a broad range of resident micro- and macroorganisms.

ENVO:00002264.label: waste material
ENVO:00002264.definition: A material which is not the desired output of a process and which is typically the input of a process which removes it from its producer (e.g. a disposal process).

FOODON:03411564.label: food source
FOODON:03411564.definition: Individual plant or animal from which the food product or its major ingredient is derived; also a chemical food source [FDA CFSAN 1995].

ENVO:01000797.label: gaseous environmental material
ENVO:01000797.definition: A material entity which is composed of one or more chemical entities and has neither independent shape nor volume but tends to expand indefinitely.

ENVO:01001125.label: ice
ENVO:01001125.definition: An ice is an environmental material which is either frozen or which is maintained in a solid state by gravitational forces or pressure.

ENVO:01000815.label: liquid environmental material
ENVO:01000815.definition: An environmental material which is in a liquid state.

ENVO:01000060.label: particulate matter
ENVO:01000060.definition: Particulate material is an environmental material which is composed of microscopic portions of solid or liquid material suspended in another environmental material.

ENVO:01001483.label: surface of an astronomical body
ENVO:01001483.definition: A surface layer where the solid or liquid material of an astronomical body comes into contact with an atmosphere or outer space.

ENVO:01000923.label: petting zoo
ENVO:01000923.definition: A petting zoo is a zoological garden which contains domesticated non-human animals and some wild non-human animals that are docile enough for humans to touch and feed.

ENVO:00002170.label: compost
ENVO:00002170.definition: The aerobically decomposed remnants of organic materials.

ENVO:02000047.label: animal feed
ENVO:02000047.definition: Animal feed is a biotic mesoscopic physical object consisting of any foodstuff that is used specifically to feed domesticated livestock, such as cattle, goats, sheep, horses, chickens and pigs. Most animal feed is from plants but some is of animal origin. Fodder refers particularly to food given to the animals (including plants cut and carried to them), rather than that which they forage for themselves. It includes hay, straw, silage, compressed and pelleted feeds, oils and mixed rations, and also sprouted grains and legumes.

ENVO:02000055.label: plant feed
ENVO:02000055.definition: Plant feed is a biotic mesoscopic physical object consisting of any foodstuff that is used specifically to feed plants.

ENVO:00001999.label: marine water body
ENVO:00001999.definition: A significant accumulation of water which is part of a marine biome.

ENVO:00002008.label: dust
ENVO:00002008.definition: Minute solid particles with diameters less than 500 micrometers. Occurs in and may be deposited from, the atmosphere.

ENVO:02000019.label: bodily fluid material
ENVO:02000019.definition: An organic material which is primarily composed of some natural bodily fluid or secretion such as blood, semen, saliva, blood plasma, intracellular and interstitial fluids.

ENVO:01000245.label: cropland biome
ENVO:01000245.definition: A cropland biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for agricultural activity and which contains no village or larger human settlement.

ENVO:01000248.label: dense settlement biome
ENVO:01000248.definition: A dense settlement biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for human habitation, recreation, and industry within built structures with little other land use.

ENVO:01000247.label: rangeland biome
ENVO:01000247.definition: A rangeland biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which is primarily used for the rearing and grazing of livestock.

ENVO:01000246.label: village biome
ENVO:01000246.definition: A village biome is an anthropogenic terrestrial biome which contains settlements such as villages, towns, and/or small cities and which is primarily used for agricultural activity.

ENVO:00000428.label: biome
ENVO:00000428.definition: A biome is an ecosystem to which resident ecological communities have evolved adaptations.

ENVO:01000320.label: marine environment
ENVO:01000320.definition: A marine environment and enviroment which is determined by a marine water body.

ENVO:01001110.label: ecosystem
ENVO:01001110.definition: An environmental system which includes both living and non-living components.

ENVO:00010504.label: surface layer
ENVO:00010504.definition: A layer of some material entity which is adjacent to one or more of its external boundaries and directly interacts with its immediate surroundings.

ENVO:00000114.label: agricultural field
ENVO:00000114.definition: A field which is located on land and used for agricultural purposes, such as the grazing of livestock or the cultivation of crops.

ENVO:00000444.label: clearing
ENVO:00000444.definition: A tract of land with few or no trees in the middle of a wooded area.

ENVO:00000062.label: populated place
ENVO:00000062.definition: Place or area with clustered or scattered buildings and a permanent human population.

ENVO:01001199.label: terrestrial environmental zone
ENVO:01001199.definition: An environmental zone which is bounded by material parts of a land mass or the atmosphere or space adjacent to it.

ENVO:00003040.label: animal house
ENVO:00003040.definition: A house used for sheltering non-human animals.

ENVO:01000933.label: residential building
ENVO:01000933.definition: A human house which serves as a long-term shelter for its inhabitants and within which they store personal property.

ENVO:00000074.label: dam
ENVO:00000074.definition: A barrier constructed across a watercourse to control the flow or raise the level of water.

ENVO:01000602.label: truck
ENVO:01000602.definition: A truck is a motor vehicle which, as its primary funcion, transports cargo rather than human passangers.

ENVO:01000971.label: food truck
ENVO:01000971.definition: A truck which is equipped to cook and sell food.

ENVO:01000601.label: motor vehicle
ENVO:01000601.definition: A motor vehicle is a vehicle which is propelled by an engine or motor and that does not operate on rails.

ENVO:00000020.label: lake
ENVO:00000020.definition: A body of water or other liquid of considerable size contained in a depression on a landmass.

ENVO:00000033.label: pond
ENVO:00000033.definition: A body of water, usually of smaller size than a lake.

ENVO:01000922.label: animal cage
ENVO:01000922.definition: A manufactured cage which may be used to confine, contain, or protect an animal.

ENVO:01000626.label: drylot
ENVO:01000626.definition: A drylot is an enclosure of limited size usually bare of vegetation and used for fattening livestock.

SIO:000666.label: township
SIO:000666.definition: A township is a rural or sub-urban settlement.

ENVO:00000063.label: water body
ENVO:00000063.definition: An accumulation of water of varying size.

ENVO:00000097.label: desert area
ENVO:00000097.definition: A region rendered barren or partially barren by environmental extremes, especially by low rainfall.

ENVO:00002173.label: hospital
ENVO:00002173.definition: A hospital is a building in which health care services are  provided by specialized staff and equipment.

ENVO:01000932.label: nursing home
ENVO:01000932.definition: A building in which nursing aides and skilled nurses provide care and treatment to residents who have significant difficulty coping with the required activities of daily living.

ENVO:00002005.label: air
ENVO:00002005.definition: The mixture of gases (roughly (by molar content/volume: 78% nitrogen, 20.95% oxygen, 0.93% argon, 0.038% carbon dioxide, trace amounts of other gases, and a variable amount (average around 1%) of water vapor) that surrounds the planet Earth.

ENVO:00000191.label: solid astronomical body part
ENVO:00000191.definition: A part of an astronomical body which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of solid material, shaped by one or more environmental processes.

ENVO:01001479.label: fluid astronomical body part
ENVO:01001479.definition: A part of an astronomical body which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid or gaseous material, shaped by one or more environmental processes.

ENVO:00001995.label: rock
ENVO:00001995.definition: A rock is a naturally occurring solid aggregate of one or more minerals or mineraloids.

ENVO:00002006.label: liquid water
ENVO:00002006.definition: An environmental material primarily composed of dihydrogen oxide in its liquid form.

ENVO:01000703.label: hydrological precipitation process
ENVO:01000703.definition: Hydrological precipitation is a process during which any product of the condensation of atmospheric water vapour is pulled to the planetary surface by gravity.

ENVO:01000969.label: cafeteria
ENVO:01000969.definition: A building which provides the site for food services with little or no waiting staff furnishing table service.

ENVO:01000972.label: take-out restaurant
ENVO:01000972.definition: A restaurant which provides prepared meals or other food products that the purchaser must eat off its premises.

ENVO:01000936.label: dedicated campground
ENVO:01000936.definition: A campground which has been modified by humans to provide and maintain facilities for camping such as fire pits, road access, latrines, and garbage bins.

ENVO:01000937.label: impromptu campground
ENVO:01000937.definition: A campground which has no pre-existing facilities installed or maintained by humans, usually found outside of anthropised ecosystems.

ENVO:01000974.label: food kiosk
ENVO:01000974.definition: A kiosk from which food products are sold.

ENVO:01000970.label: delicatessen
ENVO:01000970.definition: A food shop which sells a selection of food products that are not typical dietary components of the human population it is co-located with.

ENVO:01000986.label: agricultural fairground
ENVO:01000986.definition: A fairground which is used to exhibit agricultural technology, livestock, and farm-related activity.

ENVO:01000991.label: bathtub fixture
ENVO:01000991.definition: A plumbing fixture which may serve as a container for water in which humans or other animals may bathe.

ENVO:01000992.label: shower fixture
ENVO:01000992.definition: A plumbing fixture within which a human or other animal may bathe under a spray of water.

ENVO:01000990.label: sink fixture
ENVO:01000990.definition: A plumbing fixture which is bowl-shaped and used for washing hands, dishwashing, and other purposes.

ENVO:01000814.label: solid environmental material
ENVO:01000814.definition: An environmental material which is in a solid state.

ENVO:01001305.label: vegetated area
ENVO:01001305.definition: A vegetated area is a geographic feature which has ground cover dominated by plant communities.

ENVO:01001200.label: anthropised terrestrial environmental zone
ENVO:01001200.definition: A terrestrial zone which is bounded by constructed, manufactured, or other anthropogenic material entities.

ENVO:01000752.label: area of barren land
ENVO:01000752.definition: An area of a planet's surface which is primarily composed of bedrock, desert pavement, scarp rock, talus, material exposed by slides, volcanic material, glacial debris, sand, material exposed during strip mining, gravel, and other accumulations of earthen material in contact with an atmospheric column extending from the planetary boundary layer to the planet's exosphere with little to no physical obstruction.

ENVO:00000078.label: farm
ENVO:00000078.definition: An area of land which is used for the cultivation of crops or grazing of livestock, including any agricultural constructions therein.

ENVO:00002221.label: shop
ENVO:00002221.definition: A building in which a business presents a selection of goods and offers to trade or sell them to customers for money or other goods.

ENVO:01000927.label: day care building
ENVO:01000927.definition: A building which is used to care for a human child during the working day by a person, outside the child's immediate family, other than that child's legal guardians.

ENVO:01000973.label: kiosk
ENVO:01000973.definition: A booth with an open window on one side.

ENVO:01000934.label: restaurant
ENVO:01000934.definition: A building within which food and drink are prepared and served to customers in exchange for money or other goods and/or services.

ENVO:01001311.label: solid surface layer
ENVO:01001311.definition: A surface layer which is composed primarily of solid environmental material.

ENVO:00000106.label: grassland area
ENVO:00000106.definition: An area in which grasses (Graminae) are a significant component of the vegetation.

ENVO:00000300.label: scrubland area
ENVO:00000300.definition: Area covered with low-growing or stunted perennial vegetation and usually not mixed with trees.

ENVO:00000112.label: tundra
ENVO:00000112.definition: A vegetated area which overlaps treeless, level, or gently rolling plains characteristic of arctic or subarctic regions, permanently frozen subsoil, and communities of low growing vegetation such as lichens, mosses, and stunted shrubs.

ENVO:00000043.label: wetland area
ENVO:00000043.definition: An vegetated area which overlaps a wetland ecosystem.

ENVO:00000109.label: woodland area
ENVO:00000109.definition: Land having a cover of trees, shrubs, or both.

ENVO:01001308.label: hydroform
ENVO:01001308.definition: A geographic feature which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid water held in shape or sustained by an environmental process.

ENVO:01001477.label: liquid astronomical body part
ENVO:01001477.definition: A part of an astronomical body which is primarily composed of a continuous volume of liquid material, shaped by one or more environmental processes.

ENVO:00002003.label: fecal material
ENVO:00002003.definition: An excreta material which is composed primarily of feces, an excreta consisting of waste products expelled from an animal's digestive tract through the anus (or cloaca) during defecation.

ENVO:02000048.label: contaminated animal feed
ENVO:02000048.definition: Contaminated animal feed is an animal feed that has become contaminated with or come contact with microorganisms or toxic chemicals.

ENVO:02000054.label: bone meal
ENVO:02000054.definition: A mixture of crushed and coarsely ground bones that is used as an organic fertilizer for plants and formerly in animal feed.

ENVO:03000010.label: material transport process
ENVO:03000010.definition: A process during which material is displaced from its original location and transported either to a new location or back to the original location.

ENVO:01000875.label: precipitation process
ENVO:01000875.definition: A precipitation process is a process in which a portion of some substance segregates from a material in which that substance or its precursors were dissolved or suspended in and settles due to a force such as gravity or centrifugal force.

ENVO:00002113.label: deep marine sediment
ENVO:00002113.definition: Sediment that accumulates in the flat or very gently sloping areas of the deep ocean basin floor. The three main types of deep marine sediment, also known as pelagic sediment, are siliceous oozes, calcareous oozes, and red clays.

EO:0007038.label: autumn season
EO:0007038.definition: The treatment involving an exposure to the autumn season.

EO:0007286.label: dry season
EO:0007286.definition: The treatment involving an exposure to the dry season.

EO:0007034.label: kharif season
EO:0007034.definition: The treatment involving an exposure to the crop season (May-October) as practised in South Asia.

EO:0007033.label: rabi season
EO:0007033.definition: The treatment involving an exposure to the crop season (October-March) as practiced in South Asia.

EO:0007285.label: rainy season
EO:0007285.definition: The treatment involving an exposure to the wet or the rainy season.

EO:0007037.label: spring season
EO:0007037.definition: The treatment involving an exposure to the spring season.

EO:0007036.label: summer season
EO:0007036.definition: The treatment involving an exposure to the summer season.

EO:0007035.label: winter season
EO:0007035.definition: The treatment involving an exposure to the winter season.

ExO:0000057.label: inhalation
ExO:0000057.definition: The process of drawing in by breathing.

ERO:0001286.label: nucleic acid assay
ERO:0001286.definition: A molecular assay that generates data about the presence, abundance, structure, function, or activity of nucleic acids.

OBI:0000723.label: DNA sequencing by ligation
OBI:0000723.definition: is a DNA sequencing which relies on DNA ligase activity to perform chain extension during the sequencing reaction step.

OBI:0000734.label: DNA sequencing by synthesis
OBI:0000734.definition: is a DNA sequencing which relies on DNA polymerase activity to perform chain extension during the sequencing reaction step.

ERO:0001642.label: ion torrent next generation sequencing
ERO:0001642.definition: A next generation sequencing that monitors the incorporation of a nucleotide into a strand of DNA by sensing pH change from the release of a hydrogen ion corresponding to a bonding event.

OBI:0000626.label: DNA sequencing
OBI:0000626.definition: DNA sequencing is a sequencing process which uses deoxyribonucleic acid as input and results in a the creation of DNA sequence information artifact using a DNA sequencer instrument.

GENEPIO:0001841.label: fair health status
GENEPIO:0001841.definition: Fair - Vital signs are stable and within normal limits. Patient is conscious, but may be uncomfortable. Indicators are favorable.

GENEPIO:0001840.label: good health status
GENEPIO:0001840.definition: Good - Vital signs are stable and within normal limits. Patient is conscious and comfortable. Indicators are excellent.

GENEPIO:0001842.label: serious health status
GENEPIO:0001842.definition: Serious - Vital signs may be unstable and not within normal limits. Patient is acutely ill. Indicators are questionable.

GENEPIO:0001852.label: undetermined health status - awaiting assessment
GENEPIO:0001852.definition: Patient is awaiting physician and/or assessment.

NDF-RT:N0000003449.label: critical
NDF-RT:N0000003449.definition: Vital signs are unstable and not within normal limits. Patient may be unconscious. Indicators are unfavorable.

FOODON:00001184.label: algal food product
FOODON:00001184.definition: This food product type includes food products which are derived from a large, diverse group of photosynthetic organisms.

FOODON:00001143.label: fungal food product
FOODON:00001143.definition: Fungal food products include edible fungi, mushrooms, and yeast.

FOODON:00001145.label: microbial food product
FOODON:00001145.definition: A food product derived from one or more microorganisms including bacteria, mold, and yeast.

FOODON:00001015.label: plant food product
FOODON:00001015.definition: This food product type includes food products which are derived from or produced by a plant.

FOODON:00001092.label: vertebrate animal food product
FOODON:00001092.definition: A food product which is derived from or produced by an animal that has a vertibrae.

FOODON:03470107.label: food preservation process
FOODON:03470107.definition: The methods contributing to the prevention or retardation of microbial, enzymatic or oxidative spoilage and thus to the extension of shelf life. Index all methods for which information is available, even if a corresponding descriptor has already been used in *H. TREATMENT APPLIED*. Preservation descriptors refer to the finished food as a whole with these exceptions: (1) if the components of a multi-component food, such as cream pie, are preservation by different methods, index all methods; (2)  if chemical preservatives are declared on the label, always index them even if it is known that the preservative was introduced through or is only present in a component or ingredient of the food; and (3) if the preservation method for an ingredient is declared on the label (such as brie cheese made from pasteurized milk) index it. Also use *INGREDIENT preservation by THERMAL PROCESSING* or *INGREDIENT preservation by IRRADIATION* when ingredients have been pasteurized, ultrapasteurized, sterilized or irradiated.

FOODON:03460111.label: food treatment process
FOODON:03460111.definition: Used to specifically characterize a food product based on the treatment or processes applied to the product or any indexed ingredient. The processes include adding, substituting or removing components or modifying the food or component, e.g., through fermentation. Multiple values can be assigned.

FOODON:03440011.label: extent of food heat treatment
FOODON:03440011.definition: Used to broadly characterize a food product based on the extent of heat applied. Heat treatment affects the flavor and textural characteristics of a food and thus consumer preparation time. Heat treatment causes chemical changes and/or reduction of enzyme and of microbial activity and thus affects food safety and shelflife. Specifics of preparation are covered by *G. COOKING METHOD* and *H. TREATMENT APPLIED*. [FDA CFSAN 1995]

FOODON:03430113.label: food physical quality
FOODON:03430113.definition: The physical state of the food product (liquid, semiliquid, semisolid, or solid). Solid food products are further subdivided by shape or form. Terms are provided for products that have both liquid and solid components or that incorporate air or other gases. [FDA CFSAN 1995]

FOODON:03530049.label: meat, poultry or fish physical quality

FOODON:00001002.label: foodon product type
FOODON:00001002.definition: A substance, usually composed primarily of carbohydrates, fats, water and/or proteins, that can be eaten or drunk by an animal or human being for nutrition or pleasure.

FOODON:03411261.label: fungus
FOODON:03411261.definition: A fungus (plural: fungi or funguses) is any member of the group of eukaryotic organisms that includes unicellular microorganisms such as yeasts and molds, as well as multicellular fungi that produce familiar fruiting forms known as mushrooms. These organisms are classified as a kingdom, *Fungi*, which is separate from the other eukaryotic life kingdoms of plants and animals.[https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fungus]

FOODON:00002452.label: invertebrate animal
FOODON:00002452.definition: Invertebrates are animals that neither possess nor develop a vertebral column (commonly known as a backbone or spine), derived from the notochord. This includes all animals apart from the subphylum Vertebrata.

FOODON:03412345.label: lichen
FOODON:03412345.definition: Lichens are composite organisms consisting of a symbiotic association of a fungus (the mycobiont) with a photosynthetic partner (the photobiont or phycobiont), usually either a green alga (commonly *Trebouxia*) or cyanobacterium (commonly *Nostoc*).

FOODON:03411297.label: vertebrate animal
FOODON:03411297.definition: Multicellular animal, e.g., fish, meat animal or poultry.

FOODON:03420174.label: part of plant
FOODON:03420174.definition: Anatomical part of a plant, such as fruit, seed, pod, leaf, stem or flower as well as the whole plant.

FOODON:03420148.label: root, stem, leaf or flower
FOODON:03420148.definition: The parts of a plant that are not fruit or seed.

FOODON:03430108.label: physical state, shape or form, multiple

FOODON:03430131.label: whole
FOODON:03430131.definition: Refers to natural or formed shape as appropriate, regardless of size, which may vary from very large (e.g., beef carcass) to very small (e.g., poppy seed, yeast cell).

FOODON:03430133.label: divided into halves, quarters or segments
FOODON:03430133.definition: Divided into pieces whose shape is defined in relation to the shape of the whole, i.e., halves, quarters, or segments. It is used regardless of the size of the whole.

FOODON:03430152.label: divided into pieces
FOODON:03430152.definition: Divided into pieces whose shape bears little or no relation to the shape of the whole. If all dimensions are below 0.2 cm., use *DISINTEGRATED OR GROUND*. Examples are: bread slice, cubed beef, sliced carrot, cut green beans, apple ring, shredded cabbage or cheese.

FOODON:03430140.label: whole, shape achieved by forming, thickness 0.3-1.5 cm.

FOODON:03430105.label: whole, shape achieved by forming, thickness 1.5-7 cm.
