France is divided into 26 administrative regions. 22 are in metropolitan France (21 are on the continental part of metropolitan France; one is the territorial collectivity of Corsica), and four are overseas regions. The regions are further subdivided into 100 departments which are numbered (mainly alphabetically). Four of these departments are found in the overseas regions and are simultaneously overseas regions and overseas departments and are an integral part of France (and the European Union) and thus enjoy a status similar to metropolitan departments. The 100 departments are subdivided into 341 arrondissements which are, in turn, subdivided into 4,032 cantons. These cantons are then divided into 36,680 communes, which are municipalities with an elected municipal council. There also exist 2,588 intercommunal entities grouping 33,414 of the 36,680 communes (i.e. 91.1% of all the communes). Three communes, Paris, Lyon and Marseille are also subdivided into 45 municipal arrondissements.

GAZ:00002635.label: Kingdom of Denmark
GAZ:00002635.definition: A nation situated in Scandinavia in northern Europe (Metropolitan Denmark) plus its two autonomous provinces, Greenland and The Faroe Islands. Denmark is divided into five regions and a total of 98 municipalities, plus two autonomous provinces.

GAZ:00002699.label: Kingdom of Norway
GAZ:00002699.definition: A country and constitutional monarchy in Northern Europe that occupies the western portion of the Scandinavian Peninsula. It is bordered by Sweden, Finland, and Russia. The Kingdom of Norway also includes the Arctic island territories of Svalbard and Jan Mayen. Norwegian sovereignty over Svalbard is based upon the Svalbard Treaty, but that treaty does not apply to Jan Mayen. Bouvet Island in the South Atlantic Ocean and Peter I Island and Queen Maud Land in Antarctica are external dependencies, but those three entities do not form part of the kingdom.

GAZ:00000591.label: Kingdom of Spain
GAZ:00000591.definition: A country located in southwestern Europe on the Iberian Peninsula, plus the Balearic Islands in the Mediterranean, the Canary Islands in the Atlantic Ocean off the African coast, and two autonomous cities in North Africa that border Morocco. Spain is politically organized into 17 Autonomous Communities (comunidades autonomas) and 2 autonomous cities (ciudades autonomas) - Ceuta and Melilla. Administratively Spain also comprises fifty provinces. Seven autonomous communities are composed of only one province: Asturias, Balearic Islands, Cantabria, La Rioja, Madrid, Murcia, and Navarre. Historically, some provinces are also divided into comarcas (roughly equivalent to a US "county" or an English district). The lowest administrative division of Spain is the municipality (municipio).

GAZ:00001549.label: Kingdom of the Netherlands
GAZ:00001549.definition: An association with federal characteristics (federacy), based on a political compact, which consists of three constituent countries: the Netherlands in Western Europe, and the Netherlands Antilles and Aruba in the Caribbean.

GAZ:00000468.label: Oceania
GAZ:00000468.definition: A grouping term including Australia, New Zealand, the southwestern islands of the Pacific Ocean and the eastern islands of the Australasian Mediterranean Sea.

GAZ:00002944.label: Portuguese Republic
GAZ:00002944.definition: A country in southwestern Europe on the Iberian Peninsula and including the Atlantic archipelagos of the Azores and Madeira are also part of Portugal. Portugal is divided into 308 municipalities (Portuguese singular/plural: concelho/concelhos), which are subdivided into more than 4,000 parishes (freguesia/freguesias). Municipalities are grouped for administrative purposes into superior units. For continental Portugal the municipalities are gathered in 18 Districts, while the Islands have a Regional Government directly above them.

GAZ:00003944.label: Region d'outre-mer
GAZ:00003944.definition: Overseas regions of France which have the same status as metropolitan regions.

GAZ:00009715.label: Tuvalu
GAZ:00009715.definition: A Polynesian island nation located in the Pacific Ocean midway between Hawaii and Australia.

GAZ:00002459.label: United States of America
GAZ:00002459.definition: A federal constitutional republic comprising fifty states and a federal district. The country is situated mostly in central North America, where its forty-eight contiguous states and Washington, DC, the capital district, lie between the Pacific and Atlantic Oceans, bordered by Canada to the north and Mexico to the south. The State of Alaska is in the northwest of the continent, with Canada to its east and Russia to the west across the Bering Strait, and the State of Hawaii is in the mid-Pacific. The United States also possesses several territories, or insular areas, that are scattered around the Caribbean and Pacific. The states are divided into smaller administrative regions, called counties in most states, exceptions being Alaska (parts of the state are organized into subdivisions called boroughs; the rest of the state's territory that is not included in any borough is divided into "census areas"), and Louisiana (which is divided into county-equivalents that are called parishes). There are also independent cities which are within particular states but not part of any particular county or consolidated city-counties. Another type of organization is where the city and county are unified and function as an independent city. There are thirty-nine independent cities in Virginia and other independent cities or city-counties are San Francisco, California, Baltimore, Maryland, St. Louis, Missouri, Denver, Colorado and Carson City, Nevada. Counties can include a number of cities, towns, villages, or hamlets, or sometimes just a part of a city. Counties have varying degrees of political and legal significance, but they are always administrative divisions of the state. Counties in many states are further subdivided into townships, which, by definition, are administrative divisions of a county. In some states, such as Michigan, a township can file a charter with the state government, making itself into a "charter township", which is a type of mixed municipal and township status (giving the township some of the rights of a city without all of the responsibilities), much in the way a metropolitan municipality is a mixed municipality and county.

GAZ:00000013.label: continent
GAZ:00000013.definition: One of the large, unbroken masses of land into which the Earth's surface is divided.

GAZ:00051031.label: Australasian Mediterranean Sea
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Seas of the East Indian Archipelago {alternative name}

GAZ:00002820.label: Caribbean Sea
GAZ:00002820.definition: A sea situated between the northern coast of South America, the eastern coast of Central America and the islands of the West Indies. Limits are the following: On the North: A line joining Cape Catoche Light (21 Degrees 36 Minutes N - 87 Degrees 04 Minutes 30 Seconds W), on the northeastern coast of Yucatan in Mexico, eastward to Cape San Antonio Light (21 Degrees 52 Minutes N - 84 Degrees 57 Minutes W), the western extremity of Cuba (the common limit with the Gulf of Mexico); thence from Cape San Antonio Light eastward, through Cuba, to Caleta Point (20 Degrees 04 Minutes N - 74 Degrees 17 Minutes 45 Seconds W), on the southeastern coast of this island; thence a line joining Caleta Point southeastward to Pearl Point (19 Degrees 39 Minutes 15 Seconds N - 73 Degrees 25 Minutes 15 Seconds W), on the northwestern coast of Haiti; thence from Pearl Point eastward, through Haiti and Dominican Republic, to Cape Engano (18 Degrees 36 Minutes 30 Seconds N - 68 Degrees 19 Minutes 30 Seconds W), the eastern extremity of the Dominican Republic; thence a line joining Cape Engano eastward to Borinquen Point (18 Degrees 28 Minutes 45 Seconds N - 67 Degrees 10 Minutes W), on the northwestern coast of Puerto Rico; and thence from Borinquen Point eastward, through this island, to Chiquita Point (18 Degrees 22 Minutes 55 Seconds N - 65 Degrees 38 Minutes 40 Seconds W), on the northeastern coast thereof. On the East: A line joining Chiquita Point, on the northeastern coast of Puerto Rico, northward, along the meridian of 65 Degrees 38 Minutes 40 Seconds W, to the 200 metre contour line (approximately 18 Degrees 30 Minutes N - 65 Degrees 38 Minutes 40 Seconds W); thence from this approximate position eastward and southward to Galera Point (10 Degrees 50 Minutes 10 Seconds N - 60 Degrees 54 Minutes 30 Seconds W), the northeastern extremity of Trinidad Island - in such a way that all islands, shoals and narrow waters between Puerto Rico and Trinidad Island are included in the Caribbean Sea; thence from Galera Point southward, through Trinidad Island, to Galeota Point (10 Degrees 08 Minutes 15 Seconds N - 60 Degrees 59 Minutes 30 Seconds W), the southeastern extremity of this island; and thence a line joining Galeota Point southward to Baja Point (9 Degrees 31 Minutes N - 60 Degrees 58 Minutes W), on the eastern coast of Venezuela. On the South and the West: From Baja Point, in Venezuela, westward and northward, along the northern coast of South America and the eastern coast of Central America, to Cape Catoche Light (21 Degrees 36 Minutes N - 87 Degrees 04530 Seconds W), on the northeastern coast of Yucatan, in Mexico.

GAZ:00002566.label: Province of Alberta
GAZ:00002566.definition: One of Canada's prairie provinces. It became a province on 1905-09-01. Alberta is located in western Canada, bounded by the provinces of British Columbia to the west and Saskatchewan to the east, Northwest Territories to the north, and by the State of Montana to the south. Statistics Canada divides the province of Alberta into nineteen census divisions, each with one or more municipal governments overseeing county municipalities, improvement districts, special areas, specialized municipalities, municipal districts, regional municipalities, cities, towns, villages, summer villages, Indian settlements, and Indian reserves. Census divisions are not a unit of local government in Alberta.

GAZ:00002562.label: Province of British Columbia
GAZ:00002562.definition: The westernmost of Canada's provinces. British Columbia is bordered by the Pacific Ocean on the west, by the American State of Alaska on the northwest, and to the north by the Yukon and the Northwest Territories, on the east by the province of Alberta, and on the south by the States of Washington, Idaho, and Montana. The current southern border of British Columbia was established by the 1846 Oregon Treaty, although its history is tied with lands as far south as the California border. British Columbia's rugged coastline stretches for more than 27,000 km, and includes deep, mountainous fjords and about 6,000 islands, most of which are uninhabited. British Columbia is carved into 27 regional districts. These regional districts are federations of member municipalities and electoral areas. The unincorporated area of the regional district is carved into electoral areas.

GAZ:00002571.label: Province of Manitoba
GAZ:00002571.definition: One of Canada's 10 provinces. Manitoba is located at the longitudinal centre of Canada, although it is considered to be part of Western Canada. It borders Saskatchewan to the west, Ontario to the east, Nunavut and Hudson Bay to the north, and the American states of North Dakota and Minnesota to the south. Statistics Canada divides the province of Manitoba into 23 census divisions. Census divisions are not a unit of local government in Manitoba.

GAZ:00002570.label: Province of New Brunswick
GAZ:00002570.definition: One of Canada's three Maritime provinces. New Brunswick is bounded on the north by Quebec's Gaspe Peninsula and by Chaleur Bay. Along the east coast, the Gulf of Saint Lawrence and Northumberland Strait form the boundaries. In the south-east corner of the province, the narrow Isthmus of Chignecto connects New Brunswick to the Nova Scotia peninsula. The south of the province is bounded by the Bay of Fundy, which has the highest tides in the world with a rise of 16 m. To the west, the province borders the American State of Maine. New Brunswick is divided into 15 counties, which no longer have administrative roles except in the court system. The counties are divided into parishes.

GAZ:00002567.label: Province of Newfoundland and Labrador
GAZ:00002567.definition: A province of Canada, the tenth and latest to join the Confederation. Geographically, the province consists of the island of Newfoundland and the mainland Labrador, on Canada's Atlantic coast.

GAZ:00002565.label: Province of Nova Scotia
GAZ:00002565.definition: A Canadian province located on Canada's southeastern coast. The province's mainland is the Nova Scotia peninsula surrounded by the Atlantic Ocean, including numerous bays and estuaries. No where in Nova Scotia is more than 67 km from the ocean. Cape Breton Island, a large island to the northeast of the Nova Scotia mainland, is also part of the province, as is Sable Island.

GAZ:00002563.label: Province of Ontario
GAZ:00002563.definition: A province located in the central part of Canada. Ontario is bordered by the provinces of Manitoba to the west, Quebec to the east, and the States of Michigan, New York, and Minnesota. Most of Ontario's borders with the United States are natural, starting at the Lake of the Woods and continuing through the four Great Lakes: Superior, Huron (which includes Georgian Bay), Erie, and Ontario (for which the province is named), then along the Saint Lawrence River near Cornwall. Ontario is the only Canadian Province that borders the Great Lakes. There are three different types of census divisions: single-tier municipalities, upper-tier municipalities (which can be regional municipalities or counties) and districts.

GAZ:00002572.label: Province of Prince Edward Island
GAZ:00002572.definition: A Canadian province consisting of an island of the same name. It is divided into 3 counties.

GAZ:00002569.label: Province of Quebec
GAZ:00002569.definition: A province in the central part of Canada. Quebec is Canada's largest province by area and its second-largest administrative division; only the territory of Nunavut is larger. It is bordered to the west by the province of Ontario, James Bay and Hudson Bay, to the north by Hudson Strait and Ungava Bay, to the east by the Gulf of Saint Lawrence and the provinces of Newfoundland and Labrador and New Brunswick. It is bordered on the south by the American states of Maine, New Hampshire, Vermont, and New York. It also shares maritime borders with the Territory of Nunavut, the Province of Prince Edward Island and the Province of Nova Scotia.

GAZ:00002564.label: Province of Saskatchewan
GAZ:00002564.definition: A prairie province in Canada. Saskatchewan is bounded on the west by Alberta, on the north by the Northwest Territories, on the east by Manitoba, and on the south by the States of Montana and North Dakota. It is divided into 18 census divisions according to Statistics Canada.

GAZ:00002575.label: Northwest Territories
GAZ:00002575.definition: A territory of Canada. Located in northern Canada, it borders Canada's two other territories, Yukon to the west and Nunavut to the east, and three provinces: British Columbia to the southwest, Alberta to the south, and Saskatchewan to the southeast. The present-day territory was created in 1870-06, when the Hudson's Bay Company transferred Rupert's Land and North-Western Territory to the government of Canada.

GAZ:00002574.label: Nunavut
GAZ:00002574.definition: The largest and newest territory of Canada; it was separated officially from the Northwest Territories on 1999-04-01. The Territory covers about 1.9 million km2 of land and water in Northern Canada including part of the mainland, most of the Arctic Archipelago, and all of the islands in Hudson Bay, James Bay, and Ungava Bay (including the Belcher Islands) which belonged to the Northwest Territories. Nunavut has land borders with the Northwest Territories on several islands as well as the mainland, a border with Manitoba to the south of the Nunavut mainland, and a tiny land border with Newfoundland and Labrador on Killiniq Island. It also shares aquatic borders with the provinces of Quebec, Ontario and Manitoba and with Greenland.

GAZ:00002576.label: Yukon
GAZ:00002576.definition: The westernmost of Canada's three territories. The territory is the approximate shape of a right triangle, bordering the American State of Alaska to the west, the Northwest Territories to the east and British Columbia to the south. Its northern coast is on the Beaufort Sea. Its ragged eastern boundary mostly follows the divide between the Yukon Basin and the Mackenzie River drainage basin to the east in the Mackenzie mountains. Its capital is Whitehorse.

GAZ:00005909.label: Australian Antarctic Territory
GAZ:00005909.definition: The part of Antarctica claimed by Australia. It consists of all the islands and territory south of 60degS and between 44deg38minE and 160degE, except for Adelie Land (136deg11minE to 142deg02minE), which divides the territory into Western AAT (the larger portion) and Eastern AAT. It is bounded by Queen Maud Land in the West and by Ross Dependency in the East.

GAZ:00002788.label: Australian Capital Territory
GAZ:00002788.definition: The capital territory of the Commonwealth of Australia and its smallest self-governing internal territory. It is an inland enclave in New South Wales, situated in bushland. The ACT is bounded by the Goulburn-Cooma railway line in the east, the watershed of Naas Creek in the south, the watershed of the Cotter River in the west, and the watershed of the Molonglo River in the north-east.

GAZ:00005917.label: Coral Sea Islands Territory
GAZ:00005917.definition: A Territory of Australia which includes a group of small and mostly uninhabited tropical islands and reefs in the Coral Sea, northeast of Queensland, Australia. The only inhabited island is Willis Island. The territory covers 780,000 km2, extending east and south from the outer edge of the Great Barrier Reef, and including Heralds Beacon Island, Osprey Reef, the Willis Group, and fifteen other reef/island groups.

GAZ:00005918.label: Heard Island and McDonald Islands Territory
GAZ:00005918.definition: A group of uninhabited, barren islands located in the Southern Ocean, about two-thirds of the way from Madagascar to Antarctica, or 7718 km due south of Rajapur, Maharashtra. They have been territories of Australia since 1947.

GAZ:00002794.label: Jervis Bay Territory
GAZ:00002794.definition: A territory of the Commonwealth of Australia. It was bought by the Commonwealth Government in 1915 from the State of New South Wales so that the Federal capital at Canberra would have access to the sea. It was part of the Australian Capital Territory until 1989 when the Australian Capital Territory achieved self government, after which it became a separate territory administered by the Minister for Territories.

GAZ:00002787.label: Northern Territory
GAZ:00002787.definition: A federal territory of Australia, occupying much of the center of the mainland continent, as well as the central northern regions. It shares borders with Western Australia to the west, South Australia to the south, and Queensland to the east. To the north, the territory is bordered by the Timor Sea, the Arafura Sea and the Gulf of Carpentaria.

GAZ:00005901.label: Territory of Ashmore and Cartier Islands
GAZ:00005901.definition: A Territory of Australia that includes two groups of small low-lying uninhabited tropical islands in the Indian Ocean situated on the edge of the continental shelf north-west of Australia and south of the Indonesian island of Roti.

GAZ:00005914.label: Territory of Christmas Island
GAZ:00005914.definition: A small territory of Australia located in the Indian Ocean, 2600 km northwest of Perth in Western Australia, 500 km south of Jakarta, Indonesia, and 975 km ENE of the Cocos (Keeling) Islands.

GAZ:00005908.label: Territory of Norfolk Island
GAZ:00005908.definition: A Territory of Australia that includes Norfolk Island and neighboring islands.

GAZ:00005916.label: Territory of the Cocos (Keeling) Islands
GAZ:00005916.definition: A territory of Australia. There are two atolls and twenty-seven coral islands in the group. The islands are located in the Indian Ocean, about half way from Australia to Sri Lanka.

GAZ:00003093.label: Midwest Region
GAZ:00003093.definition: A census region in the United States of America

GAZ:00003095.label: Northeast Region
GAZ:00003095.definition: A census region in the United States of America

GAZ:00003094.label: South Region
GAZ:00003094.definition: A census region in the United States of America

GAZ:00003096.label: West Region
GAZ:00003096.definition: A census region in the United States of America

GAZ:00003203.label: Hong Kong
GAZ:00003203.definition: A special administrative region of the People's Republic of China (PRC). The territory lies on the eastern side of the Pearl River Delta, bordering Guangdong province in the north and facing the South China Sea in the east, west and south. Hong Kong was a crown colony of the United Kingdom from 1842 until the transfer of its sovereignty to the People's Republic of China in 1997.

GAZ:00003202.label: Macau
GAZ:00003202.definition: One of the two special administrative regions of the People's Republic of China, the other being Hong Kong. Macau lies on the western side of the Pearl River Delta, bordering Guangdong province in the north and facing the South China Sea in the east and south. Macau is situated 60 kmsouthwest of Hong Kong and 145 km from Guangzhou. It consists of the Macau Peninsula itself and the islands of Taipa and Coloane. The peninsula is formed by the Zhujiang (Pearl River) estuary on the east and the Xijiang (West River) on the west. It borders the Zhuhai Special Economic Zone in mainland China.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Zhonghua Renmin Gongheguo Aomen Tebie Xingzhengqu {language: Chinese}
Macau Special Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China
Regiao Administrativa Especial de Macau da Republica Popular da China

GAZ:00003209.label: Puntarenas Province
GAZ:00003209.definition: A province of Costa Rica. It is located in the western part of the country, covering most of Costa Rica's Pacific Ocean coast, and it is the largest province in Costa Rica. Clockwise from the northwest it borders on the provinces Guanacaste, Alajuela, San Jose and Limon, and the neighbouring country of Panama.

GAZ:00003731.label: Bali Province
GAZ:00003731.definition: A province of Indonesia with the provincial capital at Denpasar towards the south of the island. Located on the island of Bali and satellite islands.

GAZ:02000610.label: Papua Province
GAZ:02000610.definition: The largest province of Indonesia, comprising a majority part of the western half of the island of New Guinea and nearby islands (see also Western New Guinea). The province originally covered the entire western half of New Guinea, but in 2003, the western portion of the province, on the Bird's Head Peninsula, was declared by the Indonesian Government as a separate province named West Papua.

GAZ:00002918.label: French Polynesia
GAZ:00002918.definition: A French overseas collectivity in the southern Pacific Ocean. It is made up of several groups of Polynesian islands. French Polynesia has five administrative subdivisions (French: subdivisions administratives).

GAZ:00003943.label: Mayotte
GAZ:00003943.definition: An overseas collectivity of France consisting of a main island, Grande-Terre (or Mahore), a smaller island, Petite-Terre (or Pamanzi), and several islets around these two.

GAZ:00005206.label: New Caledonia
GAZ:00005206.definition: A "sui generis collectivity" (in practice an overseas territory) of France, made up of a main island (Grande Terre), the Loyalty Islands, and several smaller islands. It is located in the region of Melanesia in the southwest Pacific. Administratively, the archipelago is divided into three provinces, and then into 33 communes.

GAZ:00005841.label: Saint Martin
GAZ:00005841.definition: An overseas collectivity of France that came into being on 2007-02-22, encompassing the northern parts of the island of Saint Martin and neighboring islets. The southern part of the island, Sint Maarten, is part of the Netherlands Antilles. Formerly, with Saint-Barthelemy, an arrondissement of Guadeloupe.

GAZ:00003942.label: Saint-Pierre and Miquelon
GAZ:00003942.definition: An Overseas Collectivity of France located in a group of small islands in the North Atlantic Ocean, the main ones being Saint Pierre and Miquelon, 25 km off the coast of Newfoundland, Canada. Saint Pierre and Miquelon became an overseas department in 1976, but its status changed to that of an Overseas collectivity in 1985.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Territorial Collectivity of Saint Pierre and Miquelon

GAZ:00003957.label: American Samoa
GAZ:00003957.definition: An unincorporated territory of the United States located in the South Pacific Ocean, southeast of the sovereign State of Samoa. The main (largest and most populous) island is Tutuila, with the Manu'a Islands, Rose Atoll, and Swains Island also included in the territory.

GAZ:00006935.label: Commonwealth of Puerto Rico
GAZ:00006935.definition: A semi-autonomous territory composed of an archipelago in the northeastern Caribbean, east of the Dominican Republic and west of the Virgin Islands, approximately 2,000 km off the coast of Florida (the nearest of the mainland United States).
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Estado Libre Asociado de Puerto Rico

GAZ:00003706.label: Territory of Guam
GAZ:00003706.definition: An unincorporated territory of the United States.

GAZ:00007113.label: United States Minor Outlying Islands
GAZ:00007113.definition: A statistical designation defined by ISO3166-1, consists of nine insular United States possessions. Palmyra Atoll is the only incorporated territory of the United States. Currently, none of the islands have any permanent residents.

GAZ:00003959.label: United States Virgin Islands
GAZ:00003959.definition: A group of islands in the Caribbean that are an insular area of the United States. The islands are geographically part of the Virgin Islands archipelago and are located in the Leeward Islands of the Lesser Antilles. The US Virgin Islands are an organized, unincorporated United States territory. The US Virgin Islands are administratively divided into two districts and subdivided into 20 sub-districts.

GAZ:00009159.label: Anguilla
GAZ:00009159.definition: A British overseas territory in the Caribbean, one of the most northerly of the Leeward Islands in the Lesser Antilles. It consists of the main island of Anguilla itself, approximately 26 km long by 5 km wide at its widest point, together with a number of much smaller islands and cays with no permanent population.

GAZ:00001264.label: Bermuda
GAZ:00001264.definition: A British overseas territory in the North Atlantic Ocean. Located off the east coast of the United States, it is situated around 1770 km NE of Miami, Florida and 1350 km S of Halifax, Nova Scotia. Comprised of approximately 138 islands.

GAZ:00003985.label: British Indian Ocean Territory
GAZ:00003985.definition: An overseas territory of the United Kingdom situated in the Indian Ocean, halfway between Africa and Indonesia. The territory comprises the six atolls of the Chagos Archipelago with over 1,000 individual islands.

GAZ:00003961.label: British Virgin Islands
GAZ:00003961.definition: A British overseas territory, located in the Caribbean to the east of Puerto Rico. The islands make up part of the Virgin Islands archipelago, the remaining islands constituting the US Virgin Islands. The British Virgin Islands consist of the main islands of Tortola, Virgin Gorda, Anegada and Jost Van Dyke, along with over fifty other smaller islands and cays. Approximately fifteen of the islands are inhabited.

GAZ:00003986.label: Cayman Islands
GAZ:00003986.definition: A British overseas territory located in the western Caribbean Sea, comprising the islands of Grand Cayman, Cayman Brac, and Little Cayman. The Cayman Islands are divided into seven districts.

GAZ:00001412.label: Falkland Islands
GAZ:00001412.definition: An archipelago in the South Atlantic Ocean, located 483 km from the coast of Argentina, 1,080 km west of the Shag Rocks (South Georgia), and 940 km north of Antarctica (Elephant Island). They consist of two main islands, East Falkland and West Falkland, together with 776 smaller islands.

GAZ:00003987.label: Gibraltar
GAZ:00003987.definition: A British overseas territory located near the southernmost tip of the Iberian Peninsula overlooking the Strait of Gibraltar. The territory shares a border with Spain to the north.

GAZ:00003988.label: Montserrat
GAZ:00003988.definition: A British overseas territory located in the Leeward Islands. Montserrat is divided into three parishes.

GAZ:00005867.label: Pitcairn, Henderson, Ducie and Oeno Islands
GAZ:00005867.definition: A group of four islands in the southern Pacific Ocean. The Pitcairn Islands form the southeasternmost extension of the geological archipelago of the Tuamotus of French Polynesia.

GAZ:00003955.label: Turks and Caicos Islands
GAZ:00003955.definition: A British Overseas Territory consisting of two groups of tropical islands in the West Indies. The Turks and Caicos Islands are divided into six administrative districts (two in the Turks Islands and four in the Caicos Islands.

GAZ:00000847.label: Azores
GAZ:00000847.definition: A Portuguese archipelago in the Atlantic Ocean. It forms the Autonomous Region of the Azores, one of the two autonomous regions of Portugal.

GAZ:00014424.label: Nanumanga District
GAZ:00014424.definition: A local government district of Tuvala.

GAZ:00002286.label: English Channel
GAZ:00002286.definition: A channel situated between the southern coast of England and the northern coast of France and linking the North Sea and the Celtic Sea, are the following: On the North: The southern coast of England, from Land's End (50 Degrees 04 Minutes 06 Seconds N - 5 Degrees 42 Minutes 54 Seconds W) eastward to Hope Point (51 Degrees 10 Minutes N - 1 Degrees 24 Minutes 14 Seconds E). On the East: A line joining Hope Point, in England, southeastward to Walde Lighthouse (50 Degrees 59 Minutes 40 Seconds N - 1 Degrees 54 Minutes 58 Seconds E), on the northeastern coast of France (the common limit with the North Sea). On the South: The northern coast of France, from Walde Lighthouse southwestward to Isle Vierge (48 Degrees 38 Minutes 26 Seconds N - 4 Degrees 34 Minutes 13 Seconds W). On the West: A line joining Isle Vierge, in France, northwestward to Land's End (50 Degrees 04 Minutes 06 Seconds N - 5 Degrees 42 Minutes 54 Seconds W), on the southwestern coast of England (the common limit with the Celtic Sea).

GAZ:00002285.label: Irish Sea
GAZ:00002285.definition: A sea situated between the eastern coast of Ireland and the western coasts of Scotland, England and Wales, are the following: On the North: A line joining Ballyquintin Point (54 Degrees 19 Minutes 55 Seconds N - 5 Degrees 30 Minutes W), in Ireland, northeastward to the southeastern extremity of Mull of Galloway (54 Degrees 38 Minutes N - 4 Degrees 51 Minutes 20 Seconds W), in Scotland (the common limit with the Inner Seas). On the East: From the southeastern extremity of Mull of Galloway eastward and southward, along the coasts of Scotland, England and Wales, to St. David's Head (51 Degrees 54 Minutes 10 Seconds N - 5 Degrees 18 Minutes 48 Seconds W), in Wales. On the South: A line joining St. David's Head, in Wales, northwestward to Carnsore Point (52 Degrees 10 Minutes 23 Seconds N - 6 Degrees 21 Minutes 48 Seconds W), in Ireland (the common limit with the Celtic Sea). On the West: From Carnsore Point northward, along the eastern coast of Ireland, to Ballyquintin Point (54 Degrees 19 Minutes 55 Seconds N - 5 Degrees 30 Minutes W).

GAZ:00002287.label: Mediterranean Sea
GAZ:00002287.definition: An enclosed sea opening only, on the West, to the North Atlantic Ocean through the Strait of Gibraltar and, on the Northeast, to the Sea of Marmara through the Dardanelles (Canakkale Strait). It is bounded by the coasts of South Europe, West Asia and North Africa. The limit between the Mediterranean Sea and the North Atlantic Ocean (in the western entrance of the Strait of Gibraltar) is the following: A line joining Cape Trafalgar (36 Degrees 11 Minutes N - 6 Degrees 02 Minutes W), on the southern coast of Spain, southward to Cape Espartel (35 Degrees 47 Minutes 36 Seconds N - 5 Degrees 55 Minutes 24 Seconds W), on the northern coast of Morocco. The limit between the Mediterranean Sea and the Sea of Marmara (in the western entrance of the Dardanelles (Canakkale Strait), on the northwestern coast of Turkey) is the following: A line joining Mehmetcik Cape (40 Degrees 02 Minutes 40 Seconds N - 26 Degrees 10 Minutes 30 Seconds E) southward to Kumale Cape (40 Degrees 00 Minutes 35 Seconds N - 26 Degrees 11 Minutes 55 Seconds E).

GENEPIO:0000112.label: GSCID-BRC Core Project standard
GENEPIO:0000112.definition: A Core Project item is a field in the GSCID/BRC Project and Sample Application Core Project Standard.

GENEPIO:0000111.label: GSCID-BRC Core Sample standard
GENEPIO:0000111.definition: The GSCID-BRC Core Sample Standard is an extension of the GMI MDM data standard

UBERON:0000061.label: anatomical structure
UBERON:0000061.definition: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.

PO:0009011.label: plant structure
PO:0009011.definition: An anatomical structure that is or was part of a plant, or was derived from a part of a plant.

NCIT:C25610.label: Pathologic
NCIT:C25610.definition: Caused by or altered by or manifesting disease or pathology.

GENEPIO:0001636.label: animal body product
GENEPIO:0001636.definition: A product of an animal, as in blood, feces, sputum, etc. that has no particular anatomical site

GENEPIO:0000033.label: fecal indicator bacteria count
GENEPIO:0000033.definition: Number of indicator micro-organisms (colony forming units) present in a sample that have been used to suggest the presence of pathogens.

GENEPIO:0000046.label: PFGE primary test
GENEPIO:0000046.definition: First PFGE pattern from given diagnostic restriction enzyme

GENEPIO:0000048.label: PFGE secondary test
GENEPIO:0000048.definition: Second PFGE pattern from given diagnostic restriction enzyme

OBI:0000697.label: Helicos sequencing
OBI:0000697.definition: is a DNA sequencing which allows sequence identification of billions of DNA molecules immobilized to a surface by using DNA polymerase and fluorescently labeled nucleotides added one at a time. The sequencing process does not requires amplification step and is typically able to produce reads of 25 base pair length.

GENEPIO:0001765.label: 1 - standard draft
GENEPIO:0001765.definition: Standard draft: describing the minimum information needed for submission to a public database.

GENEPIO:0001766.label: 2 - high quality draft
GENEPIO:0001766.definition: High quality draft: describing sequences with little to no manual review.

GENEPIO:0001767.label: 3 - improved high quality draft
GENEPIO:0001767.definition: Improved high quality draft: in which data is either reviewed by people or machines to some extent to indicate that most of the genetic data is assembled correctly, but some errors may still be present.

GENEPIO:0001768.label: 4 - annotation-directed improvement
GENEPIO:0001768.definition: Annotation-directed improvement: in which genetic information in various gene regions is represented as accurately as possible.

GENEPIO:0001769.label: 5 - non-contiguous finished
GENEPIO:0001769.definition: Non-contiguous finished: which includes sequences that have been reviewed by both people and machines and would be considered complete except for “recalcitrant regions” that are proving problematic for genome closure.

GENEPIO:0001770.label: 6 - finished
GENEPIO:0001770.definition: Finished: which describes un-gapped complete sequences that have minimal errors, if any. The biology of the microbe will determine whether this finished genome consists of more than one chromosome.

GENEPIO:0001633.label: contig L50
GENEPIO:0001633.definition: Contig L50 is the number of contigs equal to or longer than contig N50. The length of the assembly itself is used in the calculation.

GENEPIO:0001774.label: contig L99
GENEPIO:0001774.definition: Contig L99 is the number of contigs equal to or longer than contig N99. The length of the assembly itself is used in the calculation.

GENEPIO:0001773.label: contig LG50
GENEPIO:0001773.definition: Contig L50 is the number of contigs equal to or longer than contig N50. The length of the assembly itself is used in the calculation.

GENEPIO:0001634.label: contig LG99
GENEPIO:0001634.definition: The LG99 count is like the L99 count except that the length of the reference genome is used in the calculation rather than the sum of assembly contig lengths.

GENEPIO:0001571.label: contig count QC threshold
GENEPIO:0001571.definition:
The upper threshold of contig counts that are acceptable in a genome assembly.  This may vary based on the overall genome length and depth of coverage.

A large contig count may indicate insufficient read coverage.

GENEPIO:0002109.label: draft EBI antimicrobial susceptibility test V. 2017-08-30
GENEPIO:0002109.definition: A standard for European Bioinformatics Institute (EBI) antibiogram data submission

GENEPIO:0002129.label: draft Enterobase contextual data standard
GENEPIO:0002129.definition: This is a draft (under development) collection of fields for capturing the contextual data for Enterobase (https://enterobase.warwick.ac.uk/) records.

GENEPIO:0001741.label: draft GenEpiO component record
GENEPIO:0001741.definition: This class contains components under development for fulfilling GenEpiO and other standard data specifications. Components are relevant to epidemiological, laboratory, clinical or environmental pathogen sample data collection and analysis.

GENEPIO:0001829.label: draft IRIDA standard
GENEPIO:0001829.definition: A standard established for use by the Integrated Rapid Infectious Disease Analysis (IRIDA) project, which is a Canadian-led initiative to build an open source, end-to-end platform for infectious disease genomic epidemiology.

GENEPIO:0001778.label: draft PulseNet Canada Salmonella submission standard
GENEPIO:0001778.definition: The PulseNet Canada Salmonella submission standard details the fields required in a PuseNet Canada pathogen submission report for Salmonella in spreadsheet format

GENEPIO:0001000.label: draft ReSeq Tuberculosis data platform standard
GENEPIO:0001000.definition: The Relational Sequencing TB Data Platform (ReSeqTB) catalogs a vast amount of genotypic, phenotypic and related metadata from Mycobacterium tuberculosis (Mtb) strains to enable the development of clinically useful, WHO-endorsed in vitro diagnostic assays for rapid drug susceptibility testing of Mtb.

GENEPIO:0001100.label: draft antibiogram drug test model
GENEPIO:0001100.definition: This is the minimal set of parameters for drug test results for a particular antimicrobial agent.

GENEPIO:0002006.label: draft isolate whole genome sequencing model

GENEPIO:0000124.label: draft pathogenic epidemiology case investigation record
GENEPIO:0000124.definition: This is a model of the datums involved in an epidemiology investigation.

GENEPIO:0002083.label: draft sequence repository contextual data standard
GENEPIO:0002083.definition: This draft specification provides a collection of fields related to the contextual data of a specimen, its genomic sequencing, and its pathogenic epidemiology.

GENEPIO:0001073.label: draft tuberculosis - specimen contextual data standard
GENEPIO:0001073.definition: The tuberculosis draft standard is a GenEpiO set of draft genomic and clinical data items related to Mycobacterium tuberculosis that various agencies are using in their own reporting.

GENEPIO:0001777.label: draft tuberculosis contextual data standard
GENEPIO:0001777.definition: The draft tuberculosis contextual data standard is a data standard for the collection of contextual information of a given tuberculosis case that pertain to typing, clinical treatment, and potential research questions.

GENEPIO:0000144.label: draft whole genome sequencing lab test record
GENEPIO:0000144.definition: This is a set of datums involved in laboratory processing of whole-genome-sequenced isolates.

GENEPIO:0001007.label: NCBI Antibiogram standard
GENEPIO:0001007.definition: The NCBI antibiogram standard details the reporting specifications for antimicrobial susceptibility and resistance data derived from drug resistant pathogens. This information is submitted as an antibiogram table on BioSample records.

GENEPIO:0001836.label: NCBI BioProject standard
GENEPIO:0001836.definition: The National Center for Biotechnology Information BioProject standard is a collection of datums that describe biological data related to a single initiative, originating from a single organization or from a consortium.  A BioProject record provides users a single place to find links to the diverse data types generated for that project.

GENEPIO:0001835.label: NCBI BioSample Pathogen.cl standard
GENEPIO:0001835.definition: A National Center for Biotechnology Information BioSample specification defines fields and terms that provide "descriptions of biological source materials used in experimental assays".

GENEPIO:0000147.label: NCBI SRA meta information standard
GENEPIO:0000147.definition: An NCBI SRA meta information item is a field specification for a NCBI Sequence Read Archive record.

GENEPIO:0000122.label: travel end date
GENEPIO:0000122.definition: The date of a person's return to some residence from a journey originating at that residence.

GENEPIO:0000121.label: travel start date
GENEPIO:0000121.definition: The date of a person's departure from their primary residence (at that time) on a journey to one or more other locations.

GENEPIO:0000130.label: epi contact network model - animal
GENEPIO:0000130.definition: This is a model that provides location and transportation information about an animal that may be involved in transmitting a pathogen to a human or other animal.

GENEPIO:0000129.label: epi contact network model - human
GENEPIO:0000129.definition: An epi contact network - human is contact information about a person who may be involved in transmitting a pathogen.

GAZ:00003691.label: East Midlands Region
GAZ:00003691.definition: One of the regions of England and consists of most of the eastern half of the traditional region of the Midlands. It encompasses the combined area of Derbyshire, Leicestershire, Rutland, Northamptonshire, Nottinghamshire and most of Lincolnshire.

GAZ:00003692.label: East Region
GAZ:00003692.definition: One of the nine official regions of England. It includes the ceremonial counties of Essex, Hertfordshire, Bedfordshire, Cambridgeshire, Norfolk and Suffolk.

GAZ:00003671.label: Greater London Region
GAZ:00003671.definition: The top-level administrative subdivision covering London, England.

GAZ:00003689.label: North East Region
GAZ:00003689.definition: One of the nine official regions of England and comprises the combined area of Northumberland, County Durham, Tyne and Wear, part of North Yorkshire and Tees Valley.

GAZ:00003687.label: North West Region
GAZ:00003687.definition: One of the nine official regions of England. It comprises five counties of England, Cumbria, Lancashire, Greater Manchester, Merseyside and Cheshire.

GAZ:00003693.label: South East Region
GAZ:00003693.definition: One of the nine official regions of England. Its boundaries include Berkshire, Buckinghamshire, East Sussex, Hampshire, Isle of Wight, Kent, Oxfordshire, Surrey and West Sussex.

GAZ:00003670.label: South West Region
GAZ:00003670.definition: One of the regions of England. It extends from Gloucestershire and Wiltshire to Cornwall and the Isles of Scilly. This includes the area often known as the West Country, and much of Wessex.

GAZ:00003690.label: West Midlands Region
GAZ:00003690.definition: An official region of England, covering the western half of the area traditionally known as the Midlands. It contains the second most populated British city, Birmingham, and the larger West Midlands conurbation, which includes the city of Wolverhampton and large towns of Dudley, Solihull, Walsall and West Bromwich. The city of Coventry is also located within the West Midlands county, but is separated from the conurbation to the west by several miles of green belt.

GAZ:00003688.label: Yorkshire and the Humber
GAZ:00003688.definition: One of the nine government office regions of England. It covers most of the historic county of Yorkshire, along with the part of northern Lincolnshire that was, from 1974 to 1996, within the former shire county of Humberside.

GENEPIO:0000157.label: assembly project
GENEPIO:0000157.definition: Genome assembly project utilizing already existing sequence data including data that was submitted by a different group

GENEPIO:0000159.label: epigenomics project
GENEPIO:0000159.definition: A sequencing project involving DNA methylation, histone modification, and/or chromatin accessibility datasets

GENEPIO:0000161.label: genome sequencing project
GENEPIO:0000161.definition: A whole, or partial, genome sequencing project (with or without a genome assembly)

GENEPIO:0001103.label: map project
GENEPIO:0001103.definition: Map: - project that results in non-sequence map data such as genetic map, radiation hybrid map, cytogenetic map, optical map, and etc.

GENEPIO:0001105.label: metagenome assembly project
GENEPIO:0001105.definition: Metagenome assembly: a genome assembly generated from sequenced environmental samples

GENEPIO:0001104.label: metagenome project
GENEPIO:0001104.definition: Metagenome: sequence analysis of environmental samples

GENEPIO:0001106.label: other project data type
GENEPIO:0001106.definition: Other: a free text description is provided to indicate Other data type

GENEPIO:0001107.label: phenotype or genotype project
GENEPIO:0001107.definition: Phenotype or Genotype: project correlating phenotype and genotype

GENEPIO:0001108.label: proteome project
GENEPIO:0001108.definition: Proteome: large scale proteomics experiment including mass spec. analysis

GENEPIO:0001109.label: random survey project
GENEPIO:0001109.definition: Random Survey: sequence generated from a random sampling of the collected sample; not intended to be comprehensive sampling of the material.

GENEPIO:0001110.label: targeted locus (loci) project
GENEPIO:0001110.definition: Targeted locus (loci): project to sequence specific loci, such as a 16S rRNA sequencing

GENEPIO:0001111.label: transcriptome or gene expression
GENEPIO:0001111.definition: Transcriptome or Gene expression: large scale RNA sequencing or expression analysis. Includes cDNA, EST, RNA_seq, and microarray.

GENEPIO:0001112.label: variation project
GENEPIO:0001112.definition: A sequencing project with a primary goal of identifying large or small sequence variation across populations.

GENEPIO:0001002.label: less than
GENEPIO:0001002.definition: The "less than" comparator indicates that a given substance was present at less than a given quantity or concentration.

GENEPIO:0001003.label: less than or equal to
GENEPIO:0001003.definition: The "less than or equal to" comparator indicates that a given substance was present at less than or equal to a given quantity or concentration.

GENEPIO:0001004.label: equal to
GENEPIO:0001004.definition: The "equal to" comparator indicates that a given substance was present at the given quantity or concentration.

GENEPIO:0001006.label: greater than
GENEPIO:0001006.definition: The "greater than" comparator indicates that a given substance was present at greater than a given quantity or concentration.

GENEPIO:0001005.label: greater than or equal to
GENEPIO:0001005.definition: The "greater than or equal to" comparator indicates that a given substance was present at greater than or equal to a given quantity or concentration.

GENEPIO:0001036.label: treatment end date
GENEPIO:0001036.definition: A treatment end date is a date/time datum which indicates the end of a particular medical treatment for a patient.

GENEPIO:0001025.label: treatment start date
GENEPIO:0001025.definition: A treatment start date is a date/time datum which indicates the start of a particular medical treatment for a patient.

GENEPIO:0001097.label: second line or reserve tuberculosis drug

GENEPIO:0001046.label: immigration year of arrival
GENEPIO:0001046.definition: A time measurement datum indicating the year a person immigrated to a given country.

GENEPIO:0000120.label: travel history item
GENEPIO:0000120.definition: A datetime measurement related to a person's travel with respect to potential epidemilogical implications.

GENEPIO:0001270.label: animal exposure event - contact or activity

GENEPIO:0002078.label: number of passages
GENEPIO:0002078.definition: The number of serial iterations that an isolate is grown in one environment.

GENEPIO:0002079.label: passage protocol
GENEPIO:0002079.definition: A passage protocol should detail the number of serial iterations that an isolate is grown in one environment, and the conditions of that environment.

GENEPIO:0000123.label: infection aquired during travel
GENEPIO:0000123.definition: Infection aquired during travel is a boolean datum indicating a diagnosis of a traveller's infection during a given trip.

GENEPIO:0001783.label: travel destination
GENEPIO:0001783.definition: A travel destination is a destination city (or populated place of some scale) which a given human has travelled to on a particular trip.

GENEPIO:0001064.label: travel mode
GENEPIO:0001064.definition: A travel mode is a type of transportation which a given human has used while travelling on a particular trip.

GENEPIO:0001065.label: travel reason
GENEPIO:0001065.definition: A travel reason is a motivation for traveling on a particular trip expressed by the traveller.

NCIT:C68615.label: Birth Date
NCIT:C68615.definition: The calendar date on which a person was born.

NCIT:C70810.label: Date of Death
NCIT:C70810.definition: The calendar date of subject's death.

NCIT:C124295.label: Pregnant
NCIT:C124295.definition: Observed to be or have been pregnant.

NCIT:C106561.label: Pregnant During the Study
NCIT:C106561.definition: An indicator as to whether the female subject is pregnant during the study period.

EFO:0004324.label: body weights and measures
EFO:0004324.definition: Measurements of the height, weight, length, area, etc., of the human and animal body or its parts.

GENEPIO:0001094.label: country of birth
GENEPIO:0001094.definition: A country of birth is the country that a given person (or animal) was born in.

GENEPIO:0002019.label: host hospital service status
GENEPIO:0002019.definition: A host hospital service status indicates the state of a host's interaction with hospital medical services.

GENEPIO:0001058.label: human exposure event - travel datum
GENEPIO:0001058.definition: an epidemiology travel datum is a datum regarding a particular human's travel trip destination, mode, and motivation, with respect to an epidemiology investigation.

GENEPIO:0001196.label: specimen with confirmed presence of disease agent
GENEPIO:0001196.definition: A specimen which has been confirmed by laboratory test(s) to contain a disease-causing agent such as a pathogen

GENEPIO:0000114.label: subject age - unit
GENEPIO:0000114.definition: Age unit of the age measurement of a subject (individual organism).

GENEPIO:0001608.label: commensal role
GENEPIO:0001608.definition: An organism and its host share physical space but no evidence exists to determine if one benefits from this arrangement.

GENEPIO:0001238.label: symbiotic role
GENEPIO:0001238.definition: Organism has a symbiotic relationship with host

GENEPIO:0001537.label: person role
GENEPIO:0001537.definition: a role which inheres in a person and is realized by the process of being in the context of civilization

GENEPIO:0001787.label: genus of pathogen
GENEPIO:0001787.definition: This is the genus-level taxonomic name of an organism playing a pathogen role

GENEPIO:0001788.label: species of pathogen
GENEPIO:0001788.definition: This is the species-level taxonomic name of an organism playing a pathogen role

NCIT:C15346.label: Vaccination
NCIT:C15346.definition: Administration of vaccines to stimulate the host's immune response. This includes any preparation intended for active immunological prophylaxis or treatment.

OGMS:0000073.label: diagnosis
OGMS:0000073.definition: The representation of a conclusion of a diagnostic process.

GENEPIO:0001667.label: outcome of pregnancy associated with illness

BTO:0001762.label: neonate
BTO:0001762.definition: A newborn child; especially: a child less than a month old.

GENEPIO:0001186.label: infectious disease treatment
GENEPIO:0001186.definition: A course of treatment designed to resolve an infectious disease

GENEPIO:0000026.label: subject health status at time of specimen extraction
GENEPIO:0000026.definition: Health or disease status of a given subject at time of specimen extraction.

GENEPIO:0001247.label: animal specimen
GENEPIO:0001247.definition: A specimen extracted from an animal

GENEPIO:0001038.label: infection-specific food detail
GENEPIO:0001038.definition: Some bacteria are associated with particular foods.  Need relationship

NCIT:C71164.label: Animal Model
NCIT:C71164.definition: An animal that is amenable to experimentation and whose physiological or pathologic mechanisms are sufficiently similar to those of a human for the animal to serve as a model.

MESH:D057805.label: animal - pet
MESH:D057805.definition: Animals kept by humans for companionship and enjoyment, as opposed to DOMESTIC ANIMALS such as livestock or farm animals, which are kept for economic reasons.

MESH:D000835.label: animal - wild
MESH:D000835.definition: Animals considered to be wild or feral or not adapted for domestic use. It does not include wild animals in zoos for which ANIMALS, ZOO is available.

MESH:D058751.label: livestock
MESH:D058751.definition: Domesticated farm animals raised for home use or profit but excluding POULTRY. Typically livestock includes CATTLE; SHEEP; HORSES; SWINE; GOATS; and others.

NCIT:C16423.label: Child
NCIT:C16423.definition: A person who is not yet an adult. The specific cut-off age will vary by purpose.

NCIT:C42709.label: Parent
NCIT:C42709.definition: A mother or a father; an immediate progenitor.

NCIT:C25741.label: Physician
NCIT:C25741.definition: A doctor; a person who has been educated, trained, and licensed to practice the art and science of medicine; a practitioner of medicine, as contrasted with a surgeon.

GENEPIO:0001789.label: symptom cessation date
GENEPIO:0001789.definition: A symptom cessation date is a date-time entity that marks the end of one or more reported symptoms pertaining to an episode of human or animal illness

GENEPIO:0001784.label: symptom duration
GENEPIO:0001784.definition: A symptom duration is a date-time entity which is the duration (in hours or days or weeks etc.) that one or more symptoms persist for in a particular human or animal

FLU:0000976.label: symptom onset date
FLU:0000976.definition: A symptom onset date is a date-time entity that marks the start of one or more reported symptoms pertaining to an episode of human or animal illness

GENEPIO:0001755.label: contact specification
GENEPIO:0001755.definition: This is a collection of various human (and animal contact location) contact information specifications used in data standards.

GENEPIO:0000155.label: draft WGS lab assembly quality metrics record

GENEPIO:0000145.label: draft WGS lab bioinformatics process record

GENEPIO:0000154.label: draft WGS lab sequencing quality metrics record

GENEPIO:0000125.label: draft pathogenic epi case exposure record
GENEPIO:0000125.definition: The draft epi case exposure model describes datums related to the possible transmission of a pathogen between a case person and other people, places, animals etc.

GENEPIO:0000126.label: draft pathogenic epi case food record
GENEPIO:0000126.definition: A description of a food item that a case patient has come in contact with.

GENEPIO:0000132.label: draft pathogenic epi case general information record
GENEPIO:0000132.definition: An epi case general info model contains datum specifications about an epidemiology investigation case including the person involved, contact information and their demographics.

GENEPIO:0000133.label: draft pathogenic epi case isolate detail record
GENEPIO:0000133.definition: A record of the details around how, when, and from what an isolate was extracted.

GENEPIO:0000137.label: draft pathogenic epi case test record
GENEPIO:0000137.definition: A laboratory test performed on a specimen from a patient with regard to potential pathogenic disease.

GENEPIO:0000140.label: draft pathogenic epi case travel record
GENEPIO:0000140.definition: A record of a patient's recent travel - departure and return, mode of travel and locations visited - as it may pertain to an outbreak pathogen transmission event.

GENEPIO:0002088.label: draft sequence repository data - antibiogram
GENEPIO:0002088.definition: A dataset of the minimal inhibitory concentrations (value, unit, sign (<,>, =)) and resistance phenotypes (resistant, sensitive or undetermined) of the sequenced isolate against different antibiotics tested.

GENEPIO:0002112.label: draft sequence repository data - antibiogram MIC measurement
GENEPIO:0002112.definition: This is a component of an antibiogram that enables a choice of MIC measurements based on either the diffusion or dilution method. These methods call for different numeric input ranges and units.

GENEPIO:0002106.label: draft sequence repository data - food specimen
GENEPIO:0002106.definition: This specification offers food source, product type, packaging and processing attributes relevant to describing a food specimen.

GENEPIO:0002086.label: draft sequence repository data - geographic location
GENEPIO:0002086.definition: The geographical origin of the sample by city, region, country or latitude and logitude.

GENEPIO:0002087.label: draft sequence repository data - isolate passage history

GENEPIO:0002090.label: draft sequence repository data - sequencing quality control
GENEPIO:0002090.definition: Measurements or calculated quantities used to assess the extent and success of the sequence assembly process. Metric thresholds are species-specific.

GENEPIO:0002081.label: draft sequence repository data - specimen collection

GENEPIO:0002092.label: draft sequence repository data - submission to EBI

GENEPIO:0002091.label: draft sequence repository data - submission to NCBI/DDBJ

GENEPIO:0002089.label: draft sequence repository data - virulence
GENEPIO:0002089.definition: The virulence factors determined to be present in the sequenced isolate by phenotypic or target amplification methods e.g. Shiga toxins, hemolysins.

GENEPIO:0002108.label: draft travel log specification
GENEPIO:0002108.definition: This record details a person's travel movement and duration for epidemiological analysis.

GENEPIO:0001999.label: draft tuberculosis - dataset features and provenance

GENEPIO:0002168.label: drug MIC unit specification
GENEPIO:0002168.definition: The unit provided for an antibiotic drug test dosage.

GENEPIO:0001533.label: food specimen specification
GENEPIO:0001533.definition: A food specimen type is a categorization of a food specimen, by the organism it is or came from, or by a class of food products.

GENEPIO:0002139.label: raw sequence data processing datum
GENEPIO:0002139.definition: The procedures used to remove adapters from raw sequence reads, trim low quality bases and where applicable, merge paired-end reads.

GENEPIO:0002076.label: specimen extraction site - geographic feature
GENEPIO:0002076.definition: A landform, biome or built environment at site that a given specimen was extracted or collected from.

GENEPIO:0002174.label: specimen source substance specification
GENEPIO:0002174.definition: A specimen source substance is an organism substance or food product or environmental substance from which the specimen was extracted.

GENEPIO:0002140.label: specimen strain or isolate identifier
GENEPIO:0002140.definition: Name of strain from which sample was obtained OR name of isolate from which sample was obtained.

OBI:0001619.label: specimen collection time measurement datum
OBI:0001619.definition: A time measurement datum that is the measure of the time when the specimens are collected.

GENEPIO:0000053.label: 16S rRNA sequencing
GENEPIO:0000053.definition: 16S ribosomal RNA sequencing is a sequencing method used to identify and compare bacteria present within a given sample. 16S rRNA gene sequencing is a well-established method for studying phylogeny and taxonomy of samples from complex microbiomes or environments that are difficult or impossible to study.

GENEPIO:0000061.label: Accuprobe Listeria monocytogenes Culture Identification Reagent Kit
GENEPIO:0000061.definition: Nucleic acid hybridization tests are based on the ability of complementary nucleic acid strands to specifically align and associate to form stable double-stranded complexes (6). The ACCUPROBE method uses a single-stranded DNA probe with a chemiluminescent label that is complementary to the ribosomal RNA of the target organism. After the ribosomal RNA is released from the target organism, the labeled DNA probe combines with the target organism’s ribosomal RNA to form a stable DNA:RNA hybrid. The Selection Reagent allows for the differentiation of non-hybridized and hybridized probes.The light signal emitted by the DNA:RNA hybrids is measured by a GEN-PROBE luminometer. A positive result is a luminometer reading equal to or greater than the cut-off. A value below this cut-off is the negative result.

GENEPIO:0000066.label: DuPont identification pattern library
GENEPIO:0000066.definition: a library of RiboPrinter recognised patterns

GENEPIO:0000050.label: MLST sequence type
GENEPIO:0000050.definition: Multilocus sequence typing (MLST) is a technique in molecular biology for the typing of multiple loci. The procedure characterizes isolates of microbial species using the DNA sequences of internal fragments of multiple housekeeping genes. For each housekeeping gene, the different sequences present within a bacterial species are assigned as distinct alleles and, for each isolate, the alleles at each of the loci define the allelic profile or sequence type (ST).

GENEPIO:0000065.label: Qualicon (DuPont) RiboPrinter Microbial Characterization System
GENEPIO:0000065.definition: an automated system that takes a purified bacterial suspension, lyses the cells, extracts the DNA, restriction endonuclease digests the DNA, separates the digest on a gel, transfers the DNA bands to a membrane, probes the bands with non-radioisotope-labeled, 5S-16S-23S rRNA-specific probes (Southern hybridization), photographs the membrane, and finally compares the bar code-like pattern to databases in order to identify the genus and species.

GENEPIO:0000067.label: RiboPrinter DUP Number
GENEPIO:0000067.definition: DuPont identification number from the DuPont identification library

GENEPIO:0000068.label: RiboPrinter DUP similarity
GENEPIO:0000068.definition: Similarity of pattern to one of the patterns of the DuPont Identification library of the RiboPrinter

NCIT:C1225.label: Shiga Toxin
NCIT:C1225.definition: A bacterial toxin produced by Shigella dysenteriae and by some strains of E. coli that inhibits protein synthesis by blocking the interaction of ribosomal RNA with peptide elongation factors.  The non-catalytic beta subunit of Shiga toxin may be useful as a fusion vector for induction of antigen-specific cytotoxic T lymphocyte responses.

GENEPIO:0000064.label: riboprinting
GENEPIO:0000064.definition: This method is based on restriction endonuclease digestion of bacterial chromosomal DNA, followed by Southern hybridization to probes for sequences in the regions of bacterial DNA coding for the 5S-16S-23S (the Escherichia coli rrnB rRNA operon) rRNA operon. The probes have been developed that are directed to highly conserved regions of the rRNA operon present in all eubacteria and can therefore be used for ribotyping most bacteria

GENEPIO:0000063.label: ribotyping
GENEPIO:0000063.definition: Ribotyping involves the fingerprinting of genomic DNA restriction fragments that contain all or part of the genes coding for the 16S and 23S rRNA. By digesting the genes with a specific restriction enzyme, fragments of different lengths are generated. By performing a Gel electrophoresis with the digested samples, the fragments can be visualised as lines on the gel, where larger fragments are close to the start of the gel, and smaller fragments further down. After blotting onto a matrix and probing, these lines form a unique pattern for each species and can be used to identify the origin of the DNA, almost like a barcode can identify a product.

NCIT:C105370.label: Bacterial 16S RNA
NCIT:C105370.definition: The RNA component of the small (30S) subunit of prokaryotic ribosomes.

GENEPIO:0000096.label: genome annotation source
GENEPIO:0000096.definition: For cases where annotation was provided by a community jamboree or model organism database rather than by a specific submitter

GENEPIO:0000090.label: assembly method
GENEPIO:0000090.definition: Assembly method refers to how the reads were assembled into contigs for which either a de novo or mapping (reference based) strategy is used.

SO:0000149.label: contig
SO:0000149.definition: A contiguous sequence derived from sequence assembly. Has no gaps, but may contain N's from unavailable bases.

GENEPIO:0001738.label: assembly and annotation project objective
GENEPIO:0001738.definition: The assembly and annotation objective is the set of objectives that assembly and annotation techniques (including instruments and software platforms) applied to a sample are meant to satisfy.  This impacts on the quality control thresholds applied to the sequencing project.

GENEPIO:0000094.label: assembly name (identifier)
GENEPIO:0000094.definition: Name/version of the assembly provided by the submitter that is used in the genome browsers and in the community

GENEPIO:0001568.label: assembly quality control datum
GENEPIO:0001568.definition:
A single datum having to do with a metric for genomic sequence assembly quality control.  

A "quality control measurement" can be defined as a measurement that has some norm within a definable context, e.g. for a certain subspecies.  It may be a calculated quantity.

A "quality control metric" is an upper or lower bound threshold that a measurement is compared to.  Surpassing the threshold may indicate an error situation.

A "measure" can indicate an amount of activity, consumption, transformation, etc. but doesn't itself convey an over-stepping of bounds in the way that a metric does.

GENEPIO:0001562.label: reference genome identifier
GENEPIO:0001562.definition: Identifier for a reference genome (used to build or compare an assembly)  that is used in the genome browsers and in the community

SO:0001505.label: reference_genome
SO:0001505.definition: A collection of sequences (often chromosomes) taken as the standard for a given organism and genome assembly.

SO:0000353.label: sequence_assembly
SO:0000353.definition: A sequence of nucleotides that has been algorithmically derived from an alignment of two or more different sequences.

GENEPIO:0001297.label: exposure event location
GENEPIO:0001297.definition: An epi case physical location type is a type of built structure that is suspected to be related to an outbreak investigation.

APOLLO_SV:00000511.label: infection acquisition through sexual activity with infectious host
APOLLO_SV:00000511.definition: An infection acquistion from infectious host that is causally downstream of some potentially infectious sexual contacting

GENEPIO:0001681.label: lab sequencing datum
GENEPIO:0001681.definition: A laboratory sequencing datum is a datum related to the sequencing assay process applied to an isolate.

GENEPIO:0000009.label: other (metadata value)
GENEPIO:0000009.definition: "other (metadata choice)" indicates that for the given categorical variable, a respondent has chosen an other or additional response not listed.

GENEPIO:0002018.label: personal health datum
GENEPIO:0002018.definition: A personal health datum is a datum that pertains to the health situation or history of an individual.

GENEPIO:0002036.label: phenotypic antimicrobial drug susceptibility test datum

PCO:0000033.label: human social gathering activity
PCO:0000033.definition: A type of social behavior in which a collection of humans intentionally gathers together on a temporary basis to engage socially.

GENEPIO:0001487.label: exposure event end
GENEPIO:0001487.definition: A date-time datum that marks the end of possible human or animal exposure to a pathogen agent, directly or indirectly.

GENEPIO:0001488.label: exposure event start
GENEPIO:0001488.definition: A date-time datum that marks the start of a human or animal exposure event to a suspected pathogen agent, directly or indirectly.

GENEPIO:0001102.label: predicted exposure end
GENEPIO:0001102.definition: A date-time datum that marks the predicted end of possible human or animal exposure to a pathogen agent, directly or indirectly, based on a suspected pathogen and first symptom date-time.

GENEPIO:0001101.label: predicted exposure start
GENEPIO:0001101.definition: A date-time datum that marks the predicted start of possible human or animal exposure to a pathogen agent, directly or indirectly, based on a suspected pathogen and first symptom date-time.

GENEPIO:0000022.label: culture frozen date
GENEPIO:0000022.definition: A culture frozen date is a date-time entity marking the beginning of a process in which a sample culture is frozen for preservation.

GENEPIO:0000021.label: culture isolation date
GENEPIO:0000021.definition: A culture isolation date is a date-time entity marking the end of a process in which a sample is isolated as a single colony or non-mixture culture

GENEPIO:0000024.label: isolate upload date
GENEPIO:0000024.definition: date the isolate was entered into the database

GENEPIO:0000069.label: sequencing run date
GENEPIO:0000069.definition: date the sequencing run was performed

GENEPIO:0001782.label: upload modified date
GENEPIO:0001782.definition: Date an uploaded sample was re-uploaded or had its metadata modified.

GENEPIO:0001494.label: notification date
GENEPIO:0001494.definition: A notification date is the date that an outbreak is suspected by a laboratory or other agency and is reported per outbreak detection guidelines.

GENEPIO:0001495.label: outbreak date
GENEPIO:0001495.definition: An outbreak date is on which disease onset appears to have occured

GENEPIO:0001496.label: outbreak over
GENEPIO:0001496.definition: An outbreak over date is the date on which a disease outbreak appears to have abated

GENEPIO:0000139.label: food cultural origin
GENEPIO:0000139.definition: A food cultural origin datum indicates the cultural origin of a food product.

ERO:0001965.label: experimental subject role
ERO:0001965.definition: A role that inheres in a material that is input as the subject of interest in a scientific technique - either as an entity about which data is generated in an assay or study, or an entity that is transformed or modified in a material processing technique (e.g. the source from which a biological sample is taken)

vcard:Contact.label: contact
vcard:Contact.definition: A person associated with another person or organization.

GENEPIO:0001538.label: exposed person role
GENEPIO:0001538.definition: An exposed person role is the role a person takes on who has been exposed to a pathogen.  In serious situations this may call for special treatment, e.g. quarantine.

OMRSE:00000013.label: physician role
OMRSE:00000013.definition: A health care role borne by a human being and realized by promoting, maintaining or restoring human health through the study, diagnosis, and treatment of disease, injury and other physical and mental impairments.

NCIT:C25251.label: Primary
NCIT:C25251.definition: Occurring first in time or sequence; original; of greatest rank or importance or value.

NCIT:C25667.label: Secondary
NCIT:C25667.definition: Derived as a result of a primary condition; not direct or immediate; of second rank or importance or value.

GENEPIO:0000086.label: number of expected base pairs per genome
GENEPIO:0000086.definition: The estimated size of the genome prior to sequencing. Of particular importance in the sequencing of (eukaryotic) genome which could remain in draft form for a long or unspecified period.

GENEPIO:0000087.label: number of reads passing filter
GENEPIO:0000087.definition:
Raw data are filtered to remove any reads that do not meet the overall quality as measured by a chastity filter. The chastity of a base call is calculated as the ratio of the brightest intensity divided by the sum of the brightest and second brightest intensities.
Clusters passing filter are represented by PF in analysis reports. Clusters pass filter if no more than one base call in the first 25 cycles has a chastity of < 0.6.

GENEPIO:0000089.label: phred quality score
GENEPIO:0000089.definition: percentage of reads with a Phred quality score over 30, which indicates less than a 1/1000 chance that the base was called incorrectly

GENEPIO:0000092.label: read coverage
GENEPIO:0000092.definition: Coverage (read depth or depth) is the average number of reads representing a given nucleotide in the reconstructed sequence.

GENEPIO:0001561.label: assembly genome size
GENEPIO:0001561.definition: The assembly genome size is the sum of all lengths of a sequence assembly's contigs.

GENEPIO:0000091.label: assembly status
GENEPIO:0000091.definition: "Attempting to convey the relative integrity and reliability of the data, six levels or terms have been proposed and applied to describe genome sequences."   See subclass choices.

MESH:D001482.label: base composition
MESH:D001482.definition: the relative amounts of the purines and pyrimidines in a nucleic acid.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym:
base composition
base compositions
base ratio
base ratios
gc composition
gc compositions
gc content
gc contents
gc
g+c composition
g+c compositions
g+c content
g+c contents
guanine + cytosine composition
guanine + cytosine content

GENEPIO:0002137.label: breadth of coverage
GENEPIO:0002137.definition: The breadth of coverage is the percentage of the genome that was sequenced to a prescribed depth of coverage.

GENEPIO:0000093.label: contig count
GENEPIO:0000093.definition: A contig count is the count of contigs that belong to a sequence assembly.

GENEPIO:0001632.label: contig length
GENEPIO:0001632.definition: A contig length is the count of base pairs in a given sequence assembly contig.

GENEPIO:0001563.label: genome size delta ratio
GENEPIO:0001563.definition:
The 'genome size delta ratio' is a ratio of the difference between a sample's genome assembly size and the size of a given reference genome, over the reference genome size. 

The formula:

| (reference_genome_size - assembly_genome_size) | / reference_genome_size

This yeilds a decimal / percentage ranging from 0 = exact length, to say .1 which is equivalent to a 10% variance.  If the ratio is too far from a quality control ratio that depends on the species in question, this indicates a bad assembly or a mis-identified sample.

GENEPIO:0001564.label: genome size delta ratio QC threshold
GENEPIO:0001564.definition:
This is the upper acceptable limit of the 'genome size delta ratio' with respect to a particular species.

For Salmonella a 0.10 variance in length between an assembly size and a reference genome size may be acceptable.  For E-coli a more generous 0.30 or .40 variance should be allowed, given the pathogenic subspecies’ highly dynamic genome.

GENEPIO:0002138.label: mean contig length
GENEPIO:0002138.definition: The mean contig length is the count of base pairs in the average size contig of the sequence assembly.

GENEPIO:0000142.label: contact specification - epi network contact
GENEPIO:0000142.definition: An epi network contact is a person who may have recieved or transmitted an infectious disease related to an outbreak investigation.

GENEPIO:0000138.label: contact specification - lab test requester
GENEPIO:0000138.definition: A lab test requestor is the individual or agency requesting that one or more tests be performed on a specimen.

GENEPIO:0001642.label: curator organization name
GENEPIO:0001642.definition: The curator organization name is the name of an organization that manages a given repository of entities (samples, isolates, sequences ...)

GENEPIO:0001645.label: identifier status
GENEPIO:0001645.definition: An identifier status describes the principle role of an identifier assigned to an entity by its curator or handler. An entity may have a number of identifiers assigned to it over time.  An identifier may be phased-out as can happen when its content is transferred to another curator.

GENEPIO:0001775.label: subject age at time of specimen collection
GENEPIO:0001775.definition: A subject age at time of specimen extraction is the age (since birth) of the organism at the time a given specimen was extracted.

GENEPIO:0001657.label: draft NCBI BioSample geo_loc_name model
GENEPIO:0001657.definition: Geographical origin of the sample; use the appropriate name from this list http://www.insdc.org/documents/country-qualifier-vocabulary. Use a colon to separate the country or ocean from more detailed information about the location, eg "Canada: Vancouver" or "Germany: halfway down Zugspitze, Alps"

GENEPIO:0001581.label: draft NCBI BioSample model - mixed clinical and environmental/food/other

GENEPIO:0001623.label: draft NCBI isolate source location model

GENEPIO:0001662.label: in process
GENEPIO:0001662.definition: 'In process' is a categorical choice recorded while the data for a given measurable datum has not finished being collected, is awaiting a conclusion, or has not yet been communicated.

GENEPIO:0001620.label: not collected
GENEPIO:0001620.definition: 'Not collected' is a categorical choice recorded when a datum was not measured with respect to some entity during some process.

GENEPIO:0001810.label: restricted access
GENEPIO:0001810.definition: 'restricted access' is a categorical choice recorded when the data for a given measurable datum is available but not shared publicly because of information privacy concerns.

NCIT:C74723.label: Turbidity Measurement
NCIT:C74723.definition: The determination of the opacity of a sample.

FIX:0000278.label: redox potential
FIX:0000278.definition: redox potential, measured relative to a hydrogen cell, indicating oxidation or reduction potential

EO:0007027.label: seasonal environment
EO:0007027.definition: A plant treatment (EO:0001001) involving an exposure to a given conditions of regional seasons.

GENEPIO:0000042.label: stream order categorical measurement datum
GENEPIO:0000042.definition: Stream order is a measure of the relative size of streams (The smallest tributaries are referred to as first-order streams, while the largest river in the world, the Amazon, is a twelfth-order waterway).

GENEPIO:0000041.label: total phosphorous concentration
