GENEPIO:0000041.definition: total phosphorus concentration, calculated by: total phosphorus = total dissolved phosphorus + particulate phosphorus. Can also be measured without filtering, reported as phosphorus

GENEPIO:0000029.label: collection depth datum
GENEPIO:0000029.definition: Please refer to the definitions of depth in the environmental packages

GENEPIO:0001736.label: pH measurement
GENEPIO:0001736.definition: In chemistry, pH is a numeric scale used to specify the acidity or basicity(alkalinity) of an aqueous solution

GENEPIO:0000032.label: specimen collection site land use
GENEPIO:0000032.definition: Human use of land involving the management and modification of natural environment or wilderness into built environment.

OBI:0001941.label: contig N50
OBI:0001941.definition: N50 statistic computed for the contigs produced by the assembly process. A contig N50 is calculated by first ordering every contig by length from longest to shortest. Next, starting from the longest contig, the lengths of each contig are summed, until this running sum equals one-half of the total length of all contigs in the assembly. The contig N50 of the assembly is the length of the shortest contig in this list.

GENEPIO:0001565.label: contig N50 length QC threshold
GENEPIO:0001565.definition: The contig N50 length QC threshold is a minimum length threshold that a contig N50 length datum should be above for good QC.  A lower length is indicative of assembly problems (insufficient read depth) or a mismatched reference genome.

GENEPIO:0001570.label: contig N99
GENEPIO:0001570.definition: The N99 length definition is identical to the N50 definition except that the threshold for determining the contigs is 1% of the nucleotides.  This contig basepair length can be compared to a minimum threshold to determine if gene annotation (where contigs greater than say 2000bp are necessary) would generally succeed.

GENEPIO:0001566.label: contig N99 length QC threshold
GENEPIO:0001566.definition: The contig N99 length QC threshold is the minimum length that a contig N99 or NG99 length datum can be for satisfactory QC.  This threshold avoids having too many gene coding regions prematurely clipped inside short contigs.  An assembly having 1% or more of its content in less than 2Kbp chunks is cause for concern. Bacterial genes are generally about 1Kbp in length.

GENEPIO:0001631.label: contig NG50
GENEPIO:0001631.definition: The NG50 length is the same as the N50 length except that the length of the reference genome is used in the calculation rather than the assembly genome size.

GENEPIO:0001771.label: contig NG99
GENEPIO:0001771.definition: The NG99 length is the same as the N99 length except that the length of the reference genome is used in the calculation rather than the sum of assembly contig lengths.

GENEPIO:0001630.label: contig length QC threshold
GENEPIO:0001630.definition: A 'contig length QC threshold' is an integer setting which can be applied by an algorithm to an array of assembly and annotation contig lengths to remove (filter out) all items less than the threshold value.  The reduced array is used for calculation of statistics.

UBERON:0006314.label: bodily fluid
UBERON:0006314.definition: Liquid components of living organisms. includes fluids that are excreted or secreted from the body as well as body water that normally is not.

UBERON:0007378.label: egg yolk
UBERON:0007378.definition: The yellow spheroidal mass of stored food that forms the inner portion of the egg of a bird or reptile and is surrounded by the white.

UBERON:0000174.label: excreta
UBERON:0000174.definition: A portion of organism substance that is the product of an excretion process that will be eliminated from the body. An excretion process is elimination by an organism of the waste products that arise as a result of metabolic activity

UBERON:0008291.label: down feather
UBERON:0008291.definition: A feather lacking a vane and having a rudimentary rachis and a tuft of non-interlocked barbs with elongated barbules extending from the calamus

GENEPIO:0001647.label: original submission
GENEPIO:0001647.definition: An identifier used in the initial submission of content to a repository.

GENEPIO:0001653.label: previous (archaic) identifier
GENEPIO:0001653.definition: An identifier that had been used previously but is no longer promoted.

GENEPIO:0001793.label: data aggregated
GENEPIO:0001793.definition: The 'data aggregated' role between a user and given data entails that the user is authorized to see aggregated results (like the patient count) via preset reports, queries or views.  The results are not obfuscated.

GENEPIO:0001792.label: data obfuscated
GENEPIO:0001792.definition:
The 'data obfuscated' role between a user and given data entails that the user is authorized to see particular fields that have been transformed consistently such that statistics performed on those fields would yeild the same results as statistics applied to the un-obfuscated data. The purpose of obfuscation is to prevent related individuals or commercial organizations from being identified.

Aggregated results are by nature obfuscated (example: patient count).

GENEPIO:0001796.label: data protected
GENEPIO:0001796.definition: A 'data protected' role between a user and given data entails that a user must be authorized in order to view that data.

GENEPIO:0001795.label: de-identified data
GENEPIO:0001795.definition: A 'de-identified data' role between a user and given data entails that the user is authorized to see only those fields (including those that are encrypted) which do not contain information that could be use to identify particular individuals (whether patients or medical practitioners) or potentially organizations in the case where an investigation may implicate them.

GENEPIO:0001794.label: limited data set
GENEPIO:0001794.definition: A 'limited data set' role between a user and given data entails that a user is authorized to see some of the fields but the remainder are withheld (or encrypted).

OBI:0001620.label: latitude coordinate measurement datum
OBI:0001620.definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the latitude coordinate of a site.

OBI:0001621.label: longitude coordinate measurement datum
OBI:0001621.definition: A measurement datum that is the measure of the longitude coordinate of a site.

GENEPIO:0001113.label: INSDC country qualifier
GENEPIO:0001113.definition: The INSDC country qualifier is a textual controlled vocabulary used to indicate the country of origin of a DNA sample.  It can also have the following format: country:sub_region, such as: "Canada:Vancouver".

XCO:0000412.label: gestation
XCO:0000412.definition: The state of a female and/or her offspring, and the processes which occur, during the period from conception to birth or termination of the pregnancy.

GENEPIO:0000085.label: library preparation kit
GENEPIO:0000085.definition: Packaged kits (containing adapters, indexes, enzymes, buffers etc), tailored for specific sequencing workflows, which allow the simplified preparation of sequencing-ready libraries for small genomes, amplicons, and plasmids.

GENEPIO:0000076.label: read length
GENEPIO:0000076.definition: number of base pairs per read

GENEPIO:0000088.label: sequencer flow cell cluster density
GENEPIO:0000088.definition: Cluster Generation is a process by which libraries amplified into clonal clusters on a flow cell. The density of those clusters in the lane, is the cluster density.

GENEPIO:0000082.label: sequencing kit version
GENEPIO:0000082.definition: The version is the configuration of the reagent cartidge.

GENEPIO:0000070.label: sequencing location
GENEPIO:0000070.definition: location the sequencing run was performed

GENEPIO:0000072.label: sequencing workflow
GENEPIO:0000072.definition: the workflow is the pre-defined sequence of steps to run the automated sequencing pipeline.

GENEPIO:0000083.label: adapter sequence
GENEPIO:0000083.definition: Adapters provide priming sequences for both amplification and sequencing of the sample-library fragments. Both adapters should be reported; in uppercase letters

OBI:0001894.label: email address of sequencing facility contact person
OBI:0001894.definition: An email address of the contact representative at the sequencing facility

GENEPIO:0001054.label: isolate passage history datum
GENEPIO:0001054.definition: An isolate passage history is a record of the cyclic growth process that led to it, including number of times its was put through the process, and the method used.

GENEPIO:0000148.label: isolate raw read filename
GENEPIO:0000148.definition: An isolate raw read filename is the file name (http://edamontology.org/data_1050) of the raw read file created by a genomic sequencing assay.

GENEPIO:0000135.label: isolate sequence filename
GENEPIO:0000135.definition: An isolate sequence filename is the file name (http://edamontology.org/data_1050) of the contig assembly file created by a bioinformatics assembly process.

GENEPIO:0001994.label: library construction protocol
GENEPIO:0001994.definition: Free form text describing the protocol by which the sequencing library was constructed.

GENEPIO:0001995.label: library name
GENEPIO:0001995.definition: The submitter's name for this library.

GENEPIO:0000149.label: library preparation kit version
GENEPIO:0000149.definition: The version identifier of a packaged kit tailored for specific sequencing workflows.

GENEPIO:0001940.label: library selection
GENEPIO:0001940.definition: Whether any method was used to select for or against, enrich, or screen the material being sequenced.

GENEPIO:0001965.label: library source
GENEPIO:0001965.definition: The library source specifies the type of source material that is being sequenced.

GENEPIO:0001973.label: library strategy
GENEPIO:0001973.definition: Sequencing technique intended for this library.

GENEPIO:0000084.label: read adapter trimming
GENEPIO:0000084.definition: the removal of adapter sequences from demultiplexed data reads

GENEPIO:0002096.label: read adapter trimming software
GENEPIO:0002096.definition: The name and version of the software product used for removal of adapter sequences from demultiplexed data reads

GENEPIO:0002095.label: read paired-end merging software
GENEPIO:0002095.definition: The name and version of the software used to merge paired-end reads before assembly.

GENEPIO:0000150.label: read trimming and filtering software
GENEPIO:0000150.definition: The name and version of software used in a bioinformatics workflow to improve the quality of sequencing reads.

GENEPIO:0001095.label: sequence number
GENEPIO:0001095.definition: A sequence number is a numeric identifier of a sequence with respect to a particular data table or dataset.

GENEPIO:0000073.label: sequencing application
GENEPIO:0000073.definition: the sequencing application is the use or purpose of the sequencing

GENEPIO:0000075.label: sequencing chemistry
GENEPIO:0000075.definition: lab method to determine the order of nucleotides in a DNA molecule

GENEPIO:0002093.label: sequencing dna extraction method
GENEPIO:0002093.definition: The procedure used to obtain genomic DNA from a sample through chemical, physical or mechanical means.

OBI:0001888.label: sequencing facility contact person
OBI:0001888.definition: A person who is the contact representative at the sequencing facility

GENEPIO:0001921.label: sequencing instrument model
GENEPIO:0001921.definition: A product name and model number of a manufacturer's genomic (dna) sequencer.

GENEPIO:0000081.label: sequencing kit
GENEPIO:0000081.definition: Pre-filled, ready-to-use reagent cartridges. Used to produce improved chemistry, cluster density and read length as well as improve quality (Q) scores. Reagent components are encoded to interact with the sequencing system to validate compatibility with user-defined applications.

GENEPIO:0000071.label: sequencing platform (brand)
GENEPIO:0000071.definition: A sequencing plaform (brand) is a name of a company that produces sequencer equipment.

GENEPIO:0000078.label: sequencing run multiplex identifiers
GENEPIO:0000078.definition: Molecular barcodes, called Multiplex Identifiers (MIDs), that are used to specifically tag unique samples in a sequencing run. Sequence should be reported in uppercase letters

GENEPIO:0000049.label: MLST clonal complex
GENEPIO:0000049.definition: Multilocus sequence typing (MLST) is a technique in molecular biology for the typing of multiple loci. The procedure characterizes isolates of microbial species using the DNA sequences of internal fragments of multiple housekeeping genes. Sequence types are grouped into clonal complexes by their similarity to a central allelic profile (genotype). As such, clonal complexes represent sequence types that share a number of identical alleles e.g. 5/7

SO:0001027.label: genotype
SO:0001027.definition: A genotype is a variant genome, complete or incomplete.

OMP:0000207.label: serotype phenotype
OMP:0000207.definition: A microbial phenotype that is distinguished by the presence a specific surface antigen.

GENEPIO:0001012.label: MIRU24 - Canadian standard
GENEPIO:0001012.definition: The MIRU24 - Canadian standard is a Mycobacterium tuberculosis typing method exactly like MIRU24 - international standard except that the report of the ordering of the matching loci is different.

GENEPIO:0001011.label: MIRU24 - international standard
GENEPIO:0001011.definition: The MIRU24 - international standard is a mycobacterial interspersed repetitive units (MIRU) typing method that classifies Mycobacterium tuberculosis complex (MBTC) bacteria according to a multiple locus VNTR [variable number of tandem repeats] analysis (MLVA) typing scheme of counts of repeats at 24 sequence loci.

GENEPIO:0001639.label: antigenic formula
GENEPIO:0001639.definition: An antigenic formula is a string composed of codes representing categorized results of tests performed on various viral, bacterial or immune cell surface antigens.

GENEPIO:0000136.label: cluster identifier
GENEPIO:0000136.definition: A cluster identifier is an identifier that locates a genomic variant of an organism within a community of past or present genetically related organisms.

GENEPIO:0001719.label: phage type specification
GENEPIO:0001719.definition: An integer and character referring to a pattern of opaque or confluent lysis caused by a panel of bacteriophage infections e.g. 14a.

GENEPIO:0001079.label: serovar/serotype common name
GENEPIO:0001079.definition: A serotype or serovar is a distinct variation within a species of bacteria or virus or among immune cells of different individuals. These microorganisms, viruses, or cells are classified together based on their cell surface antigens, allowing the epidemiologic classification of organisms to the sub-species level

GENEPIO:0000037.label: soluble inorganic material
GENEPIO:0000037.definition: concentration of substances such as ammonia, road-salt, sea-salt, cyanide, hydrogen sulfide, thiocyanates, thiosulfates, etc.

GENEPIO:0001716.label: subgroup
GENEPIO:0001716.definition: Taxonomy below subspecies; sometimes used in viruses to denote subgroups taken from a single isolate.

GENEPIO:0001717.label: viral subtype
GENEPIO:0001717.definition: A viral subtype is a classification name for a virus according to some protocol.

typon:MLVA.label: Multilocus Variable Number of Tandem Repeats Analysis typing
typon:MLVA.definition: MLVA stands for Multilocus Variable Number of Tandem Repeats Analysis. This method can be performed by three distinct methodologies: by running the amplified locus in a gel , using a capilary electrophoresis apparatus or sequencing the resulting amplified fragment. The first two infer the number of repeats on each locus indirectly by the fragment size.

GENEPIO:0001721.label: NCBI culture collection
GENEPIO:0001721.definition: An NCBI culture collection is a composite identifier containing “institution code:collection code”.

GENEPIO:0001805.label: variant calling / pathogen identification and clustering

GENEPIO:0001426.label: container record
GENEPIO:0001426.definition: A container id is an identifier that refers to a container object about a patient specimen. Container ids are referenced in clinical patient records reported to be suspect, or lab test results.

GENEPIO:0001641.label: identifier model
GENEPIO:0001641.definition: An identifier moe3l indicates an identifier, the organization it has been issued by, and the status of the identifier - whether it is a primary one, active or archaic.

GENEPIO:0001430.label: line list object
GENEPIO:0001430.definition:
A line list is a collection of suspected or known disease outbreak cases.  It may also include details about healthy patients associated with an exposure event (picnic, concert etc.) who have been interviewed in order to compare food intake, assess risk factors, etc.  

Note that the health status of people associated with an exposure event can change from healthy or unknown status, to ill patient.

SIO:001027.label: medical health record (history / timeline)
SIO:001027.definition: A medical health record is a record of a single patient's medical history.

GENEPIO:0001688.label: test specification
GENEPIO:0001688.definition: A lab test specification indicates the inputs and outputs (results / conclusions) of a test.

GAZ:00002848.label: Autonomous Region (China)
GAZ:00002848.definition: A first-level administrative subdivision of China. Like Chinese provinces, an autonomous region has its own local government, but an autonomous region has more legislative rights. It is a minority entity and has a higher population of a particular minority ethnic group. There are five autonomous regions in China: the Tibetan people in Tibet, the Zhuang in Guangxi, the Uyghur in Xinjiang, the Mongols in Inner Mongolia, and the Hui in Ningxia.

GAZ:00003092.label: Region (contiguous United States of America)
GAZ:00003092.definition: Census Regions and Divisions are groupings of States that subdivide the United States.

GENEPIO:0001837.label: AHA HIPPA standard
GENEPIO:0001837.definition: The American Hospital Association has issued HIPAA Updated Guidelines for Releasing Information on the Condition of Patients

GENEPIO:0001839.label: PulseNet submission standard
GENEPIO:0001839.definition: PulseNet, a national and international surveillance system used to identify and respond to foodborne disease outbreaks, has a standardized laboratory method and data submission standard for pathogen isolate typing test results and related isolate contextual data.  From this information clusters of disease can be identified that might represent unrecognized outbreaks.

GENEPIO:0000143.label: public health lab epidemiology contextual data standard
GENEPIO:0000143.definition: This model contains data type specifications for whole genome sequencing and epidemiology investigation contextual data.

GENEPIO:0000017.label: American HIPPA Protected Health Information (PHI) guidelines
GENEPIO:0000017.definition:
The American HIPPA Protected Health Information (PHI) guidelines cover information, including demographic information, which relates to:

- the individual’s past, present, or future physical or mental health or condition,
- the provision of health care to the individual, or
- the past, present, or future payment for the provision of health care to the individual, and that identifies the individual or for which there is a reasonable basis to believe can be used to identify the individual. Protected health information includes many common identifiers (e.g., name, address, birth date, Social Security Number) when they can be associated with the health information listed above."

GENEPIO:0001010.label: Canadian Integrated Public Health Information System (iPHIS) Standard
GENEPIO:0001010.definition: The Canadian Integrated Public Health Information System (iPHIS) System provides a standard for holding reportable disease cases from participating jurisdictions.

SIO:000507.label: point
SIO:000507.definition: A point is a geometric entity that is located in a zero-dimensional spatial region and whose position is defined by its coordinates in some coordinate system.

GENEPIO:0002082.label: contact specification - specimen related organization
GENEPIO:0002082.definition: Contact information for an organization related to specimen collection, processing or storage.

GENEPIO:0000128.label: epidemiology contact network model
GENEPIO:0000128.definition: An epidemiology contact network model is a definition of the information necessary to connect pathogen transmission patterns between individuals or animals in connection with an outbreak investigation.

GENEPIO:0002135.label: EBI ENA Webin environmental feature
GENEPIO:0002135.definition: identifies sequences derived by direct molecular isolation from a bulk environmental DNA sample (by PCR with or without subsequent cloning of the product, DGGE, or other anonymous methods) with no reliable identification of the source organism. Environmental samples include clinical samples, gut contents, and other sequences from anonymous organisms that may be associated with a particular host. They do not include endosymbionts that can be reliably recovered from a particular host, organisms from a readily identifiable but uncultured field sample (e.g., many cyanobacteria), or phytoplasmas that can be reliably recovered from diseased plants (even though these cannot be grown in axenic culture).

GENEPIO:0000113.label: specimen category
GENEPIO:0000113.definition: Specimen category is a categorical variable that broadly indicates the source of a specimen in order for data processing systems like NCBI's biosample submission portal to anticipate other fields related to the source. Currently this distinguishes between "clinical or host associated" specimens and "environmental/food or other pathogen" specimens.

sep:00196.label: specimen description
sep:00196.definition: A description of the biological sample analysed.

GENEPIO:0001797.label: specimen extraction agent
GENEPIO:0001797.definition: The "specimen extraction agent" is a datum containing the name of persons or institute who collected a given specimen.

GENEPIO:0001356.label: specimen history item
GENEPIO:0001356.definition: A specimen history item is a time-related datum about a particular specimen

GENEPIO:0000027.label: specimen source context
GENEPIO:0000027.definition: Describes the physical, environmental and/or local geographical source of the biological sample from which the sample was derived.

GENEPIO:0001808.label: specimen title
GENEPIO:0001808.definition: A specimen (or sample) title should be short and informative. Each specimen title must be unique in a submission.

OBI:0001903.label: email address of specimen provider principal investigator
OBI:0001903.definition: An email address of the principal investigator providing the specimens for the investigation

GENEPIO:0001433.definition: The IRIDA user ID is a user account identifier provided by the IRIDA.ca system.

data:1093.label: sequence accession
data:1093.definition: A persistent, unique identifier of a molecular sequence database entry.

GENEPIO:0001651.label: INSDC institution code
GENEPIO:0001651.definition: An INSDC institution code is an identifier of an organization from a list of sequence repository organizations managed by INSDC.

GENEPIO:0001550.label: resolving health trend
GENEPIO:0001550.definition: to restore to the normal state after some pathologic process.

CVDO:0000597.label: congenital disease
CVDO:0000597.definition: A disease existing at birth, or developping during the first month after birth.

GENEPIO:0001618.label: missing
GENEPIO:0001618.definition: 'missing' is a categorical choice recorded when a measurement value was known to be recorded in the past but the observed value cannot be located or retrieved for some reason.

GENEPIO:0001619.label: not applicable
GENEPIO:0001619.definition: 'Not applicable' is a categorical choice recorded when a measurable datum does not apply to a given context, as for example the measure of femur length for a patient with a missing limb.

GENEPIO:0001851.label: recorded
GENEPIO:0001851.definition: A recorded datum is known to be available for retrieval. Any datum that has a recorded value has this for its metadata "datum status"

GENEPIO:0001856.label: 2D space
GENEPIO:0001856.definition:
This data type is for an item that can map to a point, line, set or area on a surface (2 dimensional space) or to the surface itself.  It can be a slice of a higher dimensional space.

It can be defined by a cartesian or radial coordinate system.

GENEPIO:0001908.label: plane
GENEPIO:0001908.definition:
In mathematics, a plane is a flat, two-dimensional surface. A plane is the two-dimensional analogue of a point (zero dimensions), a line (one dimension) and three-dimensional space. Planes can arise as subspaces of some higher-dimensional space, as with the walls of a room, or they may enjoy an independent existence in their own right, as in the setting of Euclidean geometry."

"When working exclusively in two-dimensional Euclidean space, the definite article is used, so, the plane refers to the whole space.

GENEPIO:0001906.label: quadratic surface
GENEPIO:0001906.definition: In Euclidean space, quadrics have dimension D = 2, and are known as quadric surfaces.

STATO:0000010.label: coordinate system
STATO:0000010.definition: In geometry, a coordinate system is a system which uses one or more numbers, or coordinates, to uniquely determine the position of a point or other geometric element on a manifold such as Euclidean space.

STATO:0000022.label: one dimensional cartesian coordinate system
STATO:0000022.definition: a three dimensional cartesian coordinate system is a cartesian coordinate system which defines 3 orthogonal one dimensional axis and which may be used to describe a 3 dimensional spatial region

STATO:0000013.label: two dimensional cartesian coordinate system
STATO:0000013.definition: a 2 dimensional cartesian coordinate system is a cartesian coordinate system which defines 2 orthogonal one dimensional axes and which may be used to describe a 2 dimensional spatial region

STATO:0000015.label: cylindrical coordinate system
STATO:0000015.definition: A cylindrical coordinate system is a three-dimensional coordinate system that specifies point positions by the distance from a chosen reference axis, the direction from the axis relative to a chosen reference direction, and the distance from a chosen reference plane perpendicular to the axis. The latter distance is given as a positive or negative number depending on which side of the reference plane faces the point.

GEO:000000788.label: geodetic datum
GEO:000000788.definition: A coordinate system, and a set of reference points, used to locate places on the Earth (or similar objects).

STATO:0000024.label: three dimensional cartesian coordinate system
STATO:0000024.definition: a three dimensional cartesian coordinate system is a cartesian coordinate system which defines 3 orthogonal one dimensional axes and which may be used to describe a 3 dimensional spatial region

STATO:0000016.label: polar coordinate system
STATO:0000016.definition: In mathematics, the polar coordinate system is a two-dimensional coordinate system in which each point on a plane is determined by a distance from a fixed point and an angle from a fixed direction.

PATO:0002390.label: radius
PATO:0002390.definition: A length quality which is equal to the length of any straight line segment that passes from the center of a circle to any endpoint on the circular boundary. The radius is half of the diameter.

GENEPIO:0001870.label: area calculation
GENEPIO:0001870.definition: An area calculation datum is a functional mapping of a two dimensional surface area (can be anything from an abstract polygon, to a postal code or country) to a 1 dimensional scalar.  The original surface area may be curved, e.g. spheroid.  The surface area can also be described using only one input - for example the radius scalar of a polar coordinate plane described by pi*r^2.

GENEPIO:0001873.label: datetime range intermediate
GENEPIO:0001873.definition: A datetime range intermediate datum is a datetime item grouped under a process, and occuring  after some process start and before some process end.

GENEPIO:0001881.label: datetime set item
GENEPIO:0001881.definition: A datetime set item is a datetime that has been grouped semantically under a given type of process

GENEPIO:0001996.label: 2D boundary
GENEPIO:0001996.definition: A two dimensional boundary is a continuous path (loop) defined on a two dimensional surface.

GENEPIO:0001934.label: 2D entity
GENEPIO:0001934.definition: A two dimensional entity is an entity composed of one or more points on a two dimensional surface.

SIO:000608.label: curve
SIO:000608.definition: A curve is a geometric entity that may be located in n-dimensional spatial region whose extension may be n-dimensional,  is composed of at least two fully connected points and does not intersect itself.

GAZ:00000448.label: geographic location
GAZ:00000448.definition: A reference to a place on the Earth, by its name or by its geographical location.

SIO:000415.label: geopolitical region
SIO:000415.definition: a geopolitical region is a geographic region recognized by social or legal convention.

GENEPIO:0002167.label: specimen extraction site
GENEPIO:0002167.definition: The physical location that a specimen was extracted or collected at.  The location may be described by geographic coordinates, city or other geopolitical entity, biome, etc.

GENEPIO:0001902.label: unordered set
GENEPIO:0001902.definition: An unordered set is a set of elements which have no intrinsic (semantic) order with respect to each other. The set of all living people is not intrinsically ordered; an ordering can only be provided by looking at some partiular feature of the given set elements.

GENEPIO:0001907.label: spheroid
GENEPIO:0001907.definition: A spheroid, or ellipsoid of revolution, is a quadric surface obtained by rotating an ellipse about one of its principal axes; in other words, an ellipsoid with two equal semi-diameters.

GENEPIO:0001998.label: decimal quantity unit
GENEPIO:0001998.definition: A multiplier in the decimal number system that has been applied to an accompanying number or set of numbers often to simplfy their appearance.  Numbers described by multipliers may have lost significant digits through rounding or trimming.

OBI:0000696.label: AB SOLiD System
OBI:0000696.definition: is a DNA sequencer which is manufactured by Applied Biosystems and which enable DNA sequencing by ligation

OBI:0000717.label: HeliScope Single Molecule Sequencer
OBI:0000717.definition: is a DNA sequencer manufacturer by Helicos Corporation to carry out Single Molecule sequencing using reversible termination chemistry

OBI:0000703.label: Illumina Genome Analyzer II
OBI:0000703.definition: is a DNA sequence which is manufactured by Illumina (Solexa) corporation. it support sequencing of single or paired end clone libraries relying on sequencing by synthesis technology

OBI:0002003.label: MiSeq
OBI:0002003.definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation. Built upon sequencing by synthesis technology, the machine provides an end-to-end solution (cluster generation, amplification, sequencing, and data analysis) in a single machine.

OBI:0002021.label: NextSeq 500
OBI:0002021.definition: A DNA sequencer which is a desktop sequencer ideal for smaller-scale studies manufactured by the Illumina corporation. It supports sequencing of single, long or short insert paired end clone libraries relying on sequencing by synthesis technology.

OBI:0002012.label: PacBio RS II
OBI:0002012.definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Pacific Biosciences corporation. Built upon single molecule real-time sequencing technology, the machine is optimized for generation with long reads and high consensus accuracy.

GENEPIO:0001922.label: circle
GENEPIO:0001922.definition: A circle is a simple closed shape in Euclidean geometry. It is the set of all points in a plane that are at a given distance from a given point, the centre; equivalently it is the curve traced out by a point that moves so that its distance from a given point is constant.

SIO:000505.label: polygon
SIO:000505.definition: In elementary geometry, a polygon is a plane figure that is bounded by a finite chain of straight line segments closing in a loop to form a closed chain or circuit.

OBI:0000689.label: 454 Genome Sequence 20
OBI:0000689.definition:
is a DNA sequencer which is manufactured by 454 Life Science Corporation and enables pyrosequencing to be performed. It comprises both optics and fluidics subsystems, which are
controlled by a computer subsystem. The fluidics subsystem ensures accurate reagent dispensing. It consists of a reagents cassette (which holds the reagent containers), a sipper manifold, pumps, valves, and debubblers. The fluidics subsystem flows the sequencing reagents across the wells of the PicoTiterPlate device, and moves the spent reagents from the PicoTiterPlate device to the waste receptacle. The optics subsystem consists of a CCD camera and a camera controller. The camera captures the light emitted in the wells of the PicoTiterPlate device during each step of the sequencing cycle, and sends the digital images to the computer subsystem for processing. The computer controls the other Sequencer subsystems, and processes the digital images sent by the camera to extract the DNA sequence information.

OBI:0000702.label: 454 Genome Sequencer FLX
OBI:0000702.definition:
is a DNA sequencer which is manufactured by 454 Life Science Corporation and enables pyrosequencing to be performed. It comprises both optics and fluidics subsystems, which are
controlled by a computer subsystem. The fluidics subsystem ensures accurate reagent dispensing. It consists of a reagents cassette (which holds the reagent containers), a sipper manifold, pumps, valves, and debubblers. The fluidics subsystem flows the sequencing reagents across the wells of the PicoTiterPlate device, and moves the spent reagents from the PicoTiterPlate device to the waste receptacle. The optics subsystem consists of a CCD camera and a camera controller. The camera captures the light emitted in the wells of the PicoTiterPlate device during each step of the sequencing cycle, and sends the digital images to the computer subsystem for processing. The computer controls the other Sequencer subsystems, and processes the digital images sent by the camera to extract the DNA sequence information.

OBI:0002022.label: Illumina HiSeq 1000
OBI:0002022.definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation, with a single flow cell and a throughput of up to 35 Gb per day. It supports sequencing of single, long or short insert paired end clone libraries relying on sequencing by synthesis technology.

OBI:0002001.label: Illumina HiSeq 2000
OBI:0002001.definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation, with two flow cells and a throughput of up to 55 Gb per day. Built upon sequencing by synthesis technology, the machine is optimized for generation of data for multiple samples in a single run.

OBI:0002002.label: Illumina HiSeq 2500
OBI:0002002.definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation, with two flow cells and a throughput of up to 160 Gb per day. Built upon sequencing by synthesis technology, the machine is optimized for generation of data for batching multiple samples or rapid results on a few samples.

OBI:0002048.label: Illumina HiSeq 3000
OBI:0002048.definition: A DNA sequencer manufactured by Illumina corporation, with a single flow cell and a throughput of more than 200 Gb per day.

OBI:0002049.label: Illumina HiSeq 4000
OBI:0002049.definition: A DNA sequencer manufactured by Illumina corporation, with two flow cell and a throughput of more than 400 Gb per day.

GENEPIO:0001941.label: 5-methylcytidine antibody method
GENEPIO:0001941.definition: Selection of methylated DNA fragments using an antibody raised against 5-methylcytosine or 5-methylcytidine (m5C).

GENEPIO:0001950.label: Hybrid Selection method
GENEPIO:0001950.definition: Selection by hybridization in array or solution.

GENEPIO:0001951.label: MBD2 protein methyl-CpG binding domain method

GENEPIO:0001955.label: PCR method
GENEPIO:0001955.definition: Source material was selected by designed primers.

GENEPIO:0001957.label: RANDOM PCR method
GENEPIO:0001957.definition: Source material was selected by randomly generated primers.

GENEPIO:0001958.label: RANDOM method
GENEPIO:0001958.definition: Random selection by shearing or other method.

GENEPIO:0001959.label: RT-PCR method
GENEPIO:0001959.definition: Source material was selected by reverse transcription PCR

GENEPIO:0001960.label: Reduced Representation method
GENEPIO:0001960.definition: Reproducible genomic subsets, often generated by restriction fragment size selection, containing a manageable number of loci to facilitate re-sampling.

GENEPIO:0001962.label: cDNA method
GENEPIO:0001962.definition: PolyA selection or enrichment for messenger RNA (mRNA). complementary DNA.

GENEPIO:0001964.label: other library method
GENEPIO:0001964.definition: Other library enrichment, screening, or selection process.

GENEPIO:0001963.label: size fractionation method
GENEPIO:0001963.definition: Physical selection of size appropriate targets.

GENEPIO:0001966.label: genomic source
GENEPIO:0001966.definition: Genomic DNA (includes PCR products from genomic DNA).

GENEPIO:0001969.label: other library source
GENEPIO:0001969.definition: Other, unspecified, or unknown library source material.

GENEPIO:0001971.label: transcriptomic source
GENEPIO:0001971.definition: Transcription products or non genomic DNA (EST, cDNA, RT-PCR, screened libraries).

GENEPIO:0001975.label: Bisulfite-Seq strategy
GENEPIO:0001975.definition: MethylC-seq. Sequencing following treatment of DNA with bisulfite to convert cytosine residues to uracil depending on methylation status.

GENEPIO:0001980.label: DNase-Hypersensitivity strategy
GENEPIO:0001980.definition: Sequencing of hypersensitive sites, or segments of open chromatin that are more readily cleaved by DNaseI.

GENEPIO:0001981.label: EST strategy
GENEPIO:0001981.definition: Single pass sequencing of cDNA templates

GENEPIO:0001984.label: MBD-Seq strategy
GENEPIO:0001984.definition: Direct sequencing of methylated fractions sequencing strategy.

GENEPIO:0001991.label: WCS strategy
GENEPIO:0001991.definition: Random sequencing of a whole chromosome or other replicon isolated from a genome.

GENEPIO:0001992.label: WGS strategy
GENEPIO:0001992.definition: Random sequencing of the whole genome.

GENEPIO:0001993.label: WXS strategy
GENEPIO:0001993.definition: Random sequencing of exonic regions selected from the genome.

GENEPIO:0001974.label: amplicon strategy
GENEPIO:0001974.definition: Sequencing of overlapping or distinct PCR or RT-PCR products. For example, metagenomic community profiling using SSU rRNA

GENEPIO:0001982.label: finishing strategy
GENEPIO:0001982.definition: Sequencing intended to finish (close) gaps in existing coverage.

GENEPIO:0001989.label: pool clone strategy
GENEPIO:0001989.definition: Shotgun of pooled clones (usually BACs and Fosmids).

GENEPIO:0002010.label: TB lineage 3 - East-African Indian, includes CAS/Delhi

GENEPIO:0002011.label: TB lineage 4 - Euro-American, includes Haarlem, LAM3, X, T, F11, H37Rv

OBI:0001627.label: country name
OBI:0001627.definition: A textual entity that denotes a geographic location that is a site or part of a site that is identified as a country in the political geography.

SIO:010057.label: life status
SIO:010057.definition: life status is the quality of whether something is alive or dead.

GENEPIO:0001222.label: patient as host datum
GENEPIO:0001222.definition: A host datum is a datum that pertains to infection-related information about an organism (animal or human) who is likely bearing a pathogen

GENEPIO:0001212.label: subject disease outcome
GENEPIO:0001212.definition: A subject disease outcome is an assessment of the persistence of a given disease course in a subject (patient)

GENEPIO:0001625.label: subject disease stage
GENEPIO:0001625.definition: A subject disease stage is a measure of the acuteness of a subject organism's diagnosed disease, if any, at a given time in an investigation, study or specimen extraction event.

ExO:0000038.label: subject health status
ExO:0000038.definition: The condition of an organism in all aspects (e.g., functional or metabolic efficiency).

GENEPIO:0000110.label: subject health status (GSCID-BRC)
GENEPIO:0000110.definition: A description of whether a given subject organism appeared healthy, sick or deceased at the time of specimen extraction. If sick or deceased, additional details should be provided in project-specific fields.

GENEPIO:0002021.label: treated and released (not admitted to hospital)

GENEPIO:0002022.label: treated and transferred
GENEPIO:0002022.definition: Received treatment. Transferred to a different facility.

GENEPIO:0001646.label: data protection role
GENEPIO:0001646.definition: A data protection role is a role (or user permission) that a user has with respect to particular data.

ARO:3004390.label: antimicrobial resistance test platform
ARO:3004390.definition: System of analysis for determining antimicrobial susceptibility.

ARO:3004430.label: antimicrobial resistance tissue specificity
ARO:3004430.definition: The tissue type used to select breakpoints from a particular standard, for the interpretation of MIC results.

GENEPIO:0002047.label: antimicrobial resistance testing method version or reagent
GENEPIO:0002047.definition: The commercial kit or product used to determine the MIC e.g. E-Test. If a commercial product was not used, include the type of media used.

GENEPIO:0001001.label: test threshold measurement comparator
GENEPIO:0001001.definition: The measurement comparator is a sign indicating that a measurement is above, equal to, or below a given threshold.

NCIT:C85540.label: Microbial Susceptibility Test
NCIT:C85540.definition: A method to determine whether microbial growth is affected by an antimicrobial compound.

GENEPIO:0000002.label: GSCID-BRC Project and Sample Application Standard
GENEPIO:0000002.definition: The GSCID-BRC Project and Sample Application Standard captures standardized human pathogen and vector sequencing metadata to support epidemiologic and genotype-phenotype association studies for human infectious diseases.

GENEPIO:0000008.label: Minimum information about a marker gene sequence
GENEPIO:0000008.definition: The "minimum information about a marker gene sequence" (MIMARKS) is a standard developed by the Genomic Standards Consortium (GSC) for reporting marker gene sequences.

GENEPIO:0000003.label: Minimum Information about any (x) Sequence (MIxS)
GENEPIO:0000003.definition: MixS is a unified standard for describing sequence data provided by the Genomic Standards Consortium (GSC)

NCIT:C43186.label: Container
NCIT:C43186.definition: An object that can be used to hold things.

NCIT:C42856.label: Sponge
NCIT:C42856.definition: A soft flexible, absorbent pad usually made from natural material such as gauze or cotton, used to absorb blood and other fluids, as in surgery or the dressing of a wound. The term also refers to a small absorbent contraceptive pad that contains a spermicide and is placed against the cervix of the uterus before sexual intercourse.

NCIT:C17627.label: Swab
NCIT:C17627.definition: A tuft of material on the end of a stick for applying solutions and suspensions
NCIT:C17627.ui_definition: A portion of an absorbent material attached to one end of a small stick for the purpose of applying or collecting material.

NCIT:C41277.label: Tube
NCIT:C41277.definition: A hollow cylinder, especially one for holding or conveying liquids; anything shaped like such a hollow cylinder, e.g. an organic structure having the shape or function of a tube such as channel within a plant or animal body (e.g. fallopian tube).
NCIT:C41277.ui_definition: A hollow cylinder, especially one for holding or conveying liquids.

NCIT:C82508.label: Life Threatening
NCIT:C82508.definition: A situation that imperils the existence of an entity.

NCIT:C126054.label: Non-Pathological
NCIT:C126054.definition: The absence of disease or pathology.

NCIT:C63362.label: Vacutainer
NCIT:C63362.definition: A brand of of test tube specifically designed for venipuncture; the tube contains a vacuum allowing it to suck blood though a needle and fill itself. The tube may contain additives to facilitate downstream processing and testing of the blood samples; the tube cap is color-coded to indicate the type of additive present.

GENEPIO:0002134.label: infectious disease cluster
GENEPIO:0002134.definition: A disease cluster in which two or more cases have been linked by an infectious disease transmission process.

GENEPIO:0002146.label: assembly genome size specification
GENEPIO:0002146.definition: A specification for the size of an assembled genome as measured in base pairs.

GENEPIO:0002170.label: test drug minimum concentration specification
GENEPIO:0002170.definition: This is the minimum concentration of a drug applied during an an assay.

GENEPIO:0002148.label: date value specification (ISO 8601)
GENEPIO:0002148.definition: A date should be recorded as YYYY-MM-DD according to ISO 8601.  HOWEVER ... OWL 2.0 does not include xsd:date as a permitted data type, so this value specification only accepts xsd:dateTime

GENEPIO:0002155.label: date of diagnosis (ISO 8601)
GENEPIO:0002155.definition: The point at which a clinical diagnosis is made.

GENEPIO:0002157.label: subject age at time of specimen collection specification

GENEPIO:0001785.label: specimen extraction location - city
GENEPIO:0001785.definition: The specimen extraction location - city is the city where a specimen was taken (extracted) from a subject or environment

GENEPIO:0000117.label: specimen extraction location - city or region
GENEPIO:0000117.definition: A specimen extraction location - city or region is the Gazetteer ontology identifier or textual name of the most precise geographical location available for the site of a specimen extraction event.

GENEPIO:0000118.label: specimen extraction location - country
GENEPIO:0000118.definition: A specimen location country is the country of the site of a given specimen collection event.

GENEPIO:0002097.label: specimen extraction location - state/province/territory/region
GENEPIO:0002097.definition: A specimen extraction location - city or region is the Gazetteer ontology identifier or textual name of the most precise geographical location available for the site of a specimen extraction event.

GENEPIO:0002144.label: unsigned integer value specification
GENEPIO:0002144.definition: A 32 bit number having a range 0 - 4294967295.

GENEPIO:0002156.label: subject age specification
GENEPIO:0002156.definition: A subject age is the age since birth of a given organism that is involved in an investigation or study at a given time.

GENEPIO:0002224.label: isolate preparation service
GENEPIO:0002224.definition: An isolate preparation service prepares isolates for molecular sequencing.

OBI:0001904.label: sequencing service
OBI:0001904.definition: A service provides sequencing service which is the realization of some sequencing such as RNA and DNA sequencing in which the service provider role is realized.

GENEPIO:0002164.label: subject identifier specification
GENEPIO:0002164.definition: A subject identifier specification is a specification including datatype pertaining to a given standard's subject identifier field.

GENEPIO:0002750.label: animal rinse
GENEPIO:0002750.definition: Animal rinse is a rinse derived from animal material of one or more animals.

GENEPIO:0001267.label: plant rinse
GENEPIO:0001267.definition: Plant rinse is a rinse derived from plant material from one or more plants.

GENEPIO:0001338.label: earth surface
GENEPIO:0001338.definition: Earth surface is the entire surface of planet Earth, at the general boundary between water or land, and the surrounding atmosphere, from a navigational (latitude, longitude, and altitude) perspective.

EFO:0002950.label: pregnancy
EFO:0002950.definition: The state or condition of having a developing embryo or fetus in the body (uterus), after union of an ovum and spermatozoon, during the period from conception to birth.

EFO:0004318.label: smoking behavior
EFO:0004318.definition: Inhaling and exhaling the smoke of tobacco or something similar to tobacco.

GO:0007610.label: behavior
GO:0007610.definition: The actions or reactions of an object or organism, usually in relation to the environment or surrounding world of stimuli. E.g. Fixed action pattern courtship behaviour in Drosophila. Forager behaviour in honey bees.

GO:0000003.label: reproductive process
GO:0000003.definition: A process in which an organism or part of an organism participates towards the generation of offspring.

TRANS:0000000.label: transmission of infection
TRANS:0000000.definition: A process that is the means during which the pathogen is transmitted directly or indirectly from its natural reservoir, a susceptible host or source to a new host.

HP:0012211.label: Abnormal renal physiology
HP:0012211.definition: An abnormal functionality of the kidney.

HP:0010935.label: Abnormality of the upper urinary tract
HP:0010935.definition: An abnormality of the upper urinary tract.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Abnormality of the upper urinary tract

HP:0011277.label: Abnormality of the urinary system physiology

HP:0001871.label: Abnormality of blood and blood-forming tissues
HP:0001871.definition: An abnormality of the hematopoietic system.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Abnormality of blood and blood-forming tissues

HP:0000152.label: Abnormality of head or neck
HP:0000152.definition: An abnormality of head and neck.

HP:0001626.label: Abnormality of the cardiovascular system
HP:0001626.definition: Any abnormality of the cardiovascular system.

HP:0000478.label: Abnormality of the eye
HP:0000478.definition: Any abnormality of the eye, including location, spacing, and intraocular abnormalities.

HP:0000119.label: Abnormality of the genitourinary system
HP:0000119.definition: The presence of any abnormality of the genitourinary system.

HP:0002715.label: Abnormality of the immune system
HP:0002715.definition: An abnormality of the immune system.

HP:0001574.label: Abnormality of the integument
HP:0001574.definition: An abnormality of the integument, which consists of the skin and the superficial fascia.

HP:0003011.label: Abnormality of the musculature
HP:0003011.definition: Abnormality originating in one or more muscles, i.e., of the set of muscles of body.

HP:0000707.label: Abnormality of the nervous system
HP:0000707.definition: An abnormality of the nervous system.

HP:0000924.label: Abnormality of the skeletal system
HP:0000924.definition: An abnormality of the skeletal system.

HP:0025142.label: Constitutional symptom
HP:0025142.definition: A symptom or manifestation indicating a systemic or general effect of a disease and that may affect the general well-being or status of an individual.

HP:0000079.label: Abnormality of the urinary system
HP:0000079.definition: An abnormality of the urinary system.

HP:0031815.label: Abnormal oral physiology
HP:0031815.definition: A functional anomaly of the mouth (which is also known as the oral cavity).

HP:0000315.label: Abnormality of the orbital region
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Abnormality of the region around the eyes
oboInOwl:hasNarrowSynonym: Malformation of the orbital region of the face
Anomaly of the orbital region of the face
Deformity of the orbital region of the face

HP:0032039.label: Abnormality of the ocular adnexa
HP:0032039.definition: An anomaly of the adjacent structures (i.e., adnexa) of the eye, defined as the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva.

HP:0011389.label: Functional abnormality of the inner ear
HP:0011389.definition: An abnormality of the function of the inner ear.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Functional abnormality of the inner ear

HP:0012373.label: Abnormal eye physiology
HP:0012373.definition: A functional anomaly of the eye.

HP:0010750.label: Dermatochalasis
HP:0010750.definition: Loss of elasticity of the upper and lower eyelids causing the skin to sag and bulge.

HP:0000622.label: Blurred vision
HP:0000622.definition: Lack of sharpness of vision resulting in the inability to see fine detail.

HP:0031703.label: Abnormal ear morphology
HP:0031703.definition: Any structural anomaly of the ear.

HP:0012638.label: Abnormality of nervous system physiology
HP:0012638.definition: A functional anomaly of the nervous system.

HP:0011842.label: Abnormality of skeletal morphology
HP:0011842.definition: An abnormality of the form, structure, or size of the skeletal system.

HP:0011122.label: Abnormality of skin physiology
HP:0011122.definition: Any abnormality of the physiological function of the skin.

HP:0011729.label: Abnormality of joint mobility
HP:0011729.definition: An abnormality in the range and ease of motion of joints across their normal range.

HP:0001387.label: Joint stiffness
HP:0001387.definition: Joint stiffness is a perceived sensation of tightness in a joint or joints when attempting to move them after a period of inactivity. Joint stiffness typically subsides over time.

HP:0004323.label: Abnormality of body weight
HP:0004323.definition: An abnormal increase or decrease of weight or an abnormal distribution of mass in the body.

HP:0025429.label: Abnormal cry
HP:0025429.definition: Any anomaly of the vocalizing of an infant's crying, i.e.,the typically loud voice production that is accompanied by tears and agitation.

HP:0011025.label: Abnormal cardiovascular system physiology
HP:0011025.definition: Abnormal functionality of the cardiovascular system.

HP:0002321.label: Vertigo
HP:0002321.definition: An abnormal sensation of spinning while the body is actually stationary.

HP:0001892.label: Abnormal bleeding
HP:0001892.definition: An abnormal susceptibility to bleeding, often referred to as a bleeding diathesis. A bleeding diathesis may be related to vascular, platelet and coagulation defects.

HP:0011029.label: Internal hemorrhage
HP:0011029.definition: The presence of hemorrhage within the body.

HP:0012337.label: Abnormal homeostasis
HP:0012337.definition: An anomaly in the processes involved in the maintenance of an internal equilibrium.

HP:0003110.label: Abnormality of urine homeostasis
HP:0003110.definition: An abnormality of the composition of urine or the levels of its components.

HP:0002587.label: Projectile vomiting
HP:0002587.definition: Vomiting that ejects the gastric contents with great force.

HP:0025089.label: Feculent vomiting
HP:0025089.definition: Vomiting of material that is of fecal origin.

HP:0002028.label: Chronic diarrhea
HP:0002028.definition: The presence of chronic diarrhea, which is usually taken to mean diarrhea that has persisted for over 4 weeks.

HP:0005208.label: Secretory diarrhea
HP:0005208.definition: Watery voluminous diarrhea resulting from an imbalance between ion and water secretion and absorption.

HP:0025085.label: Bloody diarrhea
HP:0025085.definition: Passage of many stools containing blood.

HP:0002018.label: Nausea
HP:0002018.definition: A sensation of unease in the stomach together with an urge to vomit.

HP:0002013.label: Vomiting
HP:0002013.definition: Forceful ejection of the contents of the stomach through the mouth by means of a series of involuntary spasmic contractions.

HP:0012451.label: Acute constipation
HP:0012451.definition: Constipation of sudden onset and lasting for less than three months.

HP:0012450.label: Chronic constipation
HP:0012450.definition: Constipation for longer than three months with fewer than 3 bowel movements per week, straining, lumpy or hard stools, and a sensation of anorectal obstruction or incomplete defecation.

HP:0011848.label: Abdominal colic
HP:0011848.definition: A type of abdominal pain that comes and goes in waves, most often starting and ending suddenly and being of severe intensity.

HP:0032155.label: Abdominal cramps
HP:0032155.definition: A type of abdominal pain characterized by a feeling of contractions and typically fluctuating in intensity.

HP:0032546.label: Abdominal guarding
HP:0032546.definition: A voluntary contraction of the abdominal wall musculature to avoid pain.

HP:0032545.label: Abdominal rigidity
HP:0032545.definition: Involuntary tightening of the abdominal musculature that occurs in response to touching the abdomen to avoid pain. Rigidity can occur in the presence of abdominal inflammation and usually involves only the inflamed area.

HP:0410281.label: Dyspepsia
HP:0410281.definition: A heterogeneous group of symptoms that are localized in the epigastric region. Typical dyspeptic symptoms include postprandial fullness, early satiation, epigastric pain and epigastric burning, but other upper gastrointestinal symptoms such as nausea, belching or abdominal bloating often occur.

HP:0002574.label: Episodic abdominal pain
HP:0002574.definition: An intermittent form of abdominal pain.

HP:0002573.label: Hematochezia
HP:0002573.definition: The passage of fresh (red) blood per anus, usually in or with stools. Most rectal bleeding comes from the colon, rectum, or anus.

HP:0002249.label: Melena
HP:0002249.definition: The passage of blackish, tarry feces associated with gastrointestinal hemorrhage. Melena occurs if the blood remains in the colon long enough for it to be broken down by colonic bacteria. One degradation product, hematin, imbues the stool with a blackish color. Thus, melena generally occurs with bleeding from the upper gastrointestinal tract (e.g., stomach ulcers or duodenal ulcers), since the blood usually remains in the gut for a longer period of time than with lower gastrointestinal bleeding.

HP:0010978.label: Abnormality of immune system physiology
HP:0010978.definition: A functional abnormality of the immune system.

HP:0011804.label: Abnormal muscle physiology
HP:0011804.definition: A functional abnormality of a skeletal muscle.

HP:0012614.label: Abnormal urine cytology
HP:0012614.definition: An anomalous finding in the examination of the urine for cells.

HP:0001538.label: Protuberant abdomen
HP:0001538.definition: A thrusting or bulging out of the abdomen.

HP:0001945.label: Fever
HP:0001945.definition: Elevated body temperature due to failed thermoregulation.

HP:0030884.label: Gastrojejunal tube feeding in infancy
HP:0030884.definition: Feeding problem necessitating gastrojejunal tube feeding.

HP:0011471.label: Gastrostomy tube feeding in infancy
HP:0011471.definition: Feeding problem necessitating gastrostomy tube feeding.

HP:0011469.label: Nasal regurgitation
HP:0011469.definition: Regurgitation of milk through the nose.

HP:0011470.label: Nasogastric tube feeding in infancy
HP:0011470.definition: Feeding problem necessitating nasogastric tube feeding.

HP:0002033.label: Poor suck
HP:0002033.definition: An inadequate sucking reflex, resulting in the difficult of newborns to be breast-fed.

HP:0012647.label: Abnormal inflammatory response
HP:0012647.definition: Any anomaly of the inflammatory response, a response to injury or infection characterized by local vasodilation, extravasation of plasma into intercellular spaces and accumulation of white blood cells and macrophages.

HP:0012719.label: Functional abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract
HP:0012719.definition: Abnormal functionality of the gastrointestinal tract.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Functional abnormality of the GI tract
Functional abnormality of the GI tract

HP:0000969.label: Edema
HP:0000969.definition: An abnormal accumulation of fluid beneath the skin, or in one or more cavities of the body.

HP:0011123.label: Inflammatory abnormality of the skin
HP:0011123.definition: The presence of inflammation of the skin. That is, an abnormality of the skin resulting from the local accumulation of fluid, plasma proteins, and leukocytes.
oboInOwl:hasExactSynonym: Abnormal tendency to infections of the skin
Abnormal tendency to infections of the skin

HP:0001751.label: Vestibular dysfunction
HP:0001751.definition: An abnormality of the functioning of the vestibular apparatus.

HP:0003470.label: Paralysis
HP:0003470.definition: Paralysis of voluntary muscles means loss of contraction due to interruption of one or more motor pathways from the brain to the muscle fibers. Although the word paralysis is often used interchangeably to mean either complete or partial loss of muscle strength, it is preferable to use paralysis or plegia for complete or severe loss of muscle strength, and paresis for partial or slight loss. Motor paralysis results from deficits of the upper motor neurons (corticospinal, corticobulbar, or subcorticospinal). Motor paralysis is often accompanied by an impairment in the facility of movement.

HP:0001350.label: Slurred speech
HP:0001350.definition: Abnormal coordination of muscles involved in speech.

HP:0002027.label: Abdominal pain
HP:0002027.definition: An unpleasant sensation characterized by physical discomfort (such as pricking, throbbing, or aching) and perceived to originate in the abdomen.

HP:0030142.label: Abnormal bowel sounds
HP:0030142.definition: An anomaly of the amount or nature of abdominal sounds. Abdominal sounds (bowel sounds) are made by the movement of the intestines as they promote passage of abdominal contents by peristalsis.

HP:0002039.label: Anorexia
HP:0002039.definition: A lack or loss of appetite for food (as a medical condition).

HP:0002019.label: Constipation
HP:0002019.definition: Infrequent or difficult evacuation of feces.

HP:0002014.label: Diarrhea
HP:0002014.definition: Abnormally increased frequency of loose or watery bowel movements.

HP:0011968.label: Feeding difficulties
HP:0011968.definition: Impaired ability to eat related to problems gathering food and getting ready to suck, chew, or swallow it.

HP:0025063.label: Scaphoid abdomen
HP:0025063.definition: The anterior abdominal wall is sunken and presents a concave rather than a convex contour.

HP:0001376.label: Limitation of joint mobility
HP:0001376.definition: A reduction in the freedom of movement of one or more joints.

HP:0003750.label: Increased muscle fatiguability
HP:0003750.definition: An abnormal, increased fatiguability of the musculature.

HP:0001367.label: Abnormal joint morphology
HP:0001367.definition: An abnormal structure or form of the joints, i.e., one or more of the articulations where two bones join.

HP:0012381.label: Delayed self-feeding during toddler years
HP:0012381.definition: A delay in the development of skills required to feed oneself in the toddler period (between one and three years of age).

HP:0008872.label: Feeding difficulties in infancy
HP:0008872.definition: Impaired feeding performance of an infant as manifested by difficulties such as weak and ineffective sucking, brief bursts of sucking, and falling asleep during sucking. There may be difficulties with chewing or maintaining attention.

HP:0000790.label: Hematuria
HP:0000790.definition: The presence of blood in the urine. Hematuria may be gross hematuria (visible to the naked eye) or microscopic hematuria (detected by dipstick or microscopic examination of the urine).

HP:0000083.label: Renal insufficiency
HP:0000083.definition: A reduction in the level of performance of the kidneys in areas of function comprising the concentration of urine, removal of wastes, the maintenance of electrolyte balance, homeostasis of blood pressure, and calcium metabolism.

HP:0011032.label: Abnormality of fluid regulation
HP:0011032.definition: An abnormality of the regulation of body fluids.

HP:0000508.label: Ptosis
HP:0000508.definition: The upper eyelid margin is positioned 3 mm or more lower than usual and covers the superior portion of the iris (objective); or, the upper lid margin obscures at least part of the pupil (subjective).

HP:0032148.label: Episodic pain
HP:0032148.definition: Intermittant pain, i.e., pain that occurs occasionally and at irregular intervals.

HP:0011442.label: Abnormality of central motor function
HP:0011442.definition: An anomaly of the control or production of movement in the central nervous system.

HP:0000708.label: Behavioral abnormality
HP:0000708.definition: An abnormality of mental functioning including various affective, behavioural, cognitive and perceptual abnormalities.

HP:0002315.label: Headache
HP:0002315.definition: Cephalgia, or pain sensed in various parts of the head, not confined to the area of distribution of any nerve.

HP:0012649.label: Increased inflammatory response
HP:0012649.definition: A abnormal increase in the inflammatory response to injury or infection.

HP:0025270.label: Abnormality of esophagus physiology
HP:0025270.definition: Any physiological abnormality of the esophagus.

HP:0011024.label: Abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract
HP:0011024.definition: An abnormality of the gastrointestinal tract.

HP:0025032.label: Abnormality of digestive system physiology
HP:0025032.definition: A functional anomaly of the digestive system.

HP:0025086.label: Bloody mucoid diarrhea
HP:0025086.definition: Passage of many stools containing blood and mucus.

HP:0012378.label: Fatigue
HP:0012378.definition: A subjective feeling of tiredness characterized by a lack of energy and motivation.

HP:0012531.label: Pain
HP:0012531.definition: An unpleasant sensory and emotional experience associated with actual or potential tissue damage, or described in terms of such damage.

HP:0030143.label: Hyperactive bowel sounds
HP:0030143.definition: An increased amount of bowel sounds.

HP:0030144.label: Hypoactive bowel sounds
HP:0030144.definition: An decreased amount of bowel sounds.

HP:0030145.label: Lack of bowel sounds
HP:0030145.definition: Complete lack of abdominal sounds as assayed by examination of the abdomen with a stethoscope.

HP:0000359.label: Abnormality of the inner ear
HP:0000359.definition: An abnormality of the inner ear.

HP:0030669.label: Abnormal ocular adnexa morphology
HP:0030669.definition: A structural anomaly of the adjacent structures (i.e., adnexa) of the eye, defined as the lacrimal apparatus, the extraocular muscles and the eyelids, eyelashes, eyebrows and the conjunctiva.

HP:0100738.label: Abnormal eating behavior
HP:0100738.definition: Abnormal eating habit with excessive or insufficient consumption of food or any other abnormal pattern of food consumption.

HP:0000217.label: Xerostomia
HP:0000217.definition: Dryness of the mouth due to salivary gland dysfunction.

GENEPIO:0001572.label: project relevance
GENEPIO:0001572.definition: Indicates how the knowledge derived from the project can be applied, and to what field(s).

OBI:0001892.label: specification of data to be generated in an investigation
OBI:0001892.definition: An objective specification which indicates the type of data that will be generated and submitted to a database.

OBI:0000963.label: categorical label
OBI:0000963.definition: A label that is part of a categorical datum and that indicates the value of the data item on the categorical scale.

IAO:0000003.label: measurement unit label
IAO:0000003.definition: A measurement unit label is as a label that is part of a scalar measurement datum and denotes a unit of measure.

NCIT:C60776.label: Contact Information
NCIT:C60776.definition: Information regarding the means of contacting a person or group.

NCIT:C89084.label: Undetermined
NCIT:C89084.definition: A term referring to the lack of definitive clinical or pathologic criteria for a tumor to predict its clinical course or to classify it as benign or malignant.

EFO:0001444.label: measurement
EFO:0001444.definition: A measurement is an information entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by an instrument.

GENEPIO:0002008.label: Mycobacterium tuberculosis lineage
GENEPIO:0002008.definition: A Mycobacterium tuberculosis lineage is a named family of strains of tuberculosis, named usually with reference to their shared geographic origin.

OBI:0000679.label: average value
OBI:0000679.definition: A  data item that is produced as the output of an averaging data transformation and represents the average value of the input data.

IAO:0000100.label: data set
IAO:0000100.definition: A data item that is an aggregate of other data items of the same type that have something in common. Averages and distributions can be determined for data sets.

GENEPIO:0001850.label: datum status
GENEPIO:0001850.definition:
A datum status is the state of a measurable datum - whether it has been collected or determined, etc. - at some point in time (by default, the last known state) during a measurement process.

A datum's information privacy constraints can be defined mainly by way of the "data protection role".

The datum status's given states (missing, recorded, etc.) may be accompanied by values that they are represented as in 3rd party databases by using the "has database crossreference" hasDbXref relation, e.g. "hasDbXref 'NCBI Biosample: 'not collected'" 

Note that a given datum's status value is metadata, i.e. a statement about a particular datum in the case where no actual data entry or categorical choice for that datum has been made.

IAO:0000109.label: measurement datum
IAO:0000109.definition: A measurement datum is an information content entity that is a recording of the output of a measurement such as produced by a device.

IAO:0000140.label: setting datum
IAO:0000140.definition: A settings datum is a datum that denotes some configuration of an instrument.

APOLLO_SV:00000031.label: simulation of population
APOLLO_SV:00000031.definition: A simulation of the aggregate of organisms that are members of the population participating in a simulator.

GENEPIO:0001790.label: specimen datum
GENEPIO:0001790.definition: This is a catch-all category for listing specimen related terms

GENEPIO:0001532.label: specimen food source or product datum
GENEPIO:0001532.definition: A food source or product datum is a particular attribute (feature, quality or process history) of the food sample that an organism was found on or in.

GENEPIO:0002100.label: test drug maximum concentration
GENEPIO:0002100.definition: This is the maximum concentration of a drug applied during an an assay.

GENEPIO:0002101.label: test drug minimum concentration
GENEPIO:0002101.definition: This is the minimum concentration of a drug applied during an an assay.

APOLLO_SV:00000211.label: transmission probability
APOLLO_SV:00000211.definition: The probability of the occurence of an infection acquisition from one infected organism to another when in contact.

IAO:0000577.label: centrally registered identifier symbol
IAO:0000577.definition: A symbol that is part of a CRID and that is sufficient to look up a record from the CRID's registry.

IAO:0000029.label: numeral
IAO:0000029.definition: A symbol that denotes a number.

IAO:0000031.label: integer numeral
IAO:0000031.definition: a numeral that denotes an integer

OBI:0001933.label: value specification
OBI:0001933.definition: An information content entity that specifies a value within a classification scheme or on a quantitative scale.

FOODON:03530005.label: adjunct characteristics of food
FOODON:03530005.definition: Additional groups of descriptors of a miscellaneous nature. [FDA CFSAN 1995]

APOLLO_SV:00000296.label: case definition
APOLLO_SV:00000296.definition: An information content entity that specifies the criteria that an organism must meet to be considered to be in some abnormal state.

IAO:0000027.label: data item
IAO:0000027.definition: a data item is an information content entity that is intended to be a truthful statement about something (modulo, e.g., measurement precision or other systematic errors) and is constructed/acquired by a method which reliably tends to produce (approximately) truthful statements.

IAO:0000009.label: datum label
IAO:0000009.definition: A label is a symbol that is part of some other datum and is used to either partially define  the denotation of that datum or to provide a means for identifying the datum as a member of the set of data with the same label

IAO:0000033.label: directive information entity
IAO:0000033.definition: An information content entity whose concretizations indicate to their bearer how to realize them in a process.

IAO:0000314.label: document part
IAO:0000314.definition: an information content entity that is part of a document

IAO:0000028.label: symbol
IAO:0000028.definition: An information content entity that is a mark(s) or character(s) used as a conventional representation of another entity.

IAO:0000300.label: textual entity
IAO:0000300.definition: A textual entity is a part of a manifestation (FRBR sense), a generically dependent continuant whose concretizations are patterns of glyphs intended to be interpreted as words, formulas, etc.

APOLLO_SV:00000191.label: transmission coefficient
APOLLO_SV:00000191.definition: An information content entity that represents the rate that an infection moves from infected individuals to susceptible individuals in a population.

STATO:0000258.label: variable
STATO:0000258.definition: a variable is a data item which can assume any of a set of values, either as determined by an agent or as randomly occuring through observation.

EFO:0000719.label: temporal measurement
EFO:0000719.definition: A temporal entity is an entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time. An occurrent is something which exists over time, rather than existing completely at many times

GENEPIO:0002110.label: MIC diffusion measurement datum
GENEPIO:0002110.definition: A MIC test measurement resulting from a laboratory diffusion method.

GENEPIO:0002044.label: MIC dilution measurement datum
GENEPIO:0002044.definition: A MIC test measurement resulting from a laboratory dilution method.

OBI:0001940.label: N50
OBI:0001940.definition: the weighted median item size or N50 is a weighted median of the lengths of items, equal to the length of the longest item i such that the sum of the lengths of items greater than or equal in length to i is greater than or equal to half the length of all of the items. With regard to assemblies the items are typically contigs or scaffolds. It therefore denotes the ability of the software to create contigs and provides information about the resulting sequence assembly

IAO:0000408.label: length measurement datum
IAO:0000408.definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of length quality

IAO:0000414.label: mass measurement datum
IAO:0000414.definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measurement of mass quality

IAO:0000416.label: time measurement datum
IAO:0000416.definition: A scalar measurement datum that is the result of measuring a temporal interval

ARO:3004360.label: antimicrobial resistance testing reference standard
ARO:3004360.definition: Uses breakpoints to create standards for interpreting the clinical outcome of an MIC value for a particular microbial species and antimicrobial agent

OBI:0000658.label: data representational model
OBI:0000658.definition: Data representational model is an information content entity of the  relationships between data items. A data representational model is encoded in a data format specification such as for cytoscape or biopax.

IAO:0000007.label: action specification
IAO:0000007.definition: a directive information entity that describes an action the bearer will take

APOLLO_SV:00000194.label: individual treatment control strategy
APOLLO_SV:00000194.definition: An infectious disease control strategy that immediately targets individuals.

IAO:0000005.label: objective specification
IAO:0000005.definition: a directive information entity that describes an intended process endpoint. When part of a plan specification the concretization is realized in a planned process in which the bearer tries to effect the world so that the process endpoint is achieved.

IAO:0000104.label: plan specification
IAO:0000104.definition: A directive information entity with action specifications and objective specifications as parts that, when concretized, is realized in a process in which the bearer tries to achieve the objectives by taking the actions specified.

APOLLO_SV:00000173.label: census
APOLLO_SV:00000173.definition: The count of a specific entity in a specified region at a specified time.

GENEPIO:0002133.label: disease cluster
GENEPIO:0002133.definition: A disease cluster is an unusually high incidence of a particular disease or disorder occurring in close proximity in terms of both time and geography.

GENEPIO:0000156.label: project data type
GENEPIO:0000156.definition: A general label indicating the primary study goal. These are only relevant for Primary submission projects (not Umbrella projects).

OBI:0500000.label: study design
OBI:0500000.definition: A plan specification comprised of protocols (which may specify how and what kinds of data will be gathered) that are executed as part of an investigation and is realized during a study design execution.

OBI:0001899.label: target capture specification
OBI:0001899.definition: A plan specification which specifies how the material enrichment procedure will influence the scale, or type of material that will be assayed in the specimen.

OBI:0001896.label: investigation assay specification
OBI:0001896.definition: A plan specification which indicates the assay type used to obtain data.

OBI:0001884.label: specimen-based scope of investigation specification
OBI:0001884.definition: A plan specification which specifies the scope of an investigation based on the heterogeneity of organisms or type of material that are the specified input of specimen collection.

OBI:0001882.label: target material in specimen specification
OBI:0001882.definition: A plan specification which specifies the type of material that will be assayed in an investigation.

OBI:0000938.label: categorical measurement datum
OBI:0000938.definition: A measurement datum that is reported on a categorical scale

STATO:0000047.label: count
STATO:0000047.definition: a count is a data item denoted by an integer and represented the number of instances or occurences of an entity

GENEPIO:0001654.label: geographic location datum
GENEPIO:0001654.definition: A geographical location datum is a datum that refers to a real, hypothesized or fanciful spatial location

GENEPIO:0001607.label: investigation datum
GENEPIO:0001607.definition: A categorical investigation datum is a datum pertaining to some entity examined for scientific research or diagnostic purposes and which has a scope that is broader than one of the clinical, environmental or epidemiological domains.

IAO:0000032.label: scalar measurement datum
IAO:0000032.definition: a scalar measurement datum is a measurement datum that is composed of two parts, numerals and a unit label.

OBI:0000973.label: sequence data
OBI:0000973.definition: A measurement datum that representing the primary structure of a macromolecule(it's sequence) sometimes associated with an indicator of confidence of that measurement.

NCIT:C42614.label: Name
NCIT:C42614.definition: The words or language units by which a thing is known.

GENEPIO:0001051.label: NCBI BioSample isolate (human name or description)
GENEPIO:0001051.definition: identification or description of the specific individual from which this sample was obtained
