GENEPIO:0001055.label: NCBI pathotype
GENEPIO:0001055.definition: A pathotype is a common name for a group of organisms (of the same species) that have the same pathogenicity on a specified host

GENEPIO:0002111.label: antimicrobial resistance testing reference standard version
GENEPIO:0002111.definition: The version of the antimicrobial reistance testing reference standard protocol used in assessing an isolate.

OBI:0001898.label: comment on investigation
OBI:0001898.definition: A textual entity that is about any of the aspects of an investigation worth noting

SIO:000136.label: description
SIO:000136.definition: A description is language entity in which elements of a language (formal or natural) are used to characterize an entity.

GENEPIO:0002132.label: detection limit
GENEPIO:0002132.definition: The detection limit denotes the smallest measure that can be detected with reasonable certainty for a given analytical procedure.

OBI:0001615.label: investigation description
OBI:0001615.definition: A textual entity that describes an investigation.

OBI:0001622.label: investigation title
OBI:0001622.definition: A textual entity that denotes an investigation.

GENEPIO:0002141.label: latitude and longitude coordinate (NCBI BioSample format)
GENEPIO:0002141.definition: The geographical coordinates of the location where the sample was collected. Specify as degrees latitude and longitude in format "d[d.dddd] N|S d[dd.dddd] W|E", eg, 38.98 N 77.11 W

GENEPIO:0000131.label: note
GENEPIO:0000131.definition: A note is text that provides human-readable information on one or more subjects.

GENEPIO:0002130.label: virulence factor name
GENEPIO:0002130.definition: The name of the virulence factor molecule produced by a pathogen that specifically causes disease, or that influences the host's function to allow the pathogen to thrive.

GENEPIO:0002131.label: virulence testing protocol name
GENEPIO:0002131.definition: The laboratory protocol used to determine virulence phenotypes and markers.

NCIT:C71898.label: Proprietary Name
NCIT:C71898.definition: The part of the name or logo associated with a specific product or service identifying and distinguishing it from varieties of the same product or service marketed by competing companies.

IAO:0000634.label: notes section
IAO:0000634.definition: A part of a document containing typically short notes about the document itself and/or the authors. Often the notes section contains subsections related to funding, competing interests, ethical approval, etc.

VT:0002292.label: gestation period duration
VT:0002292.definition: The length of time between when a fertilized egg implants in the wall of the uterus and the birth of offspring.

OBI:0001167.label: age measurement datum
OBI:0001167.definition: A time measurement datum that is the result of measurement of age of an organism

EFO:0004953.label: date of diagnosis
EFO:0004953.definition: The point at which a clinical diagnosis is made.

GENEPIO:0001126.label: lifespan history item
GENEPIO:0001126.definition: A livespan history item is a date-associated event pertaining to the life of a subject.

GENEPIO:0001041.label: organism location history datum
GENEPIO:0001041.definition: A time measurement datum that pertains to an organism's physical location.

OBI:0001508.label: sampling time measurement datum
OBI:0001508.definition: A time measurement datum when an observation is made or a sample is taken from a material as measured from some reference point.

GENEPIO:0001023.label: treatment history datum
GENEPIO:0001023.definition: A time measurement datum that pertains to a patient's medical treatment.

NCIT:C42775.label: E-mail Address
NCIT:C42775.definition: A text string identifier for a location to which e-mail can be delivered.

NCIT:C25621.label: Postal Code
NCIT:C25621.definition: Any system designed to expedite the sorting and delivery of mail by assigning a series of alphanumeric codes to each delivery area. Also used to refer to any individual delivery area code.

GENEPIO:0001889.label: Canada postal code FSA
GENEPIO:0001889.definition: The "Canadia postal code FSA" is the leading FSA (Forward Sortation Area) 3 character portion of a full 6 character Canadian postal code.  It can be used to reduce the geographic granularity of a postal code for data generalization or obfuscation.

SIO:001322.label: IP number
SIO:001322.definition: an IP number is an number to connect to a device on the internet.

OBI:0001617.label: PubMed ID
OBI:0001617.definition: A CRID symbol that is sufficient to look up a citation from the PubMed, a literature database of life sciences and biomedical information.

SIO:000811.label: URL
SIO:000811.definition: A Uniform Resource Locator or Universal Resource Locator (URL) is a specific character string that constitutes a reference to an Internet resource.

GENEPIO:0001659.label: case identifier
GENEPIO:0001659.definition: A case ID is a unique identifier associated with a particular episode of care for an individual or animal.

data:2219.label: database field name
data:2219.definition: The name of a field in a database.

OBI:0001629.label: grant identifier
OBI:0001629.definition: A CRID symbol used to identify a grant.

OBI:0001141.label: individual organism identifier
OBI:0001141.definition: a CRID symbol used to distinguish one individual organism from another.

OBI:0001628.label: investigation identifier
OBI:0001628.definition: A CRID symbol used to identify an investigation.

GENEPIO:0001644.label: isolate identifier
GENEPIO:0001644.definition: An isolate identifier is an identifier assigned to a given isolate by a particular agency that is handling or storing it.

SIO:000729.label: record identifier
SIO:000729.definition: A record identifier is an identifier for a database entry.

GENEPIO:0000079.label: sequencing run sample identifier
GENEPIO:0000079.definition: A sequencing run sample identifier is an alphanumeric identifier for a sample.  In bioinformatics processing this identifier is assigned to a sample in order to track it through the process of sequencing and analysis.

OBI:0001616.label: specimen identifier
OBI:0001616.definition: A CRID symbol denotes a specimen and used to distinguish one specimen from another in an investigation.

GENEPIO:0001429.label: strain identifier
GENEPIO:0001429.definition: A strain identifier is the unique microbial or eukaryotic strain name from a reference database that a sample has been matched to.

GENEPIO:0001799.label: user identifier
GENEPIO:0001799.definition: A user identifier is an identifier provided as part of an authentication process of a client (user) to a service (server).  User identifiers normally persist over time, in contrast to session identifiers which are temporary.

MI:0489.label: source database
MI:0489.definition: Database that originally provided the interaction record for exchange purposes.

NCIT:C40978.label: Telephone Number
NCIT:C40978.definition: A sequence of decimal digits (0-9) that is used for identifying a destination telephone line or other device in a telephone network.

IDO:0000416.label: infectious agent carrier role
IDO:0000416.definition: An infectious agent host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its extended organism contains an infectious agent, the infectious agent has the infectious disposition towards the host, and the host has no symptoms of the infectious disease caused by the infectious agent.

IDO:0000414.label: infectious agent host role
IDO:0000414.definition: A pathogen host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its extended organism contains an infectious agent.

IDO:0000445.label: resistance to drug
IDO:0000445.definition: A protective resistance that mitigates the damaging effects of a drug.

IDO:0000581.label: antibiotic resistance
IDO:0000581.definition: A resistance to drug that mitigates the damaging effects of an antibiotic.

IDO:0000477.label: acute infectious disease course
IDO:0000477.definition: An infectious disease course that begins soon after infection is established and progresses rapidly to severe stages.

IDO:0000590.label: chronic infectious disease course
IDO:0000590.definition: An infectious disease course that unfolds over a long period of time.

IDO:0000615.label: colony
IDO:0000615.definition: An organism population persisting in a site it has colonized.

IDO:0000512.label: diseased population
IDO:0000512.definition: An organism population in whose members an infectious disease is being realized.

IDO:0000592.label: immune population
IDO:0000592.definition: An organism population whose members have acquired immunity to an infectious agent.

IDO:0000511.label: infected population
IDO:0000511.definition: An organism population whose members have an infection.

IDO:0000513.label: infectious agent population
IDO:0000513.definition: An organism population whose members each have an infectious disposition.

IDO:0000515.label: normal resident microbiota population
IDO:0000515.definition: An organism population whose members are participating in non-parasitic symbiosis with a particular host.

IDO:0000514.label: susceptible population
IDO:0000514.definition: An organism population whose members are not infected with an infectious agent and who lack immunity to the infectious agent.

IDO:0000538.label: pathogen host
IDO:0000538.definition: An organism bearing a pathogen host role.

IDO:0000569.label: asymptomatic host of infectious agent
IDO:0000569.definition: An organism that is host to an infectious agent and has no symptoms of the infectious disease associated with the infectious agent.

IDO:0000573.label: symptomatic host of infectious agent
IDO:0000573.definition: An organism who is host to an infectious agent and has symptoms of the infectious disease associated with the infectious agent

IDO:0000537.label: infectious agent host
IDO:0000537.definition: An organism bearing an infectious agent host role.

IDO:0000496.label: long-term non-progressing infectious disease course
IDO:0000496.definition: A chronic infectious disease course that does not progress to severe stages for a long period of time.

IDO:0000616.label: infectious agent colony
IDO:0000616.definition: A colony whose members are infectious agents.

IDO:0000415.label: pathogen host role
IDO:0000415.definition: A host role borne by an organism in virtue of the fact that its extended organism contains a pathogen.

GENEPIO:0001822.label: ASFIS
GENEPIO:0001822.definition: ASFIS is a database curated by the United Nations Food And Agriculture Organization (FAO) Fisheries and Aquaculture Statistics and Information Branch (FIPS). It contains over 12,700 species items selected according to their interest or relation to fisheries and aquaculture.
IAO:0000118: UN FAO Fisheries and Aquaculture Statistics and Information Branch database

GENEPIO:0001828.label: EcoLexicon
GENEPIO:0001828.definition: EcoLexicon is a terminological resource developed by the LexiCon Research Group at the University of Granada.

GENEPIO:0001827.label: Geonames
GENEPIO:0001827.definition: The GeoNames geographical database covers all countries and contains over eleven million placenames that are available for download free of charge.

GENEPIO:0001813.label: ITIS
GENEPIO:0001813.definition: The Integrated Taxonomic Information System (ITIS) contains authoritative taxonomic information on plants, animals, fungi, and microbes of North America and the world.

GENEPIO:0001818.label: MESH
GENEPIO:0001818.definition: MeSH is the National Library of Medicine's controlled vocabulary thesaurus. It consists of sets of terms naming descriptors in a hierarchical structure that permits searching at various levels of specificity.

GENEPIO:0001819.label: NCIT
GENEPIO:0001819.definition: The National Cancer Institute Thesaurus (NCIt) provides reference terminology for many NCI and other systems. It covers vocabulary for clinical care, translational and basic research, and public information and administrative activities.

GENEPIO:0001820.label: NIFSTD
GENEPIO:0001820.definition: The NIFSTD ontology of the Neuroscience Information Framework is composed of a collection of OWL modules with separate modules covering major domains of neuroscience: anatomy, cell, subcellular, molecule, organism, function and dysfunction.

GENEPIO:0001838.label: PubMed
GENEPIO:0001838.definition: PubMed comprises more than 26 million citations for biomedical literature from MEDLINE, life science journals, and online books. Citations may include links to full-text content from PubMed Central and publisher web sites.

GENEPIO:0001821.label: SNOMEDCT
GENEPIO:0001821.definition: SNOMED CT is a large clinical health terminology product owned and distributed by SNOMED International.

GENEPIO:0001825.label: Wikipedia
GENEPIO:0001825.definition: Wikipedia is a free online encyclopedia that aims to allow anyone to edit articles.

MPATH:603.label: pathological anatomical entity
MPATH:603.definition: Anatomically located instance of pathological response or entity.

MPATH:607.label: healing and repair structure
MPATH:607.definition: Physical entity or structure associated with normal or abnormal tissue healing or repair following extrinsic or intrinsic damage.

NCIT:C100811.definition: An individual who provides support to a pregnant individual.

NCIT:C100812.label: Sexual Partner
NCIT:C100812.definition: A person with whom one has had sexual relations.

NCIT:C20108.label: Country Code
NCIT:C20108.definition: An alphanumeric system designed to identify countries. The ISO 3166 standard includes a two letter representation, a three letter representation, and a 3 number representation. The last two are identical to the UN system. The US State Department system maintains a separate two letter representation code set.

GENEPIO:0001832.label: ANSI INCITS 38
GENEPIO:0001832.definition: Information Technology – Codes For The Identification Of The States And Equivalent Areas Within The United States, Puerto Rico, And The Insular Areas

GENEPIO:0000119.label: Darwin Core Terms
GENEPIO:0000119.definition: The Darwin Core is body of standards. It includes a glossary of terms (in other contexts these might be called properties, elements, fields, columns, attributes, or concepts) intended to facilitate the sharing of information about biological diversity by providing reference definitions, examples, and commentaries.

GENEPIO:0002136.label: EBI European Nucleotide Archive Webin
GENEPIO:0002136.definition: The European Nucleotide Archive (ENA) provides a comprehensive record of the world's nucleotide sequencing information, covering raw sequencing data, sequence assembly information and functional annotation. Webin is an ENA interface and standard for sequence submissions.

GENEPIO:0002075.label: Genomic Standards Consortium (GSC) standard
GENEPIO:0002075.definition: A Genomic Standards Consortium standard is an international, community-driven standard to facilitate  genomic data integration, discovery and comparison.

GENEPIO:0000109.label: I2B2 Data Protection role standard
GENEPIO:0000109.definition: The I2B2 Workbench Data Protection role standard is a standard which names and lists data protection roles between a user and a given dataset that define the level of detail a user has access to.

GENEPIO:0001666.label: INSDC standard
GENEPIO:0001666.definition: The International Nucleotide Sequence Database Collaboration (INSDC) is a long-standing foundational initiative that operates between DDBJ, EMBL-EBI and NCBI. INSDC covers the spectrum of data raw reads, though alignments and assemblies to functional annotation, enriched with contextual information relating to samples and experimental configurations.

GENEPIO:0001830.label: ISO3166-1
GENEPIO:0001830.definition: ISO 3166-1 is part of the ISO 3166 standard published by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO), and defines codes for the names of countries, dependent territories, and special areas of geographical interest.

GENEPIO:0001831.label: ISO3166-2
GENEPIO:0001831.definition: ISO 3166-2 is part of the ISO 3166 standard published by the International Organization for Standardization (ISO), and defines codes for identifying the principal subdivisions (e.g., provinces or states) of all countries coded in ISO 3166-1.

GENEPIO:0000115.label: NCBI standard
GENEPIO:0000115.definition: The National Center for Biotechnology Information offers standards for submitting genomic project data to their BioProject and BioSample databases.
IAO:0000118: National Center for Biotechnology Information standard

GENEPIO:0001845.label: NHS standard
GENEPIO:0001845.definition: United Kingdom National Health Service trusts, boards, etc. have some terminology in common for public disclosure of patient health conditions.

GENEPIO:0001743.label: public health data standard
GENEPIO:0001743.definition: A data standard related to public health research and service delivery.

GENEPIO:0000036.label: the Global Microbial Identifier Minimum Data for Matching (MDM) Standard
GENEPIO:0000036.definition: the Global Microbial Identifier "Minimum data for Matching" (MDM) standard is a standard that defines essential contextual data fields to be included in genomic sequence repository records.

GENEPIO:0002073.label: National Institute of Allergy and Infectious Disease standard
GENEPIO:0002073.definition: NIAID provides The GSCID/BRC Project and Sample Application Standard. It is designed to capture standardized human pathogen and vector sequencing metadata to support epidemiologic and genotype-phenotype association studies for human infectious diseases.

NCIT:C114939.label: Extremely Preterm Infant
NCIT:C114939.definition: A newborn infant less than 28 weeks, 0 days gestational age.

NCIT:C114931.label: Healthy Preterm Newborn
NCIT:C114931.definition: A healthy newborn whose only diagnoses are those related to prematurity. (NIAID)

NCIT:C114930.label: Healthy Term Newborn
NCIT:C114930.definition: AGA infant delivered after full 37 weeks gestation whose 5 minute Apgar score was above 7, has no major congenital anomalies and was discharged home with mother without any additional diagnoses except for physiologic hyperbilirubinemia. (NIAID)

NCIT:C114938.label: Late Preterm Infant
NCIT:C114938.definition: A newborn infant greater than or equal to 34 weeks, 0 days and less than 37 weeks, 0 days gestational age.

NCIT:C128042.label: Moderate to Late Preterm Infant
NCIT:C128042.definition: A baby born alive with a gestational age between 32 to less than 37 weeks.

NCIT:C114947.label: Postterm Infant
NCIT:C114947.definition: A newborn infant greater than or equal to 42 weeks, 0 days gestational age.

NCIT:C49642.label: Preterm Infant
NCIT:C49642.definition: A newborn infant less than 37 weeks, 0 days gestational age.

NCIT:C118677.label: Very Preterm Infant
NCIT:C118677.definition: A newborn infant greater than 28 weeks, 0 days and less than 34 weeks, 0 days.

NCIT:C91107.label: Young Adult
NCIT:C91107.definition: An indefinite term describing a person who has reached sexual maturity but whose character and personality are still developing. In psychology this generally covers the age range of 20-40.

FOODON:00002747.definition: A surface wipe is a type of swab designed to collect specimen material from some envirronmental surface using a fabric or other material.

NCIT:C16268.label: Elderly

NCIT:C49641.label: In Utero

NCIT:C96572.label: Biological Father

NCIT:C154851.label: Step Father

NCIT:C96580.label: Biological Mother
NCIT:C96580.definition: A female who contributes to the genetic makeup of her offspring from the fertilization of her ovum.

NCIT:C17445.label: Caregiver

NCIT:C93874.definition: A textual identifier for an organization.

NCIT:C43169.label: Bottle
NCIT:C43169.definition: A vessel with a narrow neck designed to accept a specific closure.

NCIT:C41275.label: Vial
NCIT:C41275.definition: A small, often stoppered glass or plastic bottle for holding fluids.

NCIT:C121972.label: Induction Death
NCIT:C121972.definition: Death of the patient due to the toxic side effects of induction therapy.

NCIT:C113381.label: Antepartum Stillbirth
NCIT:C113381.definition: Fetal death greater than or equal to 20 weeks of gestation prior to labor with Apgar scores of 0 at 1 minute, 5 minutes and beyond.

NCIT:C120583.label: Early Stillbirth
NCIT:C120583.definition: Delivery of a dead fetus greater than 22 weeks but less than 28 weeks gestational age, and/or whose birth weight is greater than 500 grams but less than 1,000 grams.

NCIT:C113382.label: Intrapartum Stillbirth
NCIT:C113382.definition: Fetal death greater than or equal to 20 weeks of gestation during labor with Apgar scores of 0 at 1 minute, 5 minutes and beyond.

NCIT:C120585.label: Late Stillbirth
NCIT:C120585.definition: Delivery of a dead fetus greater than 28 weeks gestational age and/or greater than 1,000 grams birth weight.

NCIT:C28147.label: Embryo
NCIT:C28147.definition: An organism in its initial stage of development following fertilization. The human embryonic period lasts approximately eight weeks, during which time organogenesis takes place.

NCIT:C13235.label: Fetus
NCIT:C13235.definition: An unborn or unhatched vertebrate in the later stages of development showing the main recognizable features of the mature being.

NCIT:C27956.label: Infant
NCIT:C27956.definition: A young child between one month and two years of age.

NCIT:C112862.label: Early Fetal Death
NCIT:C112862.definition: Death of a fetus at 10 weeks, 0 days to 15 weeks, 6 days of gestation.

NCIT:C112863.label: Late Fetal Death
NCIT:C112863.definition: Death of a fetus at 16 weeks, 0 days to 19 weeks, 6 days of gestation.

NCIT:C54197.label: Non-Sudden Cardiac Death
NCIT:C54197.definition: An expected natural death from a cardiac cause. This condition usually occurs in persons with pre-existing cardiac abnormalities or disease.

NCIT:C50911.label: Sudden Cardiac Death
NCIT:C50911.definition: An unexpected natural death from a cardiac cause within a short time period from the onset of symptoms.

NCIT:C41085.label: Person Contact Information
NCIT:C41085.definition: Information regarding the person who is acting as a channel for communication between groups.

NCIT:C80082.label: Neonatal Death
NCIT:C80082.definition: Death of a live newborn during the first 28 days of life.

NCIT:C118676.label: Perinatal Mortality
NCIT:C118676.definition: Fetal or infant death during the period of time that includes the antepartum, intrapartum, and neonatal stages.

NCIT:C121303.label: Post Neonatal Death
NCIT:C121303.definition: Death between 28 days and 1 year of life.

NCIT:C111854.label: Sudden Unexplained Death in Childhood
NCIT:C111854.definition: Unexpected death of a child over one year of age, which remains unexplained when all known and possible causes of death have been ruled out.

GENEPIO:0002077.label: subject organism
GENEPIO:0002077.definition: An investigative subject which is an organism.

NCIT:C116772.label: Early Neonatal Death
NCIT:C116772.definition: Death of a live newborn during the first 7 days of life.

NCIT:C116773.label: Late Neonatal Death
NCIT:C116773.definition: Death of live newborn between 7and 27 days after birth.

NCIT:C114870.label: Post-Natal Death at 16-20 Weeks Gestation
NCIT:C114870.definition: A fetus of 16-20 weeks gestational age that shows signs of life at birth but dies after delivery.

NCIT:C85173.label: Sudden Infant Death Syndrome
NCIT:C85173.definition: Unexpected death in infancy which remains unexplained following autopsy, review of the medical history, and investigation of the death circumstances and death scene.

NCIT:C111853.label: Sudden Unexplained Infant Death
NCIT:C111853.definition: Unexpected death of an infant less than one year of age, whose cause of death is not immediately obvious prior to investigation.

NCIT:C120592.label: Very Early Neonatal Death
NCIT:C120592.definition: Death of a live newborn during the first 24 hours of life

GAZ:00002844.label: populated place, Canada
GAZ:00002844.definition: A populated place. A city in Alberta, Canada. Brooks was incorporated as a village on 1910-07-14, and as a town on 1911-09-08. It became a city on 2005-09-01 and is located 168 km east of Calgary on the Trans-Canada Highway and 10 km east of Highway 36.

GAZ:00005075.label: populated place, Democratic Republic of Congo

GAZ:00003034.label: populated place, Republic of South Africa

GAZ:00010010.label: populated place, Zambia
GAZ:00010010.definition: A small town and administrative district in the Western Province of Zambia, on the plains west of the Zambezi River and the Barotse Floodplain, about 70 km from the border with Angola.

GAZ:00003138.label: populated place, contiguous United States of America

NCIT:C85559.label: Antimicrobial Dose Dependent Susceptibility Result
NCIT:C85559.definition: A microbial susceptibility test result in which the growth of microorganisms may be inhibited when higher than normal dosages of an antimicrobial agent are used and maximal possible blood concentration of the antimicrobial agent is achieved.

NCIT:C85560.label: Antimicrobial Intermediate Susceptibility Result (deprecated)
NCIT:C85560.definition: A microbial susceptibility test result in which the growth of microorganisms may be inhibited by the usually achievable concentrations of antimicrobial agent when the recommended dosage is used for the site of infection. The response rates may be lower than for susceptible isolates.

NCIT:C85561.label: Antimicrobial Nonsusceptibility Result (deprecated)
NCIT:C85561.definition: A microbial susceptibility test result in which the growth of microorganisms is not inhibited by the usually achievable concentrations of antimicrobial agent when the recommended dosage is used for the site of infection. This category may be applied to new antimicrobial agents for which no resistant microorganisms have been encountered at the time the initial interpretive criteria are determined. Microorganisms that test with an MIC above or a zone measurement below the susceptible interpretive criteria may be designated as nonsusceptible. A designation of nonsusceptible does not necessarily mean that a resistance mechanism(s) exists in the microorganism.

NCIT:C85562.label: Antimicrobial Resistance Result (deprecated)
NCIT:C85562.definition: A microbial susceptibility test result in which the growth of microorganisms is not inhibited by the usually achievable concentrations of antimicrobial agent with normal dosage, or microorganisms demonstrate minimum inhibitory concentrations (MIC) or zone diameters that fall in the range where specific microbial resistance mechanisms are likely in effect, or clinical efficacy of the agent against the microorganism has not been reliably shown in treatment studies.

NCIT:C85563.label: Antimicrobial Susceptibility Result (deprecated)
NCIT:C85563.definition: A microbial susceptibility test result in which the growth of microorganisms is inhibited by the usually achievable concentrations of antimicrobial agent when the recommended dosage is used for the site of infection.

NCIT:C85555.label: Agar Dilution Method
NCIT:C85555.definition: A method to determine microbial susceptibility to antibiotics in which test bacteria is inoculated onto agar plates with serial dilutions of know quantities of antibiotics. The minimum inhibitory concentration of antibiotic is assessed.

ARO:3004397.label: broth dilution method
ARO:3004397.definition: The microbial species are inoculated in liquid growth medium containing incremental dilutions (usually 2-fold) of the antimicrobial agent.

ARO:3004391.label: diffusion method
ARO:3004391.definition: Microbial species are inoculated in a growth medium onto which antimicrobial agents are transferred by diffusion.

NCIT:C85596.label: Epsilometry
NCIT:C85596.definition: A method to determine microbial susceptibility to antibiotics in which a plastic strip impregnated with the antibiotic of interest is placed on an agar plate that has been inoculated with bacteria. The antibiotic diffuses from the strip producing a concentration gradient of drug on the agar. The point at which the elliptical shaped area of growth inhibition meets the strip is the minimum inhibitory concentration of the drug of interest.

NCIT:C156312.label: Brazilian State
NCIT:C156312.definition: Any of the 27 federal units of Brazil, which include the 26 federal states of Brazil, plus the Federal District which contains the capital city, Brasilia.

NCIT:C156640.label: Concerned Member State
NCIT:C156640.definition: A European Economic Area country that is seeking to obtain marketing authorization, through Mutual Recognition or Decentralized procedures, for a medicinal product that has already been authorized in at least one other European Economic Area country.

NCIT:C106145.label: Mexican State
NCIT:C106145.definition: Any of the 31 states that comprise the United Mexican States.

NCIT:C156641.label: Reference Member State
NCIT:C156641.definition: A European Economic Area country with marketing authorization for a medicinal product that evaluates the marketing authorization application dossier and prepares the assessment report on behalf of another European Economic Area country that is seeking to obtain marketing authorization for the same product through Mutual Recognition or Decentralized procedures.

NCIT:C30010.label: US State
NCIT:C30010.definition: One of the fifty states which is a member of the federation known as the United States of America. Other US geographic areas, such as Puerto Rico and the District of Columbia, are essentially equivalent to State when used in an address.

GAZ:00003956.label: Unincorporated Territory (USA)
GAZ:00003956.definition: An area of the United States of America under United States jurisdiction, to which Congress has determined that only select parts of the United States of America Constitution apply.

OBI:0000094.label: material processing
OBI:0000094.definition: A planned process which results in physical changes in a specified input material.

OBI:0001173.label: service
OBI:0001173.definition: A planned process in which a service provider performs a task (i.e. a planned process) for a service consumer.

OGMS:0000090.label: treatment
OGMS:0000090.definition: A processual entity whose completion is hypothesized (by a healthcare provider) to alleviate the signs and symptoms associated with a disorder

OBI:0000070.label: assay
OBI:0000070.definition: A planned process with the objective to produce information about the material entity that is the evaluant, by physically examining it or its proxies.

APOLLO_SV:00000033.label: counting
APOLLO_SV:00000033.definition: The planned process of finding the number of elements in a finite set of objects.

OBI:0200000.label: data transformation
OBI:0200000.definition: A planned process that produces output data from input data.

OBI:0000066.label: investigation
OBI:0000066.definition: a planned process that consists of parts: planning, study design execution, documentation and which produce conclusion(s).

APOLLO_SV:00000152.label: population survey
APOLLO_SV:00000152.definition: A planned process involving counting numbers of a organism population, possibly including counting sub-populations fulfilling specific criteria.

OBI:0000659.label: specimen collection process
OBI:0000659.definition: A planned process with the objective of collecting a specimen.

OBI:0000968.label: device
OBI:0000968.definition: A material entity that is designed to perform a function in a scientific investigation, but is not a reagent.

OBI:0000079.label: culture medium
OBI:0000079.definition: a processed material that provides the needed nourishment for microorganisms or cells grown in vitro.

OBI:0001879.label: reagent
OBI:0001879.definition: A biological or chemical entity that bears a reagent role in virtue of it being intended for application in a scientific technique  to participate in (or have molecular parts that participate in) a chemical reaction that facilitates the generation of data about some distinct entity, or the generation of some distinct material specified output.

NCIT:C128985.label: Minimum Inhibitory Concentration Test
NCIT:C128985.definition: A laboratory test to determine the lowest concentration of a substance that will inhibit a biological or biochemical function, such as microorganism growth or enzymatic activity.

ARO:3004388.label: in-vitro microbial susceptibility test
ARO:3004388.definition: An experimental test conducted outside of a living organism, usually in a tube or plate.

ERO:0000833.label: molecular assay
ERO:0000833.definition: An assay that generates data about the presence, abundance, structure, function, or activity of biological molecules, or a process that occurs at a molecular level of granularity.

OBI:0000893.label: real time polymerase chain reaction assay
OBI:0000893.definition: An assay, based on the PCR, that amplifies and simultaneously quantifies a specific DNA molecule based on the use of complementary probes/primers. It enables both detection and quantification (as absolute number of copies or relative amount when normalized to DNA input or additional normalizing genes) of one or more specific sequences in a DNA sample.

OBI:0600047.label: sequencing assay
OBI:0600047.definition: An assay the uses chemical or biochemical means to infer the sequence of a biomaterial

GENEPIO:0002107.label: isolation medium
GENEPIO:0002107.definition: An isolation medium is a culture medium which has the disposition to encourage growth of particular bacteria to the exclusion of others in the same growth environment.

CHMO:0000999.label: separation method
CHMO:0000999.definition: A method that results in the separation of two or more components according to some property.

OBI:0600014.label: material component separation
OBI:0600014.definition: a material processing in which components of an input material become segregated in space

OBI:0000740.label: material sample role
OBI:0000740.definition: A material sample role is a specimen role borne by a material entity that is the output of a material sampling process.

EFO:0001799.label: ethnic group
EFO:0001799.definition: An ethnic group is a population whose members have a common heritage that is real or presumed such as common culture, language, religion, behaviour or biological trait.

NCIT:C16143.label: Repository
NCIT:C16143.definition: A facility where items can be deposited for storage or safekeeping.

GENEPIO:0001534.label: disease cluster notification agency
GENEPIO:0001534.definition: An agency that has reported a disease cluster.

OBI:0001942.label: grant agency
OBI:0001942.definition: An organization that provides funding support for projects such as investigations.

OBI:0002198.label: molecular analysis facility organization
OBI:0002198.definition: An organization that provides molecular analysis service.

OBI:0001897.label: organization of sequencing facility contact person
OBI:0001897.definition: An organization that is the affiliation of the contact representative at the sequencing facility

OBI:0001893.label: organization of specimen collector
OBI:0001893.definition: An organization that is the affiliation of the person collecting the specimen

GENEPIO:0002105.label: specimen processing organization type
GENEPIO:0002105.definition: An organization related to the collection, isolate production, sequencing or storage of specimen material or data.

OBI:0001885.label: specimen repository organization
OBI:0001885.definition: An organization that provides a service to store and distribute specimens

OBI:0001880.label: organization of specimen provider principal investigator
OBI:0001880.definition: An organization that is the affiliation of the principal investigator providing the specimens for the investigation

ERO:0001183.label: next generation DNA sequencing
ERO:0001183.definition: A DNA sequencing technique that became commercially available in 2004 and is used by specific commercial platforms that embody a complex interplay of enzymology, chemistry, high-resolution optics, hardware, and software engineering. These instruments allow highly streamlined sample preparation steps prior to DNA sequencing, which provides a significant time savings and a minimal requirement for associated equipment in comparison to the highly automated, multistep pipelines necessary for clone-based high-throughput sequencing. Each technology amplifies single strands of a fragment library and perform sequencing reactions on the amplified strands. The fragment libraries are obtained by annealing platform-specific linkers to blunt-ended fragments generated directly from a genome or DNA source of interest. Because the presence of adapter sequences means that the molecules then can be selectively amplified by PCR, and no bacterial cloning step is required to amplify the genomic fragment in a bacterial intermediate as is done in traditional sequencing approaches.

NCIT:C103180.label: Data Standard
NCIT:C103180.definition: A statement that defines conventions, guidelines, characteristics or methods for consistent data handling to facilitate exchange or processing of the data. This set of criteria are reviewed by and agreed upon by the user community or a governing body before they are released and adopted for use.

GENEPIO:0001342.label: data standard component
GENEPIO:0001342.definition: A data standard component is a utility class used to organize some of the draft or finalized data representational model standards related components that are part of one or more standards.

GENEPIO:0000106.label: draft data standard
GENEPIO:0000106.definition: The 'draft data standard' class contains draft representations of formal or defacto third party standards and related components.  These representations may have been crafted without any involvement of related standards issuers and so no guarantee can be provided about their currency, accuracy or veracity.

GENEPIO:0002178.label: field specification
GENEPIO:0002178.definition: A field specification is the specification of a data field used in a data standard or database table. This includes at least a database field name, and optionally display name, description, and data type (binary blob, numeric, categorical, textual or cross-reference).

OBI:0600005.label: collecting specimen from organism
OBI:0600005.definition: a process with the objective to obtain a material entity that was part of an organism for potential future use in an investigation

OBI:0600012.label: environmental material collection process
OBI:0600012.definition: environmental_material_collection is an acquisition where an object is taken from an environment and put into a storage container. Roles include, environment, thing collected, container, acquirer.

APOLLO_SV:00000043.label: reproduction number
APOLLO_SV:00000043.definition: The average value of transmissions of the infectious agent from one infected organism to another, resulting in an infection.

OBI:0002007.label: SOLiD 3 Plus System
OBI:0002007.definition: A DNA sequencer which is manufacted by the Applied Biosystems corporation. Built upon SOLiD sequencing technology, the machine generates greater than 1 billion mappable reads per run.

OBI:0002024.label: SOLiD 4 System
OBI:0002024.definition: An AB SOLid System which is manufacted by the Applied Biosystems corporation. Built upon SOLiD sequencing technology, the machine generates greater than 1 billion mappable reads per run.

OBI:0002027.label: Genome Analyzer IIe
OBI:0002027.definition: An Illumina Genome Analyzer II which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation. It supports sequencing of single, long or short insert paired end clone libraries relying on sequencing by synthesis technology. The Genome Analyzer IIe makes industry-leading next-generation sequencing technology accessible to more laboratories.

OBI:0002000.label: Genome Analyzer IIx
OBI:0002000.definition: An Illumina Genome Analyzer II which is manufactured by the Illumina corporation. It supports sequencing of single, long or short insert paired end clone libraries relying on sequencing by synthesis technology. The Genome Analyzer IIx is the most widely adopted next-generation sequencing platform and proven and published across the broadest range of research applications.

ERO:0001211.label: massively parallel signature sequencing
ERO:0001211.definition: A DNA sequencing by ligation technique that involves a bead-based method that uses a complex approach of adapter ligation followed by adapter decoding, reading the sequence in increments of four nucleotides; this method made it susceptible to sequence-specific bias or loss of specific sequences.

OBI:0000724.label: Solexa sequencing
OBI:0000724.definition: is a DNA sequencing which allows sequence identification by relying on use of DNA polymerase and reversible terminator. The methods requires immobilization of genomic DNA fragment onto a surface and a specific clonal amplification step known as bridge PCR. Reliance on reversible terminator allow cycles of DNA chain extension by DNA polymerase and imaging without the need of electrophoretic separation of newly synthesized DNA fragment as with Sanger sequencing.

OBI:0000695.label: chain termination sequencing
OBI:0000695.definition: is a DNA sequencing which rely on the use of dideoxynucleotides used in 4 distinct sequencing reaction on the same DNA sample. The dideoxynucleotides, once incorporated in the complementary DNA strand being synthesized by the DNA polymerase prevent any further chain elongation. The newly generated sequences are resolved on a polyacrylamide gel using electrophoresis and labels (either fluorochrome or radioactivity) are used to determine the nucleotide present at a given position

ERO:0000639.label: cycle sequencing
ERO:0000639.definition: A DNA sequencing by synthesis technique used to increase the sensitivity of the DNA sequencing process and permits the use of very small amounts of DNA starting material. This is accomplished by using a temperature cycling process similar to that employed in the polymerase chain reaction.

OBI:0400103.label: DNA sequencer
OBI:0400103.definition: A DNA sequencer is an instrument that determines the order of deoxynucleotides in deoxyribonucleic acid sequences.

OBI:0000018.label: material supplier role
OBI:0000018.definition: a role realized through the process of supplying materials such as animal subjects, reagents or other materials used in an investigation.

OBI:0000832.label: measurement device
OBI:0000832.definition: A device in which a measure function inheres.

OBI:0000436.label: needle
OBI:0000436.definition: a needle is a sharp, hollow device used to penetrate tissue or soft material. When attached to a syringe. it allows delivery of a specific volume of liquid or gaseous mixture.

GENEPIO:0001616.label: subject identifier
GENEPIO:0001616.definition: A subject identifier is an identifier of a subject organism within the context of a particular investigation, study, or specimen extraction event.

OBI:0001169.label: age since birth measurement datum
OBI:0001169.definition: An age measurement datum that is the result of the measurement of the age of an organism since birth, the process of emergence and separation of offspring from the mother.

GENEPIO:0001610.label: subject age
GENEPIO:0001610.definition: A subject age is the age since birth of a given organism that is involved in an investigation or study at a given time.

OBI:0001528.label: material service
OBI:0001528.definition: A service which has a material entity as specified input and/or specified output.

APOLLO_SV:00000240.label: census reference date
APOLLO_SV:00000240.definition: A information content entity that specifies the date of a census.

OBI:0001557.label: material storage service
OBI:0001557.definition: A storage service in which a service consumer provides some material as input which a service provider stores and returns as output.

OBI:0001547.label: material analysis service
OBI:0001547.definition: A service in which a service consumer provides some input material and a service provider performs some analysis of this material to generate data that is returned to the service consumer.

OBI:0001515.label: material maintenance service
OBI:0001515.definition: A material processing service in which a service provider makes physical modifications to a specified input material, such that at least one of the specified outputs of this process is a modified version of a specified input material.

GENEPIO:0001722.label: NCBI specimen voucher
GENEPIO:0001722.definition: The NCBI specimen voucher is an identifier composed of “institution code:collection code:specimen id” parts. In addition to a specimen identifier, it includes an institution-code (and optional collection-code) taken from a controlled vocabulary maintained by the INSDC that denotes the museum or herbarium collection where the specimen resides.

OBI:0001901.label: specimen identifier assigned by sequencing facility
OBI:0001901.definition: A specimen identifier which is assigned by a sequencing facility

OBI:0001900.label: specimen identifier assigned by specimen repository
OBI:0001900.definition: A specimen identifier which is assigned by a specimen repository

GENEPIO:0001781.label: National Laboratory for Enteric Pathogens Identifier
GENEPIO:0001781.definition: An NLEP ID is a unique identifier code for a sample registered with the Canadian "National Laboratory for Enteric Pathogens" (NLEP)

GENEPIO:0001747.label: reagent derived material from specimen
GENEPIO:0001747.definition: Reagent: material studied was obtained by chemical reaction, precipitation.

GENEPIO:0001749.label: proteome data derived from specimen
GENEPIO:0001749.definition: Proteome material is protein or peptide sequences.

GENEPIO:0001750.label: purified chromosome from specimen
GENEPIO:0001750.definition: Purified chromosome: one or more chromosomes or replicons were experimentally purified.

GENEPIO:0000012.label: other material derived from specimen
GENEPIO:0000012.definition: Other: specify the material that was used.

GENEPIO:0001586.label: synthetic sample scope
GENEPIO:0001586.definition: A synthetic sample scope involves a sample synthesized in a laboratory.

GENEPIO:0001585.label: environment sample scope
GENEPIO:0001585.definition: An environment sample scope indicates that the species content of the sample is not known. Generally, nucleic acid is directly isolated from an environmental sample for analysis. This is used for metagenome studies.

GENEPIO:0001582.label: monoisolate sample scope
GENEPIO:0001582.definition: A monoisolate sample scope involves specimens from a single animal, cultured cell-line, inbred population, or possibly a heterogeneous population when a single genome assembly is generated from a pooled sample because multiple individuals are needed to collect enough material and an inbred line is not available; however, this situation is not preferred.

GENEPIO:0001583.label: multiisolate sample scope
GENEPIO:0001583.definition: A multiisolate sample scope contains multiple individuals that represent distinct specimen collections, a population (representative of a species).

GENEPIO:0001584.label: multispecies sample scope
GENEPIO:0001584.definition: A multi-species sample scope involves a sample representing multiple species.

GENEPIO:0000011.label: other specimen scope
GENEPIO:0000011.definition: Other: specify the sample scope that was used.

GENEPIO:0001594.label: analysis objective
GENEPIO:0001594.definition: An "analysis project objective" indicates there was an other analysis not otherwise indicated, includes submission of BAM files.

GENEPIO:0001598.label: epigenetic markers objective
GENEPIO:0001598.definition: DNA methylation, histone modification, chromatin accessibility datasets

GENEPIO:0001599.label: transcript or protein expression objective
GENEPIO:0001599.definition: Expression: assays of transcript or protein existence or abundance

GENEPIO:0001600.label: mapping objective
GENEPIO:0001600.definition: Maps: non-sequence based map data; e.g., genetic, radiation hybrid, cytogenetic, etc.

GENEPIO:0001588.label: other project objective
GENEPIO:0001588.definition: Other project objective: specify an objective not listed above

GENEPIO:0001114.label: phenotype project objective
GENEPIO:0001114.definition: Phenotype: phenotypic measurements for submission to dbGaP

GENEPIO:0001592.label: raw sequence read objective
GENEPIO:0001592.definition: A raw sequence reads project objective has the goal of submission of raw reads to SRA or Trace repositories

GENEPIO:0001593.label: sequence project objective
GENEPIO:0001593.definition: A sequence project objective has a goal of submission of sequence data to standard archival sequence databases (yielding accession.version identifiers; e.g., whole genome shotgun, cDNA sequences, transcript shotgun assemblies)

GENEPIO:0001597.label: sequence variation project objective
GENEPIO:0001597.definition: Variation: identification of sequence variation data for submission to dbSNP or dbVAR

GENEPIO:0001603.label: array project method
GENEPIO:0001603.definition: select Array if that is the primary method and no sequence data is submitted

GENEPIO:0001604.label: mass spectrometry project method
GENEPIO:0001604.definition: select Mass Spectrometry if that is the primary method

GENEPIO:0000013.label: other capture type
GENEPIO:0000013.definition: "other capture type" is a free text description provided to indicate a target capture specification not covered by the other types.

GENEPIO:0001754.label: random survey data capture
GENEPIO:0001754.definition: sequences generated from a random sampling of the collected sample; not intended to be comprehensive sampling of the material

GENEPIO:0001751.label: Targeted Locus Loci data capture
GENEPIO:0001751.definition: TargetedLocusLoci: capturing specific loci (gene, genomic region, bar code standard).

GENEPIO:0001591.label: whole genomic data capture
GENEPIO:0001591.definition: Whole: the project makes use of the whole sample material (most common case). Use this for whole genome sequencing studies, transcriptome studies that are not targeting specific loci, epigenetic studies of a genome, and metagenomes or unbiased transcriptome studies of metagenomes.

OBI:0000992.label: DNA sequencing service
OBI:0000992.definition: A DNA sequencing  process provided as a service - which is the realization of some DNA sequencing in which the service provider role is realized.

GENEPIO:0002161.label: region, province, state or territory specification

GENEPIO:0002162.label: specimen extraction site specification
GENEPIO:0002162.definition: A specification for a geographic location that a specimen was extracted or collected at.

GENEPIO:0001640.label: specimen organism taxonomy (species)
GENEPIO:0001640.definition: This is the taxonomic species descriptor of a specimen isolate (an organism found within a specimen.)

GENEPIO:0002165.label: subject disease specification
GENEPIO:0002165.definition: Name of disease in a subject that is related to a given investigation, study and/or specimen.

GENEPIO:0001567.label: subject organism (host) taxonomic species
GENEPIO:0001567.definition: The species of the host organism from which a specimen (pathogen) organism was obtained. Use the full taxonomic name, eg, "Homo sapiens".

GENEPIO:0000031.label: subject sex specification
GENEPIO:0000031.definition: A subject sex is the phenotypic sex of given subject (human or animal) related to a given investigation, study, and/or specimen.

GENEPIO:0002173.label: travel destination specification
GENEPIO:0002173.definition: A travel destination is a destination city (or populated place of some scale) which a given human has travelled to on a particular trip.

GENEPIO:0002150.label: MIC diffusion measurement specification
GENEPIO:0002150.definition: A MIC test measurement resulting from a laboratory diffusion method.

GENEPIO:0002153.label: MIC dilution measurement specification
GENEPIO:0002153.definition: A MIC test measurement resulting from a laboratory dilution method.

GENEPIO:0001862.label: latitude specification (ISO 6709)
GENEPIO:0001862.definition: A decimal latitude measurement in degrees in conformance with the ISO 6709 standard.

GENEPIO:0001863.label: longitude specification (ISO 6709)
GENEPIO:0001863.definition: A decimal longitude measurement in degrees in conformance with the ISO 6709 standard.

GENEPIO:0002158.label: boolean value specification
GENEPIO:0002158.definition: A boolean value specification indicates a presence (true value) or absence (false value) of a given feature.

OBI:0001930.label: categorical value specification
OBI:0001930.definition: A value specification that is specifies one category out of a fixed number of nominal categories

OBI:0001931.label: scalar value specification
OBI:0001931.definition: A value specification that consists of two parts: a numeral and a unit label

OBI:0001891.label: sequencing facility organization
OBI:0001891.definition: An organization that provides sequence determination service

OBI:0002565.label: adapter-sequence trimming
OBI:0002565.definition: A data transformation in which adapter sequences at the end of a molecular sequence are cut (removed).

NCBITaxon:2157.label: Archaea
NCBITaxon:2157.definition: The Archaea constitute a domain and kingdom of single-celled microorganisms

IDO:0000659.label: susceptible organism
IDO:0000659.definition: An organism that is not infected with an infectious agent and lacks protective immunity to the infectious agent.

IDO:0000531.label: host
IDO:0000531.definition: An organism bearing a host role.

OBI:0000925.label: infectious agent
OBI:0000925.definition: is a material entity bearing the disposition to infect an organism

IDO:0000540.label: infectious agent vector
IDO:0000540.definition: An organism bearing an infectious agent vector role.

NCIT:C53471.label: Isolate
NCIT:C53471.definition: A specific individual microbe and its genetically identical progeny separated on a single occasion from a sample taken from a host or culture system.

GENEPIO:0002749.label: rinse
GENEPIO:0002749.definition: Rinse is the liquid output of rinsing plant, animal or other material with liquid with the objective of extracting specimen material from that liquid.

OBI:0001479.label: specimen from organism
OBI:0001479.definition: A specimen that derives from an anatomical part or substance arising from an organism. Examples of tissue specimen include tissue, organ, physiological system, blood, or body location (arm).

OBI:0002585.label: sequence trimming
OBI:0002585.definition: A data transformation in which subsequences of a molecular sequence are cut (removed).

OBI:0666667.label: nucleic acid extraction
OBI:0666667.definition: a material separation to recover the nucleic acid fraction of an input material

OBI:0000691.label: ABI 377 automated sequencer
OBI:0000691.definition: is a DNA sequencer which is manufactured by Applied Biosystems corporation (formerly Perkin-Elmer). It allows automated chain termination DNA sequencing. It has part polyacrylamide gel electrophoresis system and a laser -based detection system to detect fluorescence intensity emitted by the dyes attached to the dideoxyterminator nucleotides or to the primers.

OBI:0000710.label: Li-Cor 4300 DNA Analysis System
OBI:0000710.definition: is a DNA sequencer which is manufactured by Li-Cor corporation and enable automated chain termination based DNA sequencing

OBI:0002128.label: Illumina Genome Analyzer
OBI:0002128.definition: A DNA sequencer manufactured by Solexa as one of its first sequencer lines, launched in 2006, and capable of sequencing 1 gigabase (Gb) of data in a single run.

OBI:0002129.label: Illumina HiSeq X Ten
OBI:0002129.definition: A DNA sequencer that consists of a set of 10 HiSeq X Sequencing Systems.

NCIT:C52009.label: Amniocentesis
NCIT:C52009.definition: A prenatal diagnostic procedure in which a small sample of amniotic fluid is removed from the uterus by a needle inserted into the abdomen. This procedure is used to detect various genetic abnormalities in the fetus and/or the sex of the fetus.

NCIT:C15631.label: Aspiration
NCIT:C15631.definition: Procedure using suction, usually with a thin needle and syringe, to remove bodily fluid or tissue.

NCIT:C15189.label: Biopsy
NCIT:C15189.definition: The removal of tissue specimens or fluid from the living body for microscopic examination, performed to establish a diagnosis.

NCIT:C28221.label: Phlebotomy
NCIT:C28221.definition: The collection of blood from a vein, most commonly via needle venipuncture.

GENEPIO:0002118.label: exudate collection
GENEPIO:0002118.definition: The process of collecting bodily fluids that have been discharged from blood vessels usually arising from inflammation or injury.

GENEPIO:0002114.label: feces collection
GENEPIO:0002114.definition: The process of collecting a portion of feces from an organism.

OBI:0600044.label: lavage
OBI:0600044.definition: A protocol application to separate cells and/or cellular secretions from an anatomical space by the introduction and removal of fluid

GENEPIO:0002116.label: rinsing for specimen collection
GENEPIO:0002116.definition: The process of removal and collection of specimen material from the surface of an entity by washing, or a similar application of fluids.

GENEPIO:0002115.label: sputum collection
GENEPIO:0002115.definition: The process of collecting a portion of urine from an organism.

GENEPIO:0002117.label: swabbing for specimen collection
GENEPIO:0002117.definition: The process of collecting specimen material using a swab collection device.

GENEPIO:0002119.label: vacuuming for specimen collection
GENEPIO:0002119.definition: The removal or collection of specimen material through the use of suction.

MMO:0000344.label: necropsy
MMO:0000344.definition: A postmortem examination of the body of an animal to determine the cause of death or the character and extent of changes produced by disease. [database_cross_reference: Merriam-Webster:Merriam-Websters_Online_Dictionary--11th_Ed]

OBI:0302884.label: extraction
OBI:0302884.definition: A material separation in which a desired component of an input material is separated from the remainder

BTO:0000155.label: bronchoalveolar lavage (BAL)
BTO:0000155.definition: A technique by which cells and fluid from bronchioles and lung alveoli are removed for diagnosis of disease or evaluation of treatment. A bronchoscope is wedged into a bronchus and sterile saline is pumped in and then removed along with the fluid and cells to be analyzed.

OBI:0001177.label: RNA sequencing assay
OBI:0001177.definition: An assay that determines the sequence of an RNA molecule.

OBI:0000257.label: DNA extraction
OBI:0000257.definition: A DNA extraction is a nucleic acid extraction where the desired output material is DNA.

OBI:1110049.label: allergy
OBI:1110049.definition: is a disease in which an abnormally strong inflammatory immune response is triggered against non-self entities, and the immune response has no protective effect

OBI:1110040.label: infectious disease
OBI:1110040.definition: is a disease caused by an infectious agent

IDO:0000495.label: infectious disease course
IDO:0000495.definition: A disease course that is the realization of an infectious disease.

OMIABIS:0001008.label: comorbidity
OMIABIS:0001008.definition: A diagnosis that is the outcome of a diagnostic process targeting a second or additional health problem.

OMIT:0017096.label: Critical Illness
OMIT:0017096.definition: Vital signs are unstable and not within normal limits. Patient may be unconscious. Indicators are unfavorable.

NCIT:C45910.label: Pooled Sample
NCIT:C45910.definition: A mix of specimens from multiple individuals representing multiple sex groups.

PATO:0001894.label: phenotypic sex
PATO:0001894.definition: Phenotypic sex refers to an individual's sex as determined by their internal and external genitalia, expression of secondary sex characteristics, and behavior.

PATO:0000117.label: size
PATO:0000117.definition: A morphology quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's physical magnitude.

PATO:0000070.label: amount
PATO:0000070.definition: The number of entities of this type that are part of the whole organism.

PATO:0000069.label: deviation(from_normal)
PATO:0000069.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the whether the bearer differs from normal or average.

PATO:0000460.label: abnormal
PATO:0000460.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's deviation from normal or average.

PATO:0002301.label: decreased quality
PATO:0002301.definition: A quality that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

PATO:0000462.label: absent
PATO:0000462.definition: A quality denoting the lack of an entity.

PATO:0000467.label: present
PATO:0000467.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's existence.

PATO:0001708.label: 1-D extent
PATO:0001708.definition: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in one dimension.

PATO:0001709.label: 2-D extent
PATO:0001709.definition: A size quality inhering in an bearer by virtue of the bearer's extension in two dimensions.

NCIT:C54014.label: Castrated Female
NCIT:C54014.definition: A female individual who has had her ovaries removed.

PATO:0002365.label: intact female
PATO:0002365.definition: Female quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs

PATO:0002367.label: castrated male
PATO:0002367.definition: Male quality of being incapable to reproduce because of functional loss of the testicles from surgical removal or chemical means.

PATO:0002366.label: intact male
PATO:0002366.definition: Male quality of having complete, unaltered reproductive organs.

PATO:0001869.label: pathological
PATO:0001869.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being abnormal and having a destructive effect on living tissue.

PATO:0001585.label: conductivity
PATO:0001585.definition: A physical quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's disposition to transmit of an entity through a medium.

PATO:0001019.label: mass density
PATO:0001019.definition: A physical quality which inheres in a bearer by virtue of some influence is exerted by the bearer's mass per unit size.

PATO:0001470.label: proportionality to
PATO:0001470.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's magnitude in respect to a related entity.

PATO:0001230.label: strength
PATO:0001230.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's power or force.

PATO:0000146.label: temperature
PATO:0000146.definition: A physical quality of the thermal energy of a system.

PATO:0001779.label: decreased strength
PATO:0001779.definition: A strength which is relatively low.

PATO:0002303.label: decreased object quality
PATO:0002303.definition: A quality of an object that has a value that is decreased compared to normal or average.

PATO:0002182.label: molecular quality
PATO:0002182.definition: A quality which inheres in a molecular entity, a single molecule, atom, ion, radical etc.

PATO:0000051.label: morphology
PATO:0000051.definition: A quality of a single physical entity inhering in the bearer by virtue of the bearer's size or shape or structure.

PATO:0001995.label: organismal quality
PATO:0001995.definition: A quality that inheres in an entire organism or part of an organism.

PATO:0001018.label: physical quality
PATO:0001018.definition: A quality of a physical entity that exists through action of continuants at the physical level of organisation in relation to other entities.

PATO:0001986.label: dissolved
PATO:0001986.definition: A quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's passing into solution.

PATO:0001537.label: soluble in
PATO:0001537.definition: A solubility quality inhering in a substance by virtue of the bearer's disposition to dissolve in a liquid.

PATO:0001595.label: depth
PATO:0001595.definition: A 1-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's downward or backward or inward dimenision.

PATO:0000122.label: length
PATO:0000122.definition: A 1-D extent quality which is equal to the distance between two points.

PATO:0001323.label: area
PATO:0001323.definition: A 2-D extent quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's two dimensional extent.

PATO:0001829.label: female pseudohermaphrodite
PATO:0001829.definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of female and external sexual characteristics of male.

PATO:0001828.label: male pseudohermaphrodite
PATO:0001828.definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of male and external sexual characteristics of female.

NCIT:C45908.label: Intersex
NCIT:C45908.definition: A person (one of unisexual specimens) who is born with genitalia and/or secondary sexual characteristics of indeterminate sex, or which combine features of both sexes.

PATO:0000383.label: female
PATO:0000383.definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population that only produces gametes that can be fertilised by male gametes.

PATO:0001340.label: hermaphrodite
PATO:0001340.definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an organism or a population with both male and female sexual organs in one individual.

PATO:0000384.label: male
PATO:0000384.definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population whose sex organs contain only male gametes.

PATO:0001827.label: pseudohermaphrodite
PATO:0001827.definition: A biological sex quality inhering in an individual or a population by virtue of having internal reproductive organs of one sex and external sexual characteristics of the other sex.

GENEPIO:0001660.label: neuter
GENEPIO:0001660.definition: An animal that has had a substantial part of its reproductive organs removed surgically.

GENEPIO:0001661.label: pooled male and female
GENEPIO:0001661.definition: 'pooled male and female' is a categorical value used when the male and female categories or levels of a factor are combined. If used to describe a single organism, then the organism will be one or the other.

PATO:0000047.label: biological sex
PATO:0000047.definition: An organismal quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ability to undergo sexual reproduction in order to differentiate the individuals or types involved.

PATO:0001536.label: solubility
PATO:0001536.definition: A molecular quality that inheres in a molecular entity by virtue of the bearer's disposition to dissolve in a liquid.

PCO:0000018.label: single-species collection of organisms
PCO:0000018.definition: A material entity that has as parts two or more organisms, viruses, or viroids of the same species and no members of any other species.

NCIT:C17734.label: At-Risk Population
NCIT:C17734.definition: Population groups with an increased likelihood of a disease or other health issue, eg smoking, drug use, teen pregnancy.

APOLLO_SV:00000516.label: host population
IAO:0000118: A population of organisms some of which were susceptible to infection with a particular pathogen at some point in their lives.

PCO:0000001.label: population of organisms
PCO:0000001.definition: A collection of organisms, all of the same species, that live in the same place.

PCO:0000039.label: baby shower
PCO:0000039.definition: A human social gathering at which the key participant is an expectant parent and other guests bring presents for the soon to be born baby.

PCO:0000034.label: human community event
PCO:0000034.definition: A human social event in which humans living in the same area or neighborhood gather to carry out activiites relevent to the people living in the area.

PCO:0000035.label: party
PCO:0000035.definition: A human social gathering in which the intention is to have a good time. Often the intention is to celebrate something like a birthday, anniversary, or holiday, but there is not always a purpose.

PCO:0000038.label: wedding
PCO:0000038.definition: A human social gathering at which two people are married. May include a legal or social ceremony.

PO:0030107.label: achene fruit
PO:0030107.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) or gyneocium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), a dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and a dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that are connected to a seed coat (PO:0009088) by a funicle (PO:0020006).

PO:0030108.label: berry fruit
PO:0030108.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which at maturity comprises a fleshy endocarp (PO:0009086), fleshy mesocarp (PO:0009087), and fleshy exocarp (PO:0009085).

PO:0030091.label: capsule fruit
PO:0030091.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that usually dehisce.

PO:0030104.label: caryopsis fruit
PO:0030104.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that are fused to a seed coat (PO:0009088).

PO:0030103.label: drupe fruit
PO:0030103.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a fleshy exocarp (PO:0009085), fleshy mesocarp (PO:0009087), and a stony endocarp (PO:0009086).

PO:0030105.label: follicle fruit
PO:0030105.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that dehisce along a single fruit valve (PO:0000033).

PO:0030100.label: legume fruit
PO:0030100.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that dehisce along two fruit valves (PO:0000033).

PO:0030102.label: nut fruit
PO:0030102.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that are not fused to a seed coat (PO:0009088).

PO:0030099.label: samara fruit
PO:0030099.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that are elongated into a wing-like structure.

PO:0030098.label: schizocarp fruit
PO:0030098.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086) that separate into mericarps (PO:0020075).

PO:0030106.label: silique fruit
PO:0030106.definition: A fruit (PO:0009001) which develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a dry exocarp (PO:0009085), dry mesocarp (PO:0009087), and dry endocarp (PO:0009086), that dehisce along two fruit valves (PO:0000033) and separate from a persistent fruit replum (PO:0025267).

PO:0025496.label: multi-tissue plant structure
PO:0025496.definition: A plant structure (PO:0009011) that has as parts two or more portions of plant tissue (PO:0009007) of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single structural unit demarcated by primarily bona-fide boundaries from other structural units of different types.

PO:0009001.label: fruit
PO:0009001.definition: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that develops from a gynoecium (PO:0009062), or a single carpel (PO:0009030), and at maturity may have as parts one or more seeds (PO:0009010).

PO:0009010.label: seed
PO:0009010.definition: A multi-tissue plant structure (PO:0025496) that develops from a plant ovule (PO:0020003) and has as parts a plant embryo (PO:0009009) enclosed in a seed coat (PO:0009088).

PO:0030096.label: circumscissile capsule fruit
PO:0030096.definition: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through the release of a fruit operculum (PO:0025298).

PO:0030094.label: coccarium capsule fruit
PO:0030094.definition: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through both the fruit septa (PO:0025268) and the fruit locules (PO:0025270).

PO:0030092.label: loculicidal capsule fruit
PO:0030092.definition: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through fruit locules (PO:0025270).

PO:0030095.label: poricidal capsule fruit
PO:0030095.definition: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which at maturity dehisces through pores on a pericarp (PO:0009084).

PO:0030093.label: septicidal capsule fruit
PO:0030093.definition: A capsule fruit (PO:0030091) which dehisces through a fruit septa (PO:0025268).

PO:0030097.label: utricle capsule fruit
PO:0030097.definition: A circumscissile capsule fruit (PO:0030096) which at maturity contains one seed (PO:0009010) that is not attached to a pericarp (PO:0009084).

PO:0030101.label: loment fruit
PO:0030101.definition: A legume fruit (PO:0030100) which at maturity separates into indehiscent, one-seeded segments.

PO:0030109.label: hesperidium fruit
PO:0030109.definition: A berry fruit (PO:0030108) which develops from a superior gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a thickened exocarp (PO:0009085), thickened mesocarp (PO:0009087), and endocarp (PO:0009086), and has as parts juice sacs (PO:0006013) on a carpel adaxial epidermis (PO:0025618).

PO:0030111.label: pepo fruit
PO:0030111.definition: A berry fruit (PO:0030108) which develops from an inferior carpel (PO:0009030) and at maturity comprises a fleshy exocarp (PO:0009085), fleshy mesocarp (PO:0009087), and fleshy endocarp (PO:0009086), and has as a part a hard receptacle (PO:0009064) which surrounds, and is indistinct from, the exocarp (PO:0009085).

PO:0030110.label: pome fruit
PO:0030110.definition: A berry fruit (PO:0030108) which develops from an inferior gynoecium (PO:0009062) and at maturity comprises a fleshy exocarp (PO:0009085), fleshy mesocarp (PO:0009087), and hardened endocarp (PO:0009086) and has as a part a fleshy hypanthium (PO:0009065) which is indistinct from the exocarp (PO:0009085).

OBI:0000732.label: restriction enzyme
OBI:0000732.definition: an enzyme that has a specific target cleavage sites within nucleic acids

ENVO:01000254.label: environmental system
ENVO:01000254.definition: A system which has the disposition to environ one or more material entities.

GENEPIO:0001865.label: 2D coordinate system
GENEPIO:0001865.definition: A 2D coordinate system is a coordinate system in 2 dimensional space.  Each coordinate is composed of an offset from the origin of each dimension

STATO:0000009.label: cartesian coordinate system
STATO:0000009.definition: A Cartesian coordinate system is a coordinate system that specifies each point uniquely in a plane by a pair of numerical coordinates, which are the signed distances from the point to two fixed perpendicular directed lines, measured in the same unit of length.

STATO:0000197.label: genomic coordinate system
STATO:0000197.definition: a genomic coordinate system is a coordinate system to describe position of sequence on a genomic scaffold (assembly of chromosome, contig....)

STATO:0000014.label: spherical coordinate system
STATO:0000014.definition: In mathematics, a spherical coordinate system is a coordinate system for three-dimensional space where the position of a point is specified by three numbers: the radial distance of that point from a fixed origin, its polar angle measured from a fixed zenith direction, and the azimuth angle of its orthogonal projection on a reference plane that passes through the origin and is orthogonal to the zenith, measured from a fixed reference direction on that plane.

APOLLO_SV:00000498.label: count of cases in an epidemic
APOLLO_SV:00000498.definition: A count of disease cases in an infected population that meet the case definition criteria within a particular epidemic interval.

APOLLO_SV:00000098.label: count of contagious population
APOLLO_SV:00000098.definition: The count of individuals in a contagious population (empirical or virtual).

APOLLO_SV:00000099.label: count of resistant population
APOLLO_SV:00000099.definition: The count of individuals in a resistant population (empirical or virtual).

APOLLO_SV:00000022.label: count of simulated population
APOLLO_SV:00000022.definition: The count of (simulated organisms) in a simulated population.

GENEPIO:0001442.label: exposure group healthy count
GENEPIO:0001442.definition: The count of healthy individuals or animals on a certain date/time from a group that was likely exposed to a pathogen

GENEPIO:0001443.label: exposure group ill count
GENEPIO:0001443.definition: The count of ill individuals or animals on a certain date/time from a group that was likely exposed to a pathogen

GENEPIO:0001536.label: exposure group unknown health status count
GENEPIO:0001536.definition: The count of individuals or animals for which no health status is available on a certain date/time from a group that was likely exposed to a pathogen.

STATO:0000232.label: number of PCR cycle
STATO:0000232.definition: number of PCR cycle is a count which enumerates how many iterations of 'annealing, renaturation, amplification,' rounds (or cycles) are performed during a polymerase chain reaction (PCR) or an assay relying on PCR.

STATO:0000069.label: number of degrees of freedom
STATO:0000069.definition: The number degree of freedom is a count evaluating the number of values in a calculation that can vary. In statistics, the number of degrees of freedom ν is equal to N-1 in the case of the direct measurement of a quantity estimated by the arithmetic mean of N independent observations.

APOLLO_SV:00000281.label: number of doses in a treatment course
APOLLO_SV:00000281.definition: The count of the number of doses that are part of a treatment course.

STATO:0000064.label: sequence read count
STATO:0000064.definition: sequence read count is a data item determining how many sequence reads generated by a DNA sequencing assay for a given stretch of DNA can counted

GENEPIO:0001879.label: significant digits
GENEPIO:0001879.definition: Wikipedia: "The significant figures of a number are digits that carry meaning contributing to its measurement resolution."

STATO:0000090.label: dichotomous variable
STATO:0000090.definition: a dichotomous variable  is a categorical variable  which is defined to have only 2 categories or possible values

STATO:0000210.label: channel1/channel2 fluorescence intensity ratio
STATO:0000210.definition: is a data item formed by dividing the fluorescence intensity obtained in one channel to that obtained in the other channel, typically the case when considering 2-color microarray data when imaging is done for Cy3 and Cy5 dyes.

STATO:0000254.label: allele frequency
STATO:0000254.definition: The allele frequency is a data item which denotes the incidence of a gene variant in a population. It is calculated as a ratio, by dividing the number of copies of a particular allele by the number of copies of all alleles at the genetic place (locus) in a population.

STATO:0000300.label: dimensionless ratio
STATO:0000300.definition: A ratio where the numerator and denominator are expressed in the same unit.

OBI:0000789.label: survival rate
