OBI:0000789.definition: A measurement data that represents the percentage of people or animals in a study or treatment group who are alive for a given period of time after diagnosis or initiation of monitoring.

STATO:0000071.label: reaction rate
STATO:0000071.definition: reaction rate is a measurement datum which represents the speed of a chemical reaction turning reactive species into product species of event (i.e the number of such conversions)s occuring over a time interval

STATO:0000050.label: signal to noise ratio
STATO:0000050.definition: signal to noise ratio is a measurement datum comparing the amount of meaningful, useful or interesting data (the signal) to the amount of irrelevant or false data (the noise). Depending on the field and domain of application, different variables will be used to determinate a 'signal to noise ratio'. In statistics, the definition of signal to noise ratio is the ratio of the mean of a measurement to its standard deviation. It thus corresponds to the inverse of the coefficient of variation

STATO:0000134.label: true negative rate
STATO:0000134.definition: specificity is a measurement datum qualifying a binary classification test and is computed by substracting the false positive rate to the integral numeral 1

STATO:0000233.label: true positive rate
STATO:0000233.definition: sensitivity is a measurement datum qualifying a binary classification test and is computed by substracting the false negative rate to the integral numeral 1

STATO:0000055.label: chromosome coordinate system
STATO:0000055.definition: chromosome coordinate system is a genomic coordinate which uses chromosome of a particular assembly build process to define start and end positions. This coordinate system is unstable and will change with each new genome sequence assembly build.

STATO:0000190.label: threshold cycle
STATO:0000190.definition: Threshold cycle (or Ct or Cq) is a count which is defined as the fractional PCR cycle number at which the reporter fluorescence is greater than the threshold in the context of the RT-qPCR assay. The Ct is a basic principle of real time PCR and is an essential component in producing accurate and reproducible data.

STATO:0000228.label: ordinal variable
STATO:0000228.definition: ordinal variable is a categorical variable where  the discrete possible values are ordered or  correspond to an implicit ranking

STATO:0000087.label: polychotomous variable
STATO:0000087.definition: a polychotomous variable  is a categorical variable  which is defined to have minimally 2 categories or possible values

STATO:0000252.label: categorical variable
STATO:0000252.definition: a categorical variable  is a variable  which that can only assume a finite number  of value and cast observation in a small number of categories

STATO:0000251.label: continuous variable
STATO:0000251.definition: A continuous variable is one for which, within the limits the variable ranges, any value is possible.

STATO:0000221.label: random variable
STATO:0000221.definition: a random variable (or aleatory variable or stochastic variable) in probability and statistics,  is a variable whose value is subject to variations due to chance (i.e. randomness, in a mathematical sense)

STATO:0000182.label: odds ratio
STATO:0000182.definition:
Odds ratio is a ratio that measures effect size, that is the strength of association between 2 dichotomous variables, one describing an exposure and one describing an outcome.
It represents the odds that an outcome will occur given a particular exposure, compared to the odds of the outcome occurring in the absence of that exposure ( the probability of the event occuring divided by the probability of an event not occurring). The odds ratio is a ratio of describing the strength of association or non-independence between two binary data values by forming the ratio of the odds for the first group and the odds for the second group. Odds ratio are used when one wants to compare the odds of something occurring to two different groups.

STATO:0000220.label: false negative rate
STATO:0000220.definition: the false negative rate is a data item which denotes the proportion of missed detection of elements known to be meeting the detection criteria

STATO:0000053.label: false positive rate
STATO:0000053.definition: a false positive rate is a data item which accounts for the proportion of incorrect rejection of a true null hypothesis.

STATO:0000169.label: fold change
STATO:0000169.definition: Fold change is a number describing how much a quantity changes going from an initial to a final value or one condition to another condition

TRANS:0000001.label: direct transmission
TRANS:0000001.definition: Direct and essentially immediate transfer of infectious agents to a receptive portal of entry through which human or animal infection may take place. This may be by direct contact such as touching, kissing, biting, or sexual intercourse or by the direct projection (droplet spread) of droplet spray onto the conjunctiva or the mucous membranes of the eyes, nose, or mouth. It may also be by direct exposure of susceptible tissue to an agent in soil, compost, or decaying vegetable matter or by the bite of a rabid animal. Transplacental transmission is another form of direct transmission.

TRANS:0000002.label: indirect transmission
TRANS:0000002.definition: Indirect transmission is a transmission process during which the pathogen is indirectly transferred from a reservoir, source or host to another host by intermediary vehicles, vectors or as airborne dust particles.

TRANS:0000006.label: congenital
TRANS:0000006.definition: Congenital transmission is a direct transmission process during which the pathogen is transmitted directly from mother to child at or around the time of birth.

TRANS:0000007.label: contact
TRANS:0000007.definition: Contact transmission is a direct transmission process during which the pathogen is transmitted from a reservoir, source or host to another host by kissing, skin-to-skin contact, sexual intercourse, or by contact with soil or vegetation containing the pathogen.

TRANS:0000008.label: droplet spread
TRANS:0000008.definition: Droplet spread transmission is a direct transmission process during which the pathogen is transmitted from a reservoir, source or host to another host by spray of aerosols over a short distance, spray from sneezing, coughing or talking.

EPO:0000016.label: common vehicle transmission
EPO:0000016.definition: Transmission of a disease agent (infectious pathogen, toxic chemical, etc.) from a source that is common to those who acquire the disease. Common vehicles include air, water, food, injected substances. Legionellosis is an example of common vehicle spread in air that has passed through air conditioning equipment contaminated by the causal organism. HIV disease and hepatitis B and C can be spread among illicit drug users by the common vehicle of contaminated needles and syringes. Cholera and many other waterborne diseases are spread by the common vehicle of contaminated water.

TRANS:0000012.label: vehicle-born ingestion
TRANS:0000012.definition: Vehicle-borne ingestion transmission is an indirect vehicle-borne transmission process during which the pathogen is indirectly transferred from a reservoir, source or host to another host by ingestion of fluids or foods or food products including: food, water, milk, or meat products.

UBERON:0000105.label: life cycle stage
UBERON:0000105.definition: A spatiotemporal region encompassing some part of the life cycle of an organism.

UBERON:0000022.label: feather
UBERON:0000022.definition: one of the epidermal growths that form the distinctive outer covering, or plumage, on birds. Feathers are formed in tiny follicles in the epidermis, or outer skin layer, that produce keratin proteins.

UBERON:0003914.label: epithelial tube
UBERON:0003914.definition: Epithelial tubes transport gases, liquids and cells from one site to another and form the basic structure of many organs and tissues, with tube shape and organization varying from the single-celled excretory organ in Caenorhabditis elegans to the branching trees of the mammalian kidney and insect tracheal system.

UBERON:0000117.label: respiratory tube
UBERON:0000117.definition: A tube in the respiratory system. Examples: bronchus, bronchiole, trachea.

UBERON:0002507.label: abdominal lymph node
UBERON:0002507.definition: A lymph node that is part of an abdomen [Automatically generated definition].

UBERON:0002525.label: brachial lymph node
UBERON:0002525.definition: The lymph nodes located along the brachial vein that receive drainage from most of the free upper limb and send efferent vessels to the central axillary lymph nodes.

UBERON:0016481.label: bronchial lymph node
UBERON:0016481.definition: A lymph node that is part of a bronchus.

UBERON:0002429.label: cervical lymph node
UBERON:0002429.definition: Cervical lymph nodes are lymph nodes found in the neck. [WP,unvetted].

UBERON:0015918.label: deep lymph node
UBERON:0015918.definition: A lymph node that is located deeper within the organism, further from the surface.

UBERON:0016378.label: ileocolic lymph node
UBERON:0016378.definition: One of the lymph nodes that form a chain around the ileocolic artery.

UBERON:0015870.label: lymph node of head
UBERON:0015870.definition: A lymph node that is part of a head.

UBERON:0016398.label: lymph node of lower limb
UBERON:0016398.definition: A lymph node that is part of a hindlimb.

UBERON:0016399.label: lymph node of upper limb
UBERON:0016399.definition: A lymph node that is part of a forelimb.

UBERON:0016386.label: paraaortic lymph node
UBERON:0016386.definition: The paraaortic lymph nodes (also known as para-aortic, periaortic, and peri-aortic) are a group of lymph nodes that lie in front of the lumbar vertebral bodies near the aorta. These lymph nodes receive drainage from the lower gastrointestinal tract and the pelvic organs.

UBERON:0015876.label: pelvic lymph node
UBERON:0015876.definition: Any lymph node within the abdominal pelvic region.

UBERON:0003968.label: peripheral lymph node
UBERON:0003968.definition: The lymph nodes located outside the thoracic and abdominal cavities, such as the submandibular, prescapular, axillary, inguinal and popliteal lymph nodes

UBERON:0003425.label: renal lymph node
UBERON:0003425.definition: A lymph node that is located in a kidney [Automatically generated definition].

UBERON:0035371.label: retroperitoneal lymph node
UBERON:0035371.definition: A lymph node located in the retroperitoneal space.

UBERON:0002528.label: sacral lymph node
UBERON:0002528.definition: A lymph node located in the sacral region.

UBERON:0015469.label: splenic lymph node
UBERON:0015469.definition: The splenic lymph nodes (or pancreaticolienal) accompany the lienal (splenic) artery, and are situated in relation to the posterior surface and upper border of the pancreas; one or two members of this group are found in the gastrolienal ligament. Their afferents are derived from the stomach, spleen, and pancreas, their efferents join the celiac group of preaortic glands.

UBERON:0015453.label: subcutaneous lymph node
UBERON:0015453.definition: A lymph node that is part of a hypodermis.

UBERON:0015917.label: superficial lymph node
UBERON:0015917.definition: A lymph node that is located close to the surface.

UBERON:0007644.label: thoracic lymph node
UBERON:0007644.definition: A lymph node that is part of a thorax. Includes lymph nodes of the lungs and mediastinal lymph nodes

UBERON:0015472.label: tracheobronchial lymph node
UBERON:0015472.definition: A lymph node located near the bifurcation of the trachea.

UBERON:0000476.label: acellular anatomical structure
UBERON:0000476.definition: Anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances and together does not constitute a cell or a tissue.

UBERON:0000467.label: anatomical system
UBERON:0000467.definition: Multicellular, connected anatomical structure that has multiple organs as parts and whose parts work together to achieve some shared function.

UBERON:0004121.label: ectoderm-derived structure
UBERON:0004121.definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the ectoderm.

UBERON:0004119.label: endoderm-derived structure
UBERON:0004119.definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the endoderm.

UBERON:0015212.label: lateral structure
UBERON:0015212.definition: Any structure that is placed on one side of the left-right axis of a bilaterian.

UBERON:0004120.label: mesoderm-derived structure
UBERON:0004120.definition: An anatomical structure that develops (entirely or partially) from the mesoderm.

UBERON:0034768.label: morphological feature
UBERON:0034768.definition: A part of an organism or organ that is continuous with its surroundings and distinguished from its surroundings based on morphology.

UBERON:0010000.label: multicellular anatomical structure
UBERON:0010000.definition: An anatomical structure that has more than one cell as a part.

UBERON:0005090.label: muscle structure
UBERON:0005090.definition: Muscle structures are contractile cells, tissues or organs that are found in multicellular organisms[GO].

UBERON:0000062.label: organ
UBERON:0000062.definition: Anatomical structure that performs a specific function or group of functions [WP].

UBERON:0010314.label: structure with developmental contribution from neural crest
UBERON:0010314.definition: An anatomical structure that has some part that develops from the neural crest.

UBERON:0003102.label: surface structure
UBERON:0003102.definition: Anatomical structure that overlaps the outer epithelial layer and is adjacent to the space surrounding the organism.

UBERON:0005172.label: abdomen element
UBERON:0005172.definition: An organ or element that is in the abdomen. Examples: spleen, intestine, kidney, abdominal mammary gland.

UBERON:0003103.label: compound organ
UBERON:0003103.definition: Anatomical structure that has as its parts two or more multi-tissue structures of at least two different types and which through specific morphogenetic processes forms a single distinct structural unit demarcated by bona fide boundaries from other distinct anatomical structures of different types.

UBERON:0013765.label: digestive system element
UBERON:0013765.definition: Any of the organs or elements that are part of the digestive system. Examples: tongue, esophagus, spleen, crop, lunge feeding organ, tooth elements.

UBERON:0002530.label: gland
UBERON:0002530.definition: an organ that functions as a secretory or excretory organ

UBERON:0004177.label: hemopoietic organ
UBERON:0004177.definition: Organ that is part of the hematopoietic system.

UBERON:0005057.label: immune organ
UBERON:0005057.definition: An organ that is part of a immune system [Automatically generated definition].

UBERON:0001630.label: muscle organ
UBERON:0001630.definition: Organ consisting of a tissue made up of various elongated cells that are specialized to contract and thus to produce movement and mechanical work[GO].

UBERON:0000171.label: respiration organ
UBERON:0000171.definition: Organ that functions in gaseous exchange between an organism and its environment. In plants, microorganisms, and many small animals, air or water makes direct contact with the organism's cells or tissue fluids, and the processes of diffusion supply the organism with dioxygen (O2) and remove carbon dioxide (CO2). In larger animals the efficiency of gaseous exchange is improved by specialized respiratory organs, such as lungs and gills, which are ventilated by breathing mechanisms.

UBERON:0004765.label: skeletal element
UBERON:0004765.definition: Organ consisting of skeletal tissue. Encompasses whole bones, fused bones, cartilaginious elements, teeth, dermal denticles.

UBERON:0005177.label: trunk region element
UBERON:0005177.definition: An organ or element that part of the trunk region. The trunk region can be further subdividied into thoracic (including chest and thoracic cavity) and abdominal (including abdomen and pelbis) regions.

UBERON:0000057.label: urethra
UBERON:0000057.definition: the fibromuscular tubular canal through which urine is discharged from the bladder to the exterior via the external urinary meatus; in males, the urethra is joined by the ejaculatory ducts and serves as a passageway for semen during ejaculation, as well as a canal for urine during voiding; in females, the urethra is shorter and emerges above the vaginal opening

UBERON:0006003.label: integumentary adnexa
UBERON:0006003.definition: Anatomical structure embedded in or located in the integument that is part of the integumental system. Examples: hair, follicles, skin glands, claws, nails, feathers.

UBERON:0001728.label: nasopharynx
UBERON:0001728.definition: the section of the pharynx that lies above the soft palate

UBERON:0001130.label: vertebral column
UBERON:0001130.definition: Subdivision of skeletal system that consists of all the vertebra and associated skeletal elements and joints in the body[modified from VSAO].

UBERON:0000071.label: death stage
UBERON:0000071.definition: End of the life of an organism.

UBERON:0000068.label: embryo stage
UBERON:0000068.definition: A life cycle stage that starts with fertilization and ends with the fully formed embryo.

UBERON:0034920.label: infant stage
UBERON:0034920.definition: Nursing stage that follows the neonate stage in mammals and ends at weaning.

UBERON:0034919.label: juvenile stage
UBERON:0034919.definition: The stage of being no more dependent of the nest and/or from caregivers for subsistence while having not reach sexual maturity.

UBERON:0000069.label: larval stage
UBERON:0000069.definition: A distinct juvenile stage many animals undergo before metamorphosis into adults. Animals with indirect development such as insects, amphibians, or cnidarians typically have a larval phase of their life cycle.

UBERON:0007221.label: neonate stage
UBERON:0007221.definition: Of or pertaining to the period of time immediately following birth, or to the newborn.

UBERON:0018241.label: prime adult stage
UBERON:0018241.definition: A life cycle stage that starts at completion of development and growth of the sexually mature adult animal, and ends before senescence.

UBERON:0002185.label: bronchus
UBERON:0002185.definition: the upper conducting airways of the lung; these airways arise from the terminus of the trachea

UBERON:0003126.label: trachea
UBERON:0003126.definition: The trachea is the portion of the airway that attaches to the bronchi as it branches [GO:dph].

UBERON:0001156.label: ascending colon
UBERON:0001156.definition: Section of colon which is distal to the cecum and proximal to the transversecolon.[FMA,modified]

UBERON:0001158.label: descending colon
UBERON:0001158.definition: The portion of the colon between the left colic flexure and the sigmoid colon at the pelvic brim; the portion of the descending colon lying in the left iliac fossa is sometimes called the iliac colon.

UBERON:0001159.label: sigmoid colon
UBERON:0001159.definition: The part of the large intestine that is closest to the rectum and anus. It forms a loop that averages about 40 cm. in length, and normally lies within the pelvis, but on account of its freedom of movement it is liable to be displaced into the abdominal cavity.

UBERON:0010239.label: spiral colon
UBERON:0010239.definition: A variant of the ascending colon in ruminants and pigs.

UBERON:0001157.label: transverse colon
UBERON:0001157.definition: The proximal-distal subdivision of colon that runs transversely across the upper part of the abdomen, from the right to the left colic flexure. Continuous with the descending colon[BTO,modified].

UBERON:0002048.label: lung
UBERON:0002048.definition: Respiration organ that develops as an oupocketing of the esophagus.

UBERON:0034945.label: excreted gas
UBERON:0034945.definition: Any gaseous product of an excretory process.

UBERON:0001988.label: feces
UBERON:0001988.definition: Portion of semisolid bodily waste discharged through the anus[MW,modified]

UBERON:0001088.label: urine
UBERON:0001088.definition: Excretion that is the output of a kidney

UBERON:0013755.label: arterial blood
UBERON:0013755.definition: A blood that is part of a artery.

UBERON:0013757.label: capillary blood
UBERON:0013757.definition: A blood that is part of a capillary.

UBERON:0012168.label: umbilical cord blood
UBERON:0012168.definition: blood that remains in the placenta and in the attached umbilical cord after childbirth[WP].

UBERON:0013756.label: venous blood
UBERON:0013756.definition: A blood that is part of a vein.

UBERON:0000178.label: blood
UBERON:0000178.definition: A fluid that is composed of blood plasma and erythrocytes.

UBERON:0001969.label: blood plasma
UBERON:0001969.definition: The liquid component of blood, in which erythrocytes are suspended.

UBERON:0001977.label: blood serum
UBERON:0001977.definition: The portion of blood plasma that excludes clotting factors.

UBERON:0002391.label: lymph
UBERON:0002391.definition: Lymph is the fluid that is formed when interstitial fluid enters the conduits of the lymphatic system through lymph capillaries[WP].

UBERON:0001836.label: saliva
UBERON:0001836.definition: A fluid produced in the oral cavity by salivary glands, typically used in predigestion, but also in other functions.

UBERON:0007794.label: secretion of serous gland
UBERON:0007794.definition: Any fluid produced by a serous gland.

UBERON:0008944.label: albumen
UBERON:0008944.definition: Albumen is the clear liquid contained within an egg and consists of water and proteins, among which are ovomucin and ovomucoid. It protects the egg yolk and provides additional nutrition for the growth of the embryo.

UBERON:0034873.label: bodily gas
UBERON:0034873.definition: Any substance in the body or expelled from the body that is in a gaseous state.

UBERON:0006538.label: respiratory system fluid/secretion
UBERON:0006538.definition: A portion of organism substance that secreted_by a respiratory system.

UBERON:0000456.label: secretion of exocrine gland
UBERON:0000456.definition: A portion of organism substance that is produced by exocrine glands.

OGMS:0000087.label: extended organism
OGMS:0000087.definition: An object aggregate consisting of an organism and all material entities located within the organism, overlapping the organism, or occupying sites formed in part by the organism.

UBERON:0000463.label: organism substance
UBERON:0000463.definition: Material anatomical entity in a gaseous, liquid, semisolid or solid state; produced by anatomical structures or derived from inhaled and ingested substances that have been modified by anatomical structures as they pass through the body.

UBERON:0001004.label: respiratory system
UBERON:0001004.definition: Functional system which consists of structures involved in respiration.

UBERON:0007023.label: adult organism
UBERON:0007023.definition: A multicellular organism that existence_ends_with a post-juvenile adult stage and existence_starts_with a post-juvenile adult stage.

UBERON:0000922.label: embryo
UBERON:0000922.definition: Anatomical entity that comprises the organism in the early stages of growth and differentiation that are characterized by cleavage, the laying down of fundamental tissues, and the formation of primitive organs and organ systems. For example, for mammals, the process would begin with zygote formation and end with birth. For insects, the process would begin at zygote formation and end with larval hatching. For plant zygotic embryos, this would be from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. For plant vegetative embryos, this would be from the initial determination of the cell or group of cells to form an embryo until the point when the embryo becomes independent of the parent plant.

UBERON:0005181.label: thoracic segment organ
UBERON:0005181.definition: An organ that part of the thoracic segment region. This region can be further subdividied chest and thoracic cavity regions.

UBERON:0005079.label: eggshell
UBERON:0005079.definition: A product of the somatic follicle cell epithelium and a structure that supports the egg in a hostile environment, minimizing water loss whilst allowing gas exchanges essential for embryonic respiration[GO].

UBERON:0002371.label: bone marrow
UBERON:0002371.definition: the soft tissue that fills the cavities of bones

UBERON:0005291.label: embryonic tissue
UBERON:0005291.definition: A portion of tissue that is part of an embryo.

UBERON:0000483.label: epithelium
UBERON:0000483.definition: Portion of tissue, that consists of one or more layers of epithelial cells connected to each other by cell junctions and which is underlain by a basal lamina. Examples: simple squamous epithelium, glandular cuboidal epithelium, transitional epithelium, myoepithelium[CARO].

UBERON:0002385.label: muscle tissue
UBERON:0002385.definition: Muscle tissue is a contractile tissue made up of actin and myosin fibers[GO].

UBERON:0003929.label: digestive tract epithelium
UBERON:0003929.definition: An epithelium that lines the lumen of the digestive tract.

UBERON:0010371.label: ecto-epithelium
UBERON:0010371.definition: Epithelium composed of cells that develops from the ectoderm[FMA,modified].

UBERON:0005911.label: endo-epithelium
UBERON:0005911.definition: Epithelium that derives from the endoderm. Examples: urothelium, transitional epithelium of ureter, epithelium of prostatic gland.[FMA]

UBERON:0003350.label: epithelium of mucosa
UBERON:0003350.definition: A layer of epithelial cells on the surface of the mucosa.

UBERON:0000490.label: unilaminar epithelium
UBERON:0000490.definition: Epithelium which consists of a single layer of epithelial cells. Examples: endothelium, mesothelium, glandular squamous epithelium.[FMA]

UBERON:0018707.label: bladder organ
UBERON:0018707.definition: A membranous sac in animals that serves as the receptacle of a liquid or contains gas.

UBERON:0002113.label: kidney
UBERON:0002113.definition: A paired organ of the urinary tract which has the production of urine as its primary function.

UBERON:0009497.label: epithelium of foregut-midgut junction
UBERON:0009497.definition: An epithelium that is part of a foregut-midgut junction.

UBERON:0011642.label: oral epithelium from ectoderm
UBERON:0011642.definition: An epithelium that develops_from a ectoderm and is part of a oral epithelium.

UBERON:0008994.label: equine glandular stomach
UBERON:0008994.definition: Stomach found in horses; includes cardiac, proper gastric and pyloric glandular zones.

UBERON:0005052.label: gizzard
UBERON:0005052.definition: The muscular enlargement of the alimentary canal that has usually thick muscular walls and a tough horny lining for grinding the food and when the crop is present follows it and the proventriculus.

UBERON:0007366.label: ruminant stomach
UBERON:0007366.definition: The ruminants' stomach consists of four compartments: rumen, reticulum, omasum and abomasum. The first three compartments comprise the forestomach (proventriculus). They are lined with nonglandular membrane. The fourth compartment, the abomasum comprises the true stomach of the ruminants. It is lined with glandular mucous membrane. The rumen lies on the left of the abdominal cavity, the reticulum cranially and the omasum on the right. The abomasum lies ventrally, its proximal end lies ventral to the rumen, reticulum and omasum

UBERON:0000065.label: respiratory tract
UBERON:0000065.definition: Anatomical structure that is part of the respiratory system. In mammals consists of upper and lower tracts

UBERON:0015232.label: nematode pharynx
UBERON:0015232.definition: The feeding organ, a neuro-muscular pump in the head of the animal, used to ingest food, bacteria suspended in liquid, filter them out, grind them up and transport posteriorly into the instestine.

UBERON:0009006.label: deep inguinal lymph node
UBERON:0009006.definition: One of several small inconstant lymph nodes, proximal, intermediate and distal deep to the fascia lata and medial to the femoral vein; they receive lymph from the deep structures of the lower limb, from the glans penis and from superficial inguinal nodes; efferents pass to the external iliac nodes.

UBERON:0009007.label: superficial inguinal lymph node
UBERON:0009007.definition: A group of 12-20 lymph nodes that lie in the subcutaneous tissue below the inguinal ligament and along the terminal part of the great saphenous vein; they drain the skin and subcutaneous tissue of the lower abdominal wall, perineum, buttocks, external genitalia, and lower limbs.

UBERON:0004590.label: sphincter muscle
UBERON:0004590.definition: A structure, usually a circular muscle, that normally maintains constriction of a natural body passage or orifice and which relaxes as required by normal physiological functioning.

UBERON:0007109.label: meconium
UBERON:0007109.definition: A dark greenish mass that accumulates in the bowel during fetal life and is discharged shortly after birth.

UBERON:0002167.label: right lung
UBERON:0002167.definition: Lung which consists of the right upper lobe, middle lobe and right lower lobe.[FMA]

UBERON:0007379.label: shelled egg
UBERON:0007379.definition: The hard-shelled reproductive body produced by a bird and especially by the common domestic chicken; also: its contents used as food.

UBERON:0017672.label: abdominal viscera
UBERON:0017672.definition: A viscus that is part of a abdomen.

UBERON:0001255.label: urinary bladder
UBERON:0001255.definition: distensible musculomembranous organ situated in the anterior part of the pelvic cavity in which urine collects before excretion[MP].

UBERON:0004538.label: left kidney
UBERON:0004538.definition: A kidney that is part of a left side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

UBERON:0004539.label: right kidney
UBERON:0004539.definition: A kidney that is part of a right side of organism [Automatically generated definition].

UBERON:0002107.label: liver
UBERON:0002107.definition: An exocrine gland which secretes bile and functions in metabolism of protein and carbohydrate and fat, synthesizes substances involved in the clotting of the blood, synthesizes vitamin A, detoxifies poisonous substances, stores glycogen, and breaks down worn-out erythrocytes[GO].

UBERON:0006925.label: digestive system gland
UBERON:0006925.definition: Any gland that is part of the digestive system.

UBERON:0012307.label: anterior cervical lymph node
UBERON:0012307.definition: The anterior cervical lymph nodes are a group of nodes found on the anterior part of the neck.

UBERON:0004722.label: deep cervical lymph node
UBERON:0004722.definition: The deep cervical lymph nodes are a group of cervical lymph nodes found near the internal jugular vein. They can be divided into upper and lower groups, or superior and inferior groups. Alternatively, they can be divided into deep anterior cervical lymph nodes and deep lateral cervical lymph nodes. They can also be divided into three groups: superior deep jugular, middle deep jugular, and 'inferior deep jugular'.

UBERON:0012306.label: lateral cervical lymph node
UBERON:0012306.definition: A cervical lymph nodes are found in proximity to an internal or external jugular vein.

UBERON:0004870.label: superficial cervical lymph node
UBERON:0004870.definition: A group of nodes lying along the external jugular vein; they drain the skin and superficial structures over the region of the sternocleidomastoid muscle and anterior cervical regions. Efferent vessels drain to the deep cervical lymph nodes. Lymph nodes can be further subdivided into anterior and lateral groupings.

UBERON:0035279.label: supraclavicular lymph node
UBERON:0035279.definition: A lymph node which is located above the clavicle.

UBERON:0002526.label: lumbar lymph node
UBERON:0002526.definition: The lumbar lymph nodes (paraaortic nodes) are a group of lymph nodes residing in the lumbar region. They consist of the following groups: right and left lateral aortic lymph nodes preaortic lymph nodes retroaortic lymph nodes (or 'postaortic')

UBERON:0002527.label: pancreatic lymph node
UBERON:0002527.definition: A lymph node that is part of a pancreas [Automatically generated definition].

UBERON:0035520.label: anterior mediastinal lymph node
UBERON:0035520.definition: A lymph node located in the superior mediastinum that collects lymph from the thymus, the pericardium, and the right side of the heart.

UBERON:0007643.label: node of ligamentum arteriosum
UBERON:0007643.definition: An inconstant lymph node of the anterior mediastinal group located adjacent to the ligamentum arteriosum.

UBERON:0002368.label: endocrine gland
UBERON:0002368.definition: Endocrine glands are glands of the endocrine system that secrete their products directly into the circulatory system rather than through a duct.[WP, modified].

UBERON:0002365.label: exocrine gland
UBERON:0002365.definition: A gland that secretes products (excluding hormones and other chemical messengers) into ducts (duct glands) which lead directly into the external environment[WP]. Typical exocrine glands include sweat glands, salivary glands, mammary glands, stomach, liver, pancreas

UBERON:3000961.label: external integument structure
UBERON:3000961.definition: Structures of the dermis, epidermis, glands and pigment cells recognizable on the external surfaces of the integument.

UBERON:0007376.label: outer epithelium
UBERON:0007376.definition: The epidermis is the entire outer epithelial layer of an animal, it may be a single layer that produces an extracellular material (e.g. the cuticle of arthropods) or a complex stratified squamous epithelium, as in the case of many vertebrate species[GO].

UBERON:0000489.label: cavitated compound organ
UBERON:0000489.definition: Compound organ that contains one or more macroscopic anatomical spaces.

UBERON:0015228.label: circulatory organ
UBERON:0015228.definition: A hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, contributes to the circulation of lymph, blood or analogs. Examples: a chambered vertebrate heart; the tubular peristaltic heart of ascidians; the dorsal vessel of an insect; the lymoh heart of a reptile.

UBERON:0001005.label: respiratory airway
UBERON:0001005.definition: An airway through which respiratory air passes in organisms.

UBERON:0004176.label: external genitalia
UBERON:0004176.definition: The external genitalia are the outer sex organs, such as the penis or vulva in mammals

UBERON:0004175.label: internal genitalia
UBERON:0004175.definition: The internal genitalia are the internal sex organs such as the uterine tube, the uterus and the vagina in female mammals, and the testis, seminal vesicle, ejaculatory duct and prostate in male mammals

UBERON:0002424.label: oral epithelium
UBERON:0002424.definition: An epithelium that is part of the mouth and lines the oral cavity, typically stratified squamous, and may be para-, ortho- or non- keratinized. Primary barrier between oral environment and deeper tissues

UBERON:0007499.label: epithelial sac
UBERON:0007499.definition: An epithelial tube that is open at one end only.

UBERON:0015833.label: foregut epithelium
UBERON:0015833.definition: A epithelium that is part of a foregut.

UBERON:0001097.label: axillary lymph node
UBERON:0001097.definition: the lymph nodes located around the axillary vein that receive lymphatic drainage from the upper or forelimb, scapular region and pectoral region

UBERON:0001542.label: inguinal lymph node
UBERON:0001542.definition: the lymph nodes located in the groin area

UBERON:0001543.label: popliteal lymph node
UBERON:0001543.definition: the lymph nodes which drain the legs; contained in the popliteal fossa

UBERON:0002520.label: submandibular lymph node
UBERON:0002520.definition: The submandibular lymph nodes (submaxillary glands in older texts), three to six in number, are placed beneath the body of the mandible in the submaxillary triangle, and rest on the superficial surface of the submaxillary salivary gland. One gland, the middle gland of Stahr, which lies on the external maxillary artery as it turns over the mandible, is the most constant of the series; small lymph glands are sometimes found on the deep surface of the submaxillary salivary glands. The afferents of the submaxillary glands drain the medial palpebral commissure, the cheek, the side of the nose, the upper lip, the lateral part of the lower lip, the gums, and the anterior part of the margin of the tongue. Efferent vessels from the facial and submental glands also enter the submaxillary glands. Their efferent vessels pass to the superior deep cervical glands. [WP,unvetted].

UBERON:0000569.label: ileocecal valve
UBERON:0000569.definition: The ileocecal valve is a sphincter muscle situated at the junction of the small intestine (ileum) and the large intestine. Its critical function is to limit the reflux of colonic contents into the ileum.

UBERON:0000025.label: tube
UBERON:0000025.definition: Any hollow cylindrical anatomical structure containing a lumen through which substances are transported.

UBERON:0004185.label: endodermal part of digestive tract
UBERON:0004185.definition: A portions of the gut that is derived from endoderm.

UBERON:0002110.label: gall bladder
UBERON:0002110.definition: An organ that aids digestion and stores bile produced by the liver[WP].

UBERON:0001729.label: oropharynx
UBERON:0001729.definition: the portion of the pharynx that lies between the soft palate and the upper edge of the epiglottis

UBERON:0000072.label: proximo-distal subdivision of respiratory tract
UBERON:0000072.definition: An section of a respiratory tract.

UBERON:0000948.label: heart
UBERON:0000948.definition: A myogenic muscular circulatory organ found in the vertebrate cardiovascular system composed of chambers of cardiac muscle. It is the primary circulatory organ.

UBERON:0002509.label: mesenteric lymph node
UBERON:0002509.definition: The lymph nodes located in the mesentery, of which there are 3 classes: ileocolic, juxtaintestinal mesenteric, and central superior group.

UBERON:0004906.label: ectodermal part of digestive tract
UBERON:0004906.definition: A portion of the gut that is derived from ectoderm.

UBERON:0002106.label: spleen
UBERON:0002106.definition: the organ that functions to filter blood and to store red corpuscles and platelets

UBERON:0008835.label: hepatic diverticulum
UBERON:0008835.definition: An out-pocket of thickened ventral foregut epithelium adjacent to the developing heart. Constitutes the first morphological sign of the embryonic liver. The anterior portion of the hepatic diverticulum gives rise to the liver and intrahepatic biliary tree, while the posterior portion forms the gall bladder and extrahepatic bile ducts.

UBERON:0013703.label: integumentary projection
UBERON:0013703.definition: Anatomical projection that is part of the integumentl system.

UBERON:0011185.label: gastrointestinal sphincter
UBERON:0011185.definition: A sphincter muscle that is part of the gastrointestinal system

UBERON:0012311.label: deep anterior cervical lymph node
UBERON:0012311.definition: The deep anterior cervical lymph nodes are found near the middle cricothyroid ligament and the trachea.

UBERON:0012310.label: deep lateral cervical lymph node
UBERON:0012310.definition: The deep lateral cervical lymph nodes are found near the upper part of the internal jugular vein in the neck, lateral or posterior to the carotid sheath.

UBERON:0012309.label: superficial anterior cervical lymph node
UBERON:0012309.definition: The superficial anterior cervical lymph nodes are found in proximity to the anterior jugular vein.

UBERON:0012308.label: superficial lateral cervical lymph node
UBERON:0012308.definition: The superficial lateral cervical lymph nodes are found in proximity to the external jugular vein.

UBERON:0012287.label: Rathkes pouch epithelium
UBERON:0012287.definition: A epithelial sac that is part of a Rathke's pouch.

UBERON:0008250.label: cardiac stomach
UBERON:0008250.definition: In starfishes the cardiac stomach is connected to a pyloric stomach which is located above it. Food can be brought into the stomach through the mouth or, in many species, the cardiac stomach can be extended out through the mouth to digest food outside the body. Suspension-feeding starfish use their tube feet to pass food to the mouth.

UBERON:0001155.label: colon
UBERON:0001155.definition: Last portion of the large intestine before it becomes the rectum.

UBERON:0012652.label: colorectum
UBERON:0012652.definition: The subdivision of the digestive tract that consists of the colon and the rectum.

UBERON:0009854.label: digestive tract diverticulum
UBERON:0009854.definition: Branch or outpocketing of the digestive tract.

UBERON:0013644.label: duodenal ampulla
UBERON:0013644.definition: The very first part of the duodenum which is slightly dilated.

UBERON:0002114.label: duodenum
UBERON:0002114.definition: The first part of the small intestine. At the junction of the stomach and the duodenum the alimentary canal is inflected. The duodenum first goes anteriorly for a short distance, turns dorsally, and eventually caudally, thus it is a U-shaped structure with two horizontal sections (a ventral and a dorsal one).

UBERON:0008248.label: echinoderm pyloric cecum
UBERON:0008248.definition: The pyloric ceca (or digestive glands) and the cardiac stomach produce digestive enzymes in starfishes. Digested material is absorbed through the pyloric ceca for transport to the rest of the body. Each pyloric cecum extends the length of each arm.

UBERON:0001043.label: esophagus
UBERON:0001043.definition: Tube that connects the pharynx to the stomach. In mammals, the oesophagus connects the buccal cavity with the stomach. The stratified squamous non-keratinised epithelium lining the buccal cavity is continued through the pharynx down into the oesophagus. The lowest part of the oesophagus (ca. 2 cm) is lined with gastric mucosa and covered by peritoneum. The main body of the oesophagus is lined with small, simple mucous glands. Each gland opens into the lumen by a long duct which pierces the muscularis mucosae (Wilson and Washington, 1989). A sphincter is situated at the point where the oesophagus enters the stomach to prevent gastro-oesophageal reflux, i.e. to prevent acidic gastric contents from reaching stratified epithelia of the oesophagus, where they can cause inflammation and irritation (Wilson and Washington, 1989; Brown et al., 1993).

UBERON:0001041.label: foregut
UBERON:0001041.definition: Anterior subdivision of a digestive tract.

UBERON:0001046.label: hindgut
UBERON:0001046.definition: The caudalmost subdivision of a digestive tract.

UBERON:0002116.label: ileum
UBERON:0002116.definition: the portion of the small intestine that extends from the jejunum to the colon

UBERON:0000160.label: intestine
UBERON:0000160.definition: Segment of the alimentary canal extending from the stomach to the anus and, in humans and other mammals, consists of two segments, the small intestine and the large intestine.

UBERON:0002115.label: jejunum
UBERON:0002115.definition: the portion of the small intestine that extends from the duodenum to the ileum

UBERON:0000059.label: large intestine
UBERON:0000059.definition: A subdivision of the digestive tract that connects the small intestine to the cloaca or anus. Lacks or has few villi[Kardong].

UBERON:0004907.label: lower digestive tract
UBERON:0004907.definition: The region of the digestive tract extending from the beginning of the intestines to the anus[GO - gut definition].

UBERON:0013473.label: lower esophagus
UBERON:0013473.definition: The lower one third of the esophagus in which the muscle layer is composed of muscle cells predominantly of the smooth type.

UBERON:0013474.label: middle part of esophagus
UBERON:0013474.definition: The middle one third of the esophagus in which the muscle layer is composed of muscle cells of the striated and smooth types.

UBERON:0001045.label: midgut
UBERON:0001045.definition: Middle subdivision of a digestive tract[CJM]. In vertebrates: The middle part of the alimentary canal from the stomach, or entrance of the bile duct, to, or including, the large intestine[GO].

UBERON:0011698.label: midgut loop
UBERON:0011698.definition: Portion of midgut after it bends around the superior mesenteric artery

UBERON:0000165.label: mouth
UBERON:0000165.definition: The proximal portion of the digestive tract, containing the oral cavity and bounded by the oral opening. In vertebrates, this extends to the pharynx and includes gums, lips, tongue and parts of the palate. Typically also includes the teeth, except where these occur elsewhere (e.g. pharyngeal jaws) or protrude from the mouth (tusks).

UBERON:0006562.label: pharynx
UBERON:0006562.definition: The pharynx is the part of the digestive system immediately posterior to the mouth[GO].

UBERON:0000168.label: proximal-distal subdivision of colon
UBERON:0000168.definition: A section dividing a colon along a proximal-distal axis.

UBERON:0008246.label: pyloric stomach
UBERON:0008246.definition: The mouth of a starfish is located on the underside of the body, and opens through a short esophagus into firstly a cardiac stomach, and then, a second, pyloric stomach. Each arm also contains two pyloric caeca, long hollow tubes branching outwards from the pyloric stomach. Each pyloric caecum is lined by a series of digestive glands, which secrete digestive enzymes and absorb nutrients from the food. A short intestine runs from the upper surface of the pyloric stomach to open at an anus in the center of the upper body

UBERON:0001052.label: rectum
UBERON:0001052.definition: the terminal portion of the intestinal tube, terminating with the anus

UBERON:0007364.label: reticulorumen
UBERON:0007364.definition: The first chamber in the alimentary canal of a ruminant stomach, composed of the rumen and reticulum.

UBERON:0002108.label: small intestine
UBERON:0002108.definition: Subdivision of digestive tract that connects the stomach to the large intestine and is where much of the digestion and absorption of food takes place (with the exception of ruminants). The mammalian small intestine is long and coiled and can be differentiated histologically into: duodenum, jejunem, ileum[WP,cjm,Kardong].

UBERON:0000945.label: stomach
UBERON:0000945.definition: An expanded region of the vertebrate alimentary tract that serves as a food storage compartment and digestive organ. A stomach is lined, in whole or in part by a glandular epithelium.

UBERON:0004045.label: tailgut
UBERON:0004045.definition: The extension of the hindgut of the primitive digestive tube of the embryo, caudal to the location of the anal opening

UBERON:0006866.label: terminal part of digestive tract
UBERON:0006866.definition: The distalmost portion of the digestive tract, derived from the hindgut, and terminating with the anus.

UBERON:0004908.label: upper digestive tract
UBERON:0004908.definition: The region of the digestive tract extending from the mouth cavity through pharynx esophagus stomach and duodenum.

UBERON:0013472.label: upper esophagus
UBERON:0013472.definition: The upper one third of esophagus in which the muscle layer is composed of muscle cells of the striated type.

UBERON:0000029.label: lymph node
UBERON:0000029.definition: Any of the rounded masses of lymphoid tissue that are surrounded by a capsule of connective tissue, are distributed along the lymphatic vessels, and contain numerous lymphocytes which filter the flow of lymph.

UBERON:0005179.label: pelvic region element
UBERON:0005179.definition: An organ or element that is part of the pelvic region. Examples: reproductive organs (in some organisms), urinary bladder, bones of the pelvis.

UBERON:0005173.label: abdominal segment element
UBERON:0005173.definition: An organ or element that is part of the adbominal segment of the organism. This region can be further subdivided into the abdominal cavity and the pelvic region.

UBERON:0002075.label: viscus
UBERON:0002075.definition: An organ that is located within the body cavity (or in its extension, in the scrotum); it consists of organ parts that are embryologically derived from endoderm, splanchnic mesoderm or intermediate mesoderm; together with other organs, the viscus constitutes the respiratory, gastrointestinal, urinary, reproductive and immune systems, or is the central organ of the cardiovascular system. Examples: heart, lung, esophagus, kidney, ovary, spleen.

UBERON:0005178.label: thoracic cavity element
UBERON:0005178.definition: An organ or element that is in the thoracic cavity. Examples: lung, heart, longus colli.

UBERON:0002050.label: embryonic structure
UBERON:0002050.definition: Anatomical structure that is part of an embryo.

NCIT:C13347.label: Aspirate
NCIT:C13347.definition: Fluid withdrawn from a body cavity, organ, cyst, or tumor.

UBERON:0000179.label: haemolymphatic fluid
UBERON:0000179.definition: Circulating fluid that is part of the hemolymphoid system. Blood, lymph, interstitial fluid or its analogs.

UBERON:0007311.label: sputum
UBERON:0007311.definition: Matter ejected from the lungs, bronchi, and trachea, through the mouth.

UBERON:0007779.label: transudate
UBERON:0007779.definition: Any bodily fluid that has passed through a membrane such as the capillary wall, as a result of unbalanced hydrostatic and osmotic forces

UBERON:0001042.label: chordate pharynx
UBERON:0001042.definition: A portion of the respiratory and digestive tracts; its distal limit is the superior part of the esophagus and it connects the nasal and oral cavities with the esophagus and larynx; it contains the valleculae and the pyriform recesses; its upper limits are the nasal cavity and cranial base.[FEED].

NCIT:C13308.label: Hepatic
NCIT:C13308.definition: Pertaining to, affecting, or associated with the liver.

UBERON:0009097.label: gravid organism
UBERON:0009097.definition: An organism containing a developing embryo, fetus, or unborn offspring within the body.

UBERON:0012236.label: intercostal lymph node
UBERON:0012236.definition: The intercostal lymph nodes (intercostal glands ) occupy the posterior parts of the intercostal spaces, in relation to the intercostal vessels. They receive the deep lymphatics from the postero-lateral aspect of the chest; some of these vessels are interrupted by small lateral intercostal glands.

UBERON:0002524.label: mediastinal lymph node
UBERON:0002524.definition: A lymph node that is part of a mediastinum. Each consists of several lymph node groups, especially along the trachea (5 groups), along the esophagus and between the lung and the diaphragm. In the mediastinal lymph nodes arises lymphatic ducts, which draines the lymph to the left subclavian vein (to the venous angle in the confluence of the subclavian and deep jugular veins). The mediastinal lymph nodes along the esophagus are in tight connection with the abdominal lymph nodes along the esophagus and the stomach. That fact facilitates spreading of tumors cells through these lymphatics in cases of cancers of the stomach and particularly of the esophagus. Through the mediastinum, the main lymphatic drainage from the abdominal organs goes via the thoracic duct (ductus thoracicus), which drains majority of the lymph from the abdomen to the above mentioned left venous angle.

UBERON:0035219.label: parasternal lymph node
UBERON:0035219.definition: Any of the lymph nodes of the breast located under the ribcage, near the sternum.

UBERON:0001268.label: peritoneal fluid
UBERON:0001268.definition: Transudate contained in the peritoneal cavity.

UBERON:0001090.label: synovial fluid
UBERON:0001090.definition: Joint fluid is a transudate of plasma that is actively secreted by synovial cells.

UBERON:0001359.label: cerebrospinal fluid
UBERON:0001359.definition: A clear, colorless, bodily fluid, that occupies the subarachnoid space and the ventricular system around and inside the brain and spinal cord.

UBERON:0015895.label: proximal deep inguinal lymph node
UBERON:0015895.definition: One of the deep inguinal lymph nodes located in or adjacent to the femoral canal; sometimes mistaken for a femoral hernia when enlarged.

UBERON:4300174.label: actinopterygian pyloric caecum
UBERON:4300174.definition: A finger-like out-pocketing of the intestine where it meets the end of the stomach (pylorus). Also spelled cecum (ceca). Serves to aid digestion.

UBERON:0001153.label: caecum
UBERON:0001153.definition: A pouch in the digestive tract that connects the ileum with the ascending colon of the large intestine. It is separated from the ileum by the ileocecal valve, and is the beginning of the large intestine. It is also separated from the colon by the cecocolic junction.

UBERON:0009855.label: echinoderm gastric caecum
UBERON:0009855.definition: non-contractile pouch that is connected to the anterior stomach through a slit-like opening. This pouch is also well-connected to the haemal system through numerous haemal ducts within its connective tissue layer.

UBERON:0012474.label: hepatic cecum
UBERON:0012474.definition: A ventral evagination extending anteriorly in the mid-portion of the intestine in Amphioxi.

UBERON:0004111.label: anatomical conduit
UBERON:0004111.definition: Any tube, opening or passage that connects two distinct anatomical spaces.

UBERON:0000468.label: multicellular organism
UBERON:0000468.definition: Anatomical structure that is an individual member of a species and consists of more than one cell.

UBERON:0000064.label: organ part
UBERON:0000064.definition: A multicellular structure that is a part of an organ.

UBERON:0011216.label: organ system subdivision
UBERON:0011216.definition: A subdivision of an anatomical system.

UBERON:0005156.label: reproductive structure
UBERON:0005156.definition: Any anatomical structure that is part of the reproductive system.

UBERON:0000479.label: tissue
UBERON:0000479.definition: Multicellular anatomical structure that consists of many cells of one or a few types, arranged in an extracellular matrix such that their long-range organisation is at least partly a repetition of their short-range organisation.

UBERON:0000075.label: subdivision of skeletal system
UBERON:0000075.definition: Anatomical cluster consisting of the skeletal elements and articular elements that are part of an individual subdivision of the organism.

UBERON:0015869.label: retropharyngeal lymph node
UBERON:0015869.definition: The retropharyngeal lymph nodes, from one to three in number, lie in the buccopharyngeal fascia, behind the upper part of the pharynx and in front of the arch of the atlas, being separated, however, from the latter by the Longus capitis. Their afferents drain the nasal cavities, the nasal part of the pharynx, and the auditory tubes. Their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands. They are in the retropharyngeal space.

UBERON:0000162.label: cloaca
UBERON:0000162.definition: Common chamber into which the intestines and excretory system opens. Arises during development in all vertebrates, but in many it becomes subdivided, lost or incorporated into other structures

UBERON:0004921.label: subdivision of digestive tract
UBERON:0004921.definition: A proximal-distal subdivision of the digestive tract.

UBERON:0000021.label: cutaneous appendage
UBERON:0000021.definition: Anatomical projection that protrudes from the skin. Examples: hair, nail, feather, claw, hoof, horn, wattle, spur, beak, antler, bristle and some scales.

UBERON:0010039.label: food storage organ
UBERON:0010039.definition: An organ of the digestive tract that is capable of retaining and storing food

UBERON:0007100.label: primary circulatory organ
UBERON:0007100.definition: A hollow, muscular organ, which, by contracting rhythmically, keeps up the circulation of the blood or analogs[GO,modified].

UBERON:0016393.label: deep parotid lymph node
UBERON:0016393.definition: The deep parotid lymph nodes are lymph nodes found below the parotid gland. The afferents of the subparotid glands drain the nasal part of the pharynx and the posterior parts of the nasal cavities. Their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.

UBERON:0015923.label: superficial parotid lymph node
UBERON:0015923.definition: A parotid lymph node that is located superficially.

UBERON:0002508.label: celiac lymph node
UBERON:0002508.definition: the visceral glands that are associated with the branches of the celiac artery, including the gastric, hepatic, and pancreaticolienal (splenic) lymph nodes

UBERON:0015863.label: gastric lymph node
UBERON:0015863.definition: A lymph node along the left gastric artery or greater omentum.

UBERON:0015859.label: hepatic lymph node
UBERON:0015859.definition: Any of the lymph nodes adjacent to the stomach and duodenum.

UBERON:0016402.label: mesocolic lymph node
UBERON:0016402.definition: A lymph node that located_in a colon.

UBERON:0015865.label: pancreaticosplenic lymph node
UBERON:0015865.definition: lymph nodes of the pancreatic tail and spleen, receiving afferents from both organs plus the greater curvature of the stomach; they drain to the celiac lymph nodes.

UBERON:0015871.label: facial lymph node
UBERON:0015871.definition: Any of the lymph nodes that are part of a face.

UBERON:0016392.label: mastoid lymph node
UBERON:0016392.definition: The mastoid lymph nodes (retroauricular lymph nodes, posterior auricular glands), usually two in number, are situated on the mastoid insertion of the Sternocleidomastoideus, beneath the Auricularis posterior. Their afferent vessels drain the posterior part of the temporoparietal region, the upper part of the cranial surface of the auricula or pinna, and the back of the external acoustic meatus; their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.

UBERON:0035204.label: occipital lymph node
UBERON:0035204.definition: A lymph node located in the back of the head adjacent to the trapezius muscle.

UBERON:0015857.label: parotid lymph node
UBERON:0015857.definition: A lymph node found near the parotid gland.

UBERON:0016397.label: submental lymph node
UBERON:0016397.definition: The submental lymph nodes (or suprahyoid) are situated between the anterior bellies of the Digastrici. Their afferents drain the central portions of the lower lip and floor of the mouth and the apex of the tongue. Their efferents pass partly to the submandibular lymph nodes and partly to a gland of the deep cervical group situated on the internal jugular vein at the level of the cricoid cartilage.

UBERON:0015872.label: mandibular lymph node
UBERON:0015872.definition: The mandibular lymph node is a lymph node found near the jaw.

UBERON:0015878.label: common iliac lymph node
UBERON:0015878.definition: The external iliac lymph nodes, from eight to ten in number, lie along the external iliac vessels. They are arranged in three groups, one on the lateral, another on the medial, and a third on the anterior aspect of the vessels; the third group is, however, sometimes absent. Their principal afferents are derived from the inguinal lymph nodes, the deep lymphatics of the abdominal wall below the umbilicus and of the adductor region of the thigh, and the lymphatics from the glans penis vel clitoridis, the membranous urethra, the prostate, the fundus of the urinary bladder, the cervix uteri, and upper part of the vagina.

UBERON:0015881.label: internal iliac lymph node
UBERON:0015881.definition: The internal iliac lymph nodes (or hypogastric) surround the internal iliac artery and its branches (the hypogastric vessels), and receive the lymphatics corresponding to the distribution of the branches of it, i. e. , they receive lymphatics from all the pelvic viscera, from the deeper parts of the perineum, including the membranous and cavernous portions of the urethra, and from the buttock and back of the thigh. It does not receive lymph from the ovary, testis, or superior half of the rectum; the gonads drain to the paraaortic lymph nodes, while the superior half of the rectum drains to the pararectal lymph nodes.

UBERON:0035162.label: infraclavicular lymph node
UBERON:0035162.definition: A lymph node located in the area below the clavicle.

UBERON:0016394.label: anterior auricular lymph node
UBERON:0016394.definition: The preauricular deep parotid lymph nodes (anterior auricular glands or preauricular glands), from one to three in number, lie immediately in front of the tragus. Their afferents drain the lateral surface of the auricula and the skin of the adjacent part of the temporal region; their efferents pass to the superior deep cervical glands.

UBERON:0016395.label: infra-auricular lymph node
UBERON:0016395.definition: The infra-auricular deep parotid lymph nodes are a group of lymph nodes found underneath the ear.

UBERON:0016374.label: sciatic lymph node
UBERON:0016374.definition: A lymph node that is medial to the gluteus superficialis m., caudal to gluteus medius m. and sciatic nerve lymph node

UBERON:0004529.label: anatomical projection
UBERON:0004529.definition: A projection or outgrowth of tissue from a larger body or organ.

UBERON:0009870.label: zone of stomach
UBERON:0009870.definition: A division of the stomach. The stomach can be divided based on mucosal histology (glandular epithelium and gastric glands) and the relative position and type of gastric gland.

UBERON:0034946.label: gas excreted from digestive tract
UBERON:0034946.definition: Any excreted gas that is produced by the digestive tract.

UBERON:0035079.label: deep intraparotid lymph node
UBERON:0035079.definition: The intraglandular deep parotid lymph nodes are a group of lymph nodes found inside the parotid gland.

UBERON:0035765.label: subsegmental lymph node
UBERON:0035765.definition: The lymph nodes around the subsegmental bronchi.

UO:0000121.label: angle unit
UO:0000121.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the figure or space formed by the junction of two lines or planes.

UO:0000045.label: base unit
UO:0000045.definition: A unit which is one of a particular measure to which all measures of that type can be related.

UO:0000051.label: concentration unit
UO:0000051.definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of how much of a given substance there is mixed with another substance.

UO:0000261.label: conduction unit
UO:0000261.definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of the transmission of an entity through a medium.

UO:0000182.label: density unit
UO:0000182.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the influence exerted by some mass.

UO:0000186.label: dimensionless unit
UO:0000186.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of physical quantity consisting of only a numerical number without any units.

UO:0000217.label: electric potential difference unit
UO:0000217.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the work done per unit charge as a charge is moved between two points in an electric field.

UO:0000001.label: length unit
UO:0000001.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the distance between two points.

UO:0000060.label: speed/velocity unit
UO:0000060.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the rate of movement. Speed is measured in the same physical units of measurement as velocity, but does not contain the element of direction that velocity has. Speed is thus the magnitude component of velocity.

UO:0000006.label: substance unit
UO:0000006.definition: A unit which is a standardised quantity of an element or compound with uniform composition.

UO:0000005.label: temperature unit
UO:0000005.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the average kinetic energy of the particles in a sample of matter.

UO:0000003.label: time unit
UO:0000003.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the dimension in which events occur in sequence.

UO:0000315.label: turbidity unit
UO:0000315.definition: A unit used to indicate the clarity of water or other solutions or suspensions, as measured by the ability of the solution or suspension to scatter light of a defined wavelength range.

UO:0000095.label: volume unit
UO:0000095.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the amount of space occupied by any substance, whether solid, liquid, or gas.

UO:0000019.label: angstrom
UO:0000019.definition: A length unit which is equal to 10 [-10] m.

UO:0000326.label: centiMorgan
UO:0000326.definition: A unit used to express distances on a genetic map. In genetic mapping, distances between markers are determined by measuring the rate of meoitic recombination between them, which increases proportionately with the distance separating them. A cM is defined as the length of an interval in which there is a 1% probability of recombination. On the average, 1 cM is roughly equivalent to 1 megabase (Mb) of DNA, although this can vary widely due to hot and cold spots of recombination.

UO:0000327.label: centiRay
UO:0000327.definition: A unit of genetic map distance defined corresponding to an interval in which there is a 1% probability of X-irradiation induced breakage. To be completely specified, the unit must be qualified by the radiation in dosage in rads (e.g. cR8000), because this determines the actual breakage probability.

UO:0000015.label: centimeter
UO:0000015.definition: A length unit which is equal to one hundredth of a meter or 10^[-2] m.

UO:0000008.label: meter
UO:0000008.definition: A length unit which is equal to the length of the path traveled by light in vacuum during a time interval of 1/299 792 458 of a second.

UO:0000017.label: micrometer
UO:0000017.definition: A length unit which is equal to one millionth of a meter or 10^[-6] m.

UO:0000016.label: millimeter
UO:0000016.definition: A length unit which is equal to one thousandth of a meter or 10^[-3] m.

UO:0000018.label: nanometer
UO:0000018.definition: A length unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a meter or 10^[-9] m.

UO:0000020.label: picometer
UO:0000020.definition: A length unit which is equal to 10^[-12] m.

UO:0000151.label: century
UO:0000151.definition: A time unit which is equal to 100 years.

UO:0000033.label: day
UO:0000033.definition: A time unit which is equal to 24 hours.

UO:0000152.label: half life
UO:0000152.definition: A time unit which represents the period over which the activity or concentration of a specified chemical or element falls to half its original activity or concentration.

UO:0000032.label: hour
UO:0000032.definition: A time unit which is equal to 3600 seconds or 60 minutes.

UO:0000029.label: microsecond
UO:0000029.definition: A time unit which is equal to one millionth of a second or 10^[-6] s.

UO:0000028.label: millisecond
UO:0000028.definition: A time unit which is equal to one thousandth of a second or 10^[-3] s.

UO:0000031.label: minute
UO:0000031.definition: A time unit which is equal to 60 seconds.

UO:0000035.label: month
UO:0000035.definition: A time unit which is approximately equal to the length of time of one of cycle of the moon's phases which in science is taken to be equal to 30 days.

UO:0000150.label: nanosecond
UO:0000150.definition: A time unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a second or 10^[-9] s.

UO:0000030.label: picosecond
UO:0000030.definition: A time unit which is equal to 10^[-12] s.

UO:0000010.label: second
UO:0000010.definition: A time unit which is equal to the duration of 9 192 631 770 periods of the radiation corresponding to the transition between the two hyperfine levels of the ground state of the caesium 133 atom.

UO:0000034.label: week
UO:0000034.definition: A time unit which is equal to 7 days.

UO:0000036.label: year
UO:0000036.definition: A time unit which is equal to 12 months which is science is taken to be equal to 365.25 days.

UO:0000027.label: degree Celsius
UO:0000027.definition: A temperature unit which is equal to one kelvin degree. However, they have their zeros at different points. The centigrade scale has its zero at 273.15 K.

UO:0000195.label: degree Fahrenheit
UO:0000195.definition: A temperature unit which is equal to 5/9ths of a kelvin. Negative 40 degrees Fahrenheit is equal to negative 40 degrees Celsius.

UO:0000012.label: kelvin
UO:0000012.definition: A thermodynamic temperature unit which is equal to the fraction 1/273.16 of the thermodynamic temperature of the triple point of water.

NCIT:C48519.label: Ounce
NCIT:C48519.definition: The traditional unit of mass. The avoirdupois ounce is equal to 1/16 pound, or 28.349 5 grams, or 0.911 457 troy ounce.

NCIT:C48531.label: Pound
NCIT:C48531.definition: The traditional unit of mass. By international agreement, one avoirdupois pound is equal to exactly 0.453 592 37 kilogram, 16 ounces, or 1.215 28 troy pounds.

UO:0000039.label: micromole
UO:0000039.definition: A substance unit equal to a millionth of a mol or 10^[-6] mol.

UO:0000212.label: colony forming unit per volume
UO:0000212.definition: A concentration unit which a measure of viable bacterial numbers in a given volume.

UO:0000163.label: mass percentage
UO:0000163.definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of a substance in a mixture as a percentage of the mass of the entire mixture.

UO:0000164.label: mass volume percentage
UO:0000164.definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the mass of the substance in a mixture as a percentage of the volume of the entire mixture.

UO:0000076.label: mole fraction
UO:0000076.definition: A concentration unit which denotes the number of moles of solute as a proportion of the total number of moles in a solution.

UO:0000196.label: pH
UO:0000196.definition: A dimensionless concentration notation which denotes the acidity of a solution in terms of activity of hydrogen ions (H+).

UO:0000205.label: volume per unit volume
UO:0000205.definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the given volume of the solute in the total volume of the resulting solution.

UO:0000084.label: gram per cubic centimeter
UO:0000084.definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in cubic centimeters.

UO:0000208.label: gram per deciliter
UO:0000208.definition: A mass density unit which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in deciliters.

UO:0000175.label: gram per liter
UO:0000175.definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in liters.

UO:0000173.label: gram per milliliter
UO:0000173.definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in grams divided by the volume in milliliter.

UO:0000083.label: kilogram per cubic meter
UO:0000083.definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in kilograms divided by the volume in cubic meters.

UO:0000174.label: kilogram per liter
UO:0000174.definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in kilograms divided by the volume in liters.

UO:0000301.label: microgram per liter
UO:0000301.definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in micrograms divided by the volume in liters.

UO:0000274.label: microgram per milliliter
UO:0000274.definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in micrograms divided by the volume in millliters.

UO:0000273.label: milligram per liter
UO:0000273.definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in milligrams divided by the volume in liters.

UO:0000176.label: milligram per milliliter
UO:0000176.definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in milligrams divided by the volume in milliliters.

UO:0000275.label: nanogram per milliliter
UO:0000275.definition: A mass unit density which is equal to mass of an object in nanograms divided by the volume in milliliters.

UO:0000090.label: cubic centimeter per mole
UO:0000090.definition: A molar volume unit which is equal to 1 cubic centimeter occupied by one mole of a substance in the form of a solid, liquid, or gas.

UO:0000089.label: cubic meter per mole
UO:0000089.definition: A molar volume unit which is equal to 1 cubic meter occupied by one mole of a substance in the form of a solid, liquid, or gas.

UO:0000093.label: cubic meter per kilogram
UO:0000093.definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to one cubic meter volume occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance.

UO:0000197.label: liter per kilogram
UO:0000197.definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to one liter volume occupied by one kilogram of a particular substance.

UO:0000199.label: microliter per kilogram
UO:0000199.definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a liter per kilogram or 10^[-6] l/kg.

UO:0000198.label: milliliter per kilogram
UO:0000198.definition: A specific volume unit which is equal to a thousandth of a liter per kilogram or 10^[-3] l/kg.

UO:0000094.label: meter per second
UO:0000094.definition: A speed/velocity unit which is equal to the speed of an object traveling 1 meter distance in one second.

UO:0000097.label: cubic centimeter
UO:0000097.definition: A volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a cubic meter or 10^[-9] m^[3], or to 1 ml.

UO:0000100.label: cubic decimeter
UO:0000100.definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousand of a cubic meter or 10^[-3] m^[3], or to 1 L.

UO:0000096.label: cubic meter
UO:0000096.definition: A volume unit which is equal to the volume of a cube with edges one meter in length. One cubic meter equals to 1000 liters.

UO:0000209.label: deciliter
UO:0000209.definition: A volume unit which is equal to one tenth of a liter or 10^[-1] L.

UO:0000104.label: femtoliter
UO:0000104.definition: A volume unit which is equal to 10^[-15] L.

UO:0000099.label: liter
UO:0000099.definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a cubic meter or 10^[-3] m^[3], or to 1 decimeter.

UO:0000101.label: microliter
UO:0000101.definition: A volume unit which is equal to one millionth of a liter or 10^[-6] L.

UO:0000098.label: milliliter
UO:0000098.definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of a liter or 10^[-3] L, or to 1 cubic centimeter.

UO:0000056.label: molar volume unit
UO:0000056.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of a homogeneous substance containing 6.02 x 1023 atoms or molecules.

UO:0000102.label: nanoliter
UO:0000102.definition: A volume unit which is equal to one thousandth of one millionth of a liter or 10^[-9] L.

UO:0000103.label: picoliter
UO:0000103.definition: A volume unit which is equal to 10^[-12] L.

UO:0000059.label: specific volume unit
UO:0000059.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the volume of a given mass of substance (the reciprocal of density).

UO:0000122.label: plane angle unit
UO:0000122.definition: A unit which is a standard measure of the angle formed by two straight lines in the same plane.

UO:0000185.label: degree
UO:0000185.definition: A plane angle unit which is equal to 1/360 of a full rotation or 1.7453310^[-2] rad.

UO:0000123.label: radian
UO:0000123.definition: A plane angle unit which is equal to the angle subtended at the center of a circle by an arc equal in length to the radius of the circle, approximately 57 degrees 17 minutes and 44.6 seconds.

UO:0000052.label: mass density unit
UO:0000052.definition: A density unit which is a standard measure of the mass of a substance in a given volume.

UO:0000189.label: count unit
UO:0000189.definition: A dimensionless unit which denotes a simple count of things.

UO:0000190.label: ratio
UO:0000190.definition: A dimensionless unit which denotes an amount or magnitude of one quantity relative to another.

UO:0000194.label: confluence percentage
UO:0000194.definition: A dimensionless percent unit which denotes the density of an attached or monolayer culture (e.g., cell culture).

UO:0000193.label: purity percentage
UO:0000193.definition: A dimensionless percent unit which denotes the homogeneity of a biomaterial.

UO:0000165.label: volume percentage
UO:0000165.definition: A dimensionless concentration unit which denotes the volume of the solute in mL per 100 mL of the resulting solution.

UO:0000244.label: base pair
UO:0000244.definition: A count unit which contains one nucleotide.

UO:0000330.label: gigabasepair
UO:0000330.definition: A unit equal to one billion base pairs.

UO:0000328.label: kilobasepair
UO:0000328.definition: A unit equal to one thousand base pairs.

UO:0000329.label: megabasepair
UO:0000329.definition: A unit equal to one million base pairs

UO:0000191.label: fraction
UO:0000191.definition: A dimensionless ratio unit which relates the part (the numerator) to the whole (the denominator).

UO:0000187.label: percent
UO:0000187.definition: A dimensionless ratio unit which denotes numbers as fractions of 100.

UO:0000213.label: colony forming unit per milliliter
UO:0000213.definition: A colony forming unit which a measure of viable bacterial numbers in one milliliter.

GENEPIO:0001997.label: colony forming unit per 100 millilitre
GENEPIO:0001997.definition: A colony forming unit count which is a ratio of viable bacterial numbers in 100 milliliters of liquid.

UO:0000247.label: millivolt
UO:0000247.definition: An electric potential difference unit which is equal to one thousandth of a volt or 10^[-3] V.

UO:0000262.label: electrical conduction unit
UO:0000262.definition: A unit which represents a standard measurement of the movement of electrically charged particles through a transmission medium (electrical conductor).

UO:0000264.label: siemens
UO:0000264.definition: An electrical conduction unit which is equal to A/V.

UO:0000318.label: formazin nephelometric unit
UO:0000318.definition: 1000 formazin turbidity units (FNU) on the empirical formazin turbidity scale represents reflectance of insol. reaction products of 0.0725 g hydrazine sulfate with 0.7250 g hexamethylenetetramine diluted to 1 L.

hancestro:0016.label: African American/Afro-Caribbean
hancestro:0016.definition: People who defined themselves as American with an admixture of west african, amerindian and european

GENEPIO:0001615.label: host profile or identifers
GENEPIO:0001615.definition: The host profile or identifiers text is the "identification or description of the specific individual from which this sample was obtained".

SIO:000964.label: standard operating procedure
SIO:000964.definition: A standard operating procedure is a specification approved for use in specific environments.

GENEPIO:0001614.label: subject description
GENEPIO:0001614.definition: A subject description is a field containing additional information about an organism (related to an investigation, study and/or specimen) that is not included in other defined vocabulary fields.

NCIT:C25464.label: Country
NCIT:C25464.definition: A collective generic term that refers here to a wide variety of dependencies, areas of special sovereignty, uninhabited islands, and other entities in addition to the traditional countries or independent states.

GENEPIO:0002035.label: centre point
GENEPIO:0002035.definition: A centre point is a point used in the description of an n-dimentional entity from which other (given) aspects of the entity are most efficienty described. A point of symmetry.  The entity must have only one such point.

GENEPIO:0001844.label: origin
GENEPIO:0001844.definition:
"In mathematics, the origin of a Euclidean space is a special point, usually denoted by the letter O, used as a fixed point of reference for the geometry of the surrounding space.

In physical problems, the choice of origin is often arbitrary, meaning any choice of origin will ultimately give the same answer. This allows one to pick an origin point that makes the mathematics as simple as possible, often by taking advantage of some kind of geometric symmetry."

SIO:000512.label: line segment
