SIO:000512.definition: A line segment is a line and a part of a curve that is (inclusively) bounded by two terminal points.

SIO:000501.label: polygon edge
SIO:000501.definition: A polygon edge is a line segment joining two polygon vertices.

GENEPIO:0001905.label: points in 2 dimensions
GENEPIO:0001905.definition: A set of points that exist in a 2-dimensional plane. (This plane may be a cross-section of points defined in n > 2 dimensions).

SIO:000511.label: line
SIO:000511.definition: A line is curve that extends in a single dimension (e.g. straight line; exhibits no curvature), and is composed of at least two fully connected points.

NCIT:C37987.label: Alive
NCIT:C37987.definition: Showing characteristics of life; displaying signs of life.

ARO:3004404.label: automated testing platform vendor
ARO:3004404.definition: Vendor of automated system of analysis for determining antimicrobial susceptibility.

EFO:0005056.label: age at death
EFO:0005056.definition: The age at which death occurs.

EFO:0004703.label: age at menarche
EFO:0004703.definition: The age of onset of (human) menarche, the beginning of the first menstrual cycle in an individual

EFO:0004704.label: age at menopause
EFO:0004704.definition: The age of onset of (human) menopause, the beginning of the first menstrual cycle in an individual

EFO:0004847.label: age at onset
EFO:0004847.definition: The age at which some process, or disease started in a human individual.

EFO:0005112.label: gestational age
EFO:0005112.definition: The age of the conceptus, beginning from the time of FERTILIZATION. In clinical obstetrics, the gestational age is often estimated as the time from the last day of the last MENSTRUATION which is about 2 weeks before OVULATION and fertilization.

EFO:0008007.label: age at assessment
EFO:0008007.definition: The age of an individual at the time an assessment takes place

EFO:0007888.label: age at voice drop
EFO:0007888.definition: The age of onset of (human) voice drop, the deepening of the voice of adolescents as they reach puberty

EFO:0001272.label: adult
EFO:0001272.definition: A maturity quality inhering in an individual by virtue of the individual having attained sexual maturity and full growth

EFO:0007725.label: embryo stage
EFO:0007725.definition: A life cycle stage that starts with fertilization and ends with the fully formed embryo.

EFO:0004920.label: progression free survival
EFO:0004920.definition: Progression free survival is a measurement from a defined time point e.g. diagnosis and indicates that the disease did not progress i.e. tumours did not increase in size and new incidences did not occur. PFS is usually used in analyzing results of treatment for advanced disease.

APOLLO_SV:00000258.label: delay from symptoms to treatment
APOLLO_SV:00000258.definition: The duration between the appearance of symptoms of a disease and the start of a treatment.

APOLLO_SV:00000280.label: duration of treatment course
APOLLO_SV:00000280.definition: A duration that measures the temporal interval occupied by a treatment course.

APOLLO_SV:00000016.label: infectious period duration
APOLLO_SV:00000016.definition: A duration of the parts of an infection during which the host bears an infectious disposition in a population of hosts.

APOLLO_SV:00000017.label: latent period duration
APOLLO_SV:00000017.definition: A duration of the time interval between the host acquiring an infection and the host bearing a contagiousness disposition during the same disease course within a population of hosts.

APOLLO_SV:00000291.label: time delay of treatment detection
APOLLO_SV:00000291.definition: The duration from the time an individual receives a treatment until the time a system designed to detect that the treatment occurred detects it in a population

APOLLO_SV:00000267.label: time delay to case detection
APOLLO_SV:00000267.definition: The duration from the time an organism satisfies a case definition until a process or system detects the organism as satisfying that case definition

EFO:0000409.label: disease free survival
EFO:0000409.definition: A temporal measurement of the period after successful treatment in which there is no appearance of the symptoms or effects of the disease.

EFO:0004919.label: metastasis free survival
EFO:0004919.definition: The percentage of subjects in a study who have survived without cancer spread for a defined period of time. Usually reported as time since diagnosis or treatment. Can be reported for an individual or a study population.

EFO:0002091.label: biological replicate
EFO:0002091.definition: A biological replicate is a replicate role that consists of independent biological replicates made from different individual biosamples.

EFO:0002090.label: technical replicate
EFO:0002090.definition: A technical replicate is a replicate role where the same BioSample is use e.g. the same pool of RNA used to assess technical (as opposed to biological) variation within an experiment.

EFO:0000482.label: event free survival time
EFO:0000482.definition: Is the survival of a subject (or group of subjects) measured from the date of diagnosis until  locoregional or systemic recurrence,  second malignancy, or death from any cause or disease progression or relapse, institution of new unplanned anticancer treatment, or death from any cause.

EFO:0000638.label: overall survival
EFO:0000638.definition: A measurement of the survival rate for a group of individuals suffering from a disease.

EFO:0000246.label: age
EFO:0000246.definition: A temporal measurement of the time period elapsed since an identifiable point in the life cycle of an organism. If a developmental stage is specified, the identifiable point would be the beginning of that stage. Otherwise the identifiable point must be specified such as planting (e.g. 3 days post planting).

EFO:0000433.label: duration
EFO:0000433.definition: A temporal measurement of the time between two specified points.

EFO:0000724.label: timepoint
EFO:0000724.definition: Time point at which a sample or observation is made or taken from a biomaterial as measured from some reference point.

EFO:0004949.label: clinical temporal measurement
EFO:0004949.definition: A temporal measurement related to disease progression

EFO:0004425.label: initial time point
EFO:0004425.definition: The first time point measured at the start of some process.

EFO:0004950.label: date of birth
EFO:0004950.definition: The point in time at which an individual was born.

EFO:0004561.label: African
EFO:0004561.definition: Denotes a person with African ancestral origins who self identifies, or is identified, as African. The concept does not refer to those of other ancestry, for example, European and South Asian. In practice, the term mainly refers to people originated from forty-eight sub-Saharan Africa nations; and excudes individuals from North Africa countries, e.g. such as Algeria, Morocco, Egypt, Tunisia with Arab and Berber ethnicity.

EFO:0003150.label: African American
EFO:0003150.definition: A term used in the United States to categorize a population group comprised of persons having origins in any of the black racial groups of Africa. Includes population subgroups (e.g., Kenyan, Nigerian, Haitian). The concept refers also to individuals who classify themselves as described.

EFO:0003152.label: Asian
EFO:0003152.definition: Denotes a person having origins in any of the original peoples of the Far East, Southeast Asia, or the Indian subcontinent, including Cambodia, China, India, Japan, Korea, Malaysia, Mongolia, Pakistan, the Philippine Islands, Thailand, and Vietnam.

EFO:0003153.label: Asian Indian
EFO:0003153.definition: In North America the term is used to distinguish a person having origins in the original peoples of the Indian sub-continent from Native Americans.

EFO:0003154.label: Asian/Pacific Islander
EFO:0003154.definition: Denotes a person having origins in any of the original peoples of Hawaii, Guam, Samoa, or other Pacific Islands. The term covers particularly people who identify themselves as part-Hawaiian, Native Hawaiian, Guamanian or Chamorro, Carolinian, Samoan, Chuukese (Trukese), Fijian, Kosraean, Melanesian, Micronesian, Northern Mariana Islander, Palauan, Papua New Guinean, Pohnpeian, Polynesian, Solomon Islander, Tahitian, Tokelauan, Tongan, Yapese, or Pacific Islander, not specified.

EFO:0003156.label: Caucasian
EFO:0003156.definition: Denotes person with European, Middle Eastern, or North African ancestral origin who identifies, or is identified, as White.

EFO:0003157.label: Chinese
EFO:0003157.definition: Denotes the inhabitants of China, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

EFO:0003168.label: Hawaiian
EFO:0003168.definition: Denotes a person having origins in any of the original peoples of Hawaii, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

EFO:0003169.label: Hispanic
EFO:0003169.definition: A person of Mexican, Puerto Rican, Cuban, Central or South American or other Spanish culture or origin, regardless of race. An arbitrary ethnic classification.

EFO:0003162.label: Iranian
EFO:0003162.definition: Denotes the inhabitants of Iran, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

EFO:0003163.label: Irish
EFO:0003163.definition: Denotes the inhabitants of Ireland, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

EFO:0003166.label: Latino
EFO:0003166.definition: A person of Mexican, Puerto Rican, Cuban, Central or South American or other Spanish culture or origin, regardless of race. An arbitrary ethnic classification.

EFO:0004901.label: Northern and Western European
EFO:0004901.definition: Population of northern and western European ancestry.

EFO:0003160.label: Filipino
EFO:0003160.definition: Denotes the inhabitants of the Philippine Islands, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

EFO:0003164.label: Japanese
EFO:0003164.definition: Denotes the inhabitants of Japan, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

EFO:0003165.label: Korean
EFO:0003165.definition: Denotes the inhabitants of Korea, a person from there, or their descendants elsewhere.

EFO:0003161.label: Han Chinese
EFO:0003161.definition: Han Chinese are an ethnic group native to East Asia. Han Chinese constitute about 92% of the population of the People's Republic of China (mainland China)

EFO:0004340.label: body mass index
EFO:0004340.definition: An indicator of body density as determined by the relationship ofÂ BODY WEIGHT to BODY HEIGHT. BMI=weight (kg)/height squared (m2). BMI correlates with body fat (ADIPOSE TISSUE). Their relationship varies with age and gender. For adults, BMI falls into these categories: below 18.5 (underweight); 18.5-24.9 (normal); 25.0-29.9 (overweight); 30.0 and above (obese). (National Center for Health Statistics, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention)

EFO:0004900.label: Yoruba
EFO:0004900.definition: The Yoruba people are one of the largest ethnic groups in West Africa.

EFO:0000412.label: distant metastasis free survival
EFO:0000412.definition: Is a temporal measure from a defined start point e.g. diagnosis, or treatment of the period to appearance of a distant metastasis. A distant metastasis refers to cancer that has spread from the original (primary) tumor to distant organs or distant lymph nodes. Also known as distant cancer.

HP:0011007.label: age of onset
HP:0011007.definition: The age group in which disease manifestations appear.

EFO:0007058.label: last follow up
EFO:0007058.definition: The date or time of the last check of a patient by a medical professional.

EFO:0000714.label: survival time
EFO:0000714.definition: Time of survival is an information entity which is about the length of time a material entity has survived after some adverse event, such as infection from a disease.

EFO:0004918.label: age at diagnosis
EFO:0004918.definition: The age, measured from some defined time point e.g. birth at which a subject (e.g. a human patient) is diagnosed with some disease e.g. breast cancer.

EFO:0004951.label: alive at endpoint
EFO:0004951.definition: A clinical temporal measurement indicating that the subject is alive at the end of the clinical investigation.

EFO:0008336.label: disease progression measurement
EFO:0008336.definition: quantification of some aspect of disease progression such as speed or symptom variability. Disease progression can be quantified in a number of ways, for example as a correlated measure of progression scores from different symptom areas

EFO:0004952.label: disease recurrence
EFO:0004952.definition: The recurrence of a disease after treatment

NCIT:C85539.label: Microbial Susceptibility Test Result
NCIT:C85539.definition: The outcome of a test to determine whether microbial growth is affected by an antimicrobial compound.

GENEPIO:0002065.label: German Institute for Standardization (DIN) (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002065.definition: DIN is recognized by the Federal Government of Germany as the competent standards organization for Germany and as the national standards body representing Germany in non-governmental international standards organizations.

GENEPIO:0002063.label: British Society for Antimicrobial Chemotherapy (BSAC) (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002063.definition: BSAC is a British inter-professional organisation involved in antibiotic education, research and leadership

GENEPIO:0002064.label: Clinical and Laboratory Standards Institute (CLSI) (Deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002064.definition: The Clinical and Laboratory Standards Institute develops and implements clinical laboratory testing standards

GENEPIO:0002066.label: European Committe on Antimicrobial Susceptibility Testing (EUCAST) (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002066.definition: EUCAST is a standing committee jointly organized by ESCMID, ECDC and European national breakpoint committees; it deals with breakpoints and technical aspects of phenotypic in vitro antimicrobial susceptibility testing.

GENEPIO:0000077.label: GSCID-BRC data item (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0000077.definition: A GSCID/BRC data item is a field in one of the GSCID/BRC Project and Sample Application Standard subsets.

GENEPIO:0000104.label: INSDC MDM standard (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0000104.definition: The INDISC consortium "Minimum data for Matching" standard aims to define a format to capture reads and minimum metadata.  It is developed by the "Repository and storage of sequence and meta-data" workgroup 2.  It is used in the Global Microbial Identifier platform.

GENEPIO:0000105.label: MIxS data item (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0000105.definition: a MixS data item is a term or field defined in the Genomic Standards Consortium MIxS standard.

GENEPIO:0001535.label: NCBI BioProject ID (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001535.definition: This is a subset of OBI investigation identifier.  It pertains only to NCBI Biosample projects

GENEPIO:0000103.label: NCBI BioProject data item (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0000103.definition: An NCBI BioProject data item is a datum within the NCBI BioProject standard collection

GENEPIO:0001579.label: NCBI BioProject model (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001579.definition: The NCBI BioProject model includes all datums associated with the current NCBI BioProject specification.

GENEPIO:0000016.label: NCBI antibiogram data item (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0000016.definition: An NCBI antibiogram data item is an antimicrobial susceptibility and resistance datum related to drug resistant pathogens. This information is provided within an antibiogram table on BioSample records.

GENEPIO:0001890.label: US postal code (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001890.definition: A "USA zip code" is a five digit (Zone Improvement Plan) or 9 digit postal code pertaining to a region of the United States of America. The optional trailing 4 digits of a 9 digit zip code provide greater granularity of delivery target.

GENEPIO:0002038.label: antibiotic intermediate resistance (I) (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002038.definition: Intermediate resistance indicates that an isolate is observed to offer an intermediate level of resistance to a given antibiotic.

GENEPIO:0002039.label: antibiotic nonsensitive (high resistance) (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002039.definition: non-susceptible indicates that an isolate is observed to offer complete resistance to a given antibiotic.

GENEPIO:0002041.label: antibiotic resistant (R) (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002041.definition: Resistant indicates that an isolate is observed to offer a greater than intermediate level of resistance to a given antibiotic.

GENEPIO:0002042.label: antibiotic sensitive (S) (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002042.definition: Susceptible indicates that an isolate is observed to offer a detectable but less than intermediate level of resistance to a given antibiotic.

GENEPIO:0002037.label: antimicrobial resistance phenotype (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002037.definition: The resistance phenotype of an isolate represents the interpretation of an MIC value with regard to some breakpoint threshold e.g. resistant (R), sensitive (S), intermediate (I), wild type (WT), or non-wild type (NWT)

GENEPIO:0002181.label: antimicrobial resistance phenotype - epidemiological cut-off values

GENEPIO:0002045.label: antimicrobial resistance testing method (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002045.definition: The type of assay used to determine the minimum inhibitory concentration.

GENEPIO:0002049.label: antimicrobial resistance testing platform (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002049.definition: The instrumentation used to determine minimum inhibitory concentration values.

GENEPIO:0002056.label: antimicrobial resistance testing platform vendor (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002056.definition: The manufacturer of an antibiotic resistance lab typing platform

GENEPIO:0002062.label: antimicrobial resistance testing reference standard (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002062.definition: The clinical and laboratory guidelines or standards that prescribe the threshold values for determining resistance phenotypes.

GENEPIO:0002102.label: antimicrobial resistance tissue specificity (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002102.definition: The tissue type used to select breakpoints from a particular standard, for the interpretation of MIC results.

GENEPIO:0001016.label: cafeteria (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001016.definition: A cafeteria is a type of food service location in which there is little or no waiting staff table service, whether a restaurant or within an institution such as a large office building or school.

GENEPIO:0001655.label: categorical tree specification (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001655.definition: A categorical tree specification datum is a categorical value specification which takes its value from the ontology URI identifier of any one of its subclass items; these may be organized in a hierarchy.

GENEPIO:0001018.label: delicatessen (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001018.definition: A delicatessen or deli is a retail establishment that sells a selection of unusual or foreign prepared foods.

GENEPIO:0001705.label: draft GenEpiO BioProject standard (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001705.definition: This is an organizational category for grouping parameters relevant to biomedical research projects.

GENEPIO:0000015.label: draft GenEpiO BioSample standard (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0000015.definition: This is an organizational category for grouping parameters relevant to a biomedical sample.

GENEPIO:0002080.label: drug minimum inhibitory concentration unit (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002080.definition: The unit provided for an antibiotic drug test dosage.

GENEPIO:0001019.label: food kiosk (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001019.definition: A food kiosk is a kiosk (a booth with an open window on one side) that sells food.

GENEPIO:0001020.label: grocery store (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001020.definition: A grocery store is a retail store that primarily sells food.

GENEPIO:0001422.label: laboratory sequencing datum (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001422.definition: A laboratory sequencing datum is a datum related to the sequencing assay process applied to an isolate.

GENEPIO:0001035.label: long term care facility (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001035.definition: A long term care facility provides a type of residential care. It is a place of residence for people who require continual nursing care and have significant difficulty coping with the required activities of daily living.

GENEPIO:0001022.label: market (obsolete)
GENEPIO:0001022.definition: A market, or marketplace, is a location where people regularly gather for the purchase and sale of provisions, livestock, and other goods

GENEPIO:0002099.label: non-wild type (NWT) (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002099.definition: A non-wild type (WT) resistance phenotype indicates a bacterial pathogen has an acquired or mutational resistance mechanism present with respect to the antimicrobial in question. The bacteria has a reduced susceptibility to this agent.

ENVO:01000753.label: obsolete air temperature
ENVO:01000753.definition: A temperature that inheres in some portion of air.

GENEPIO:0002027.label: ordinal variable (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002027.definition: An ordinal variable is a categorical variable whose values have sequential order, but no distance metric between them.

GENEPIO:0001009.label: restaurant (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001009.definition: A restaurant or an eatery, is a business which prepares and serves food and drinks to customers in exchange for money.

GENEPIO:0002043.label: sensitive - dose dependent (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002043.definition: Susceptible - dose dependent indicates that an isolate is observed to offer resistance to a given antibiotic when a sufficient dose is given.

GENEPIO:0000074.label: sequencing assay (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0000074.definition: the sequencing conditions and the analyte being measured

GENEPIO:0001021.label: specialty/ethnic store (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001021.definition: A specialty/ethnic food store is a store specializing in a particular variety of food or food of cultural / regional origin.

GENEPIO:0001635.label: specimen from subject datum (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001635.definition: An organism isolate datum is any datum pertaining to an isolate organism

GENEPIO:0000030.label: specimen source environmental material (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0000030.definition: The environmental material level refers to the material that was displaced by the sample, or material in which a sample was embedded, prior to the sampling event. Environmental material terms are generally mass nouns. Examples include: air, soil, or water. EnvO (v 2013-06-14) terms can be found via the link: www.environmentontology.org/Browse-EnvO

GENEPIO:0001637.label: specimen source material category (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001637.definition: This is the scientific role or category that the subject organism or material has with respect to an investigation.

GENEPIO:0000018.label: subject species (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0000018.definition: The natural (as opposed to laboratory) full scientific taxonomic name of a subject related to a given investigation, study and/or specimen.

GENEPIO:0001024.label: take out restaurant (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0001024.definition: A restaurant providing prepared meals or other food items that the purchaser intends to eat elsewhere

GENEPIO:0002098.label: wild type (WT) (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002098.definition:
A wild type (WT) resistance phenotype indicates a bacterial pathogen belongs to a "Naïve", susceptible wild-type population with respect to a given antimicrobial. No acquired or mutational resistance mechanisms are
present to the antimicrobial in question.

GENEPIO:0002068.label: Société Française de Microbiologie (SFM) (deprecated)
GENEPIO:0002068.definition: The French Society of Microbiology (SFM) is a non-profit association which aims to bring together microbiologists from French-speaking countries, working in the domains of bacteria, viruses, Fungi and parasites, and related medical, industrial and environmental microbiology, physiology, genetics, taxonomy, hygiene, and antimicrobial agents.

GENEPIO:0001432.label: awaiting ontology review/placement
GENEPIO:0001432.definition: This class is a temporary holding bin for items that need a class hierarchy home, definition, and/or subclass items.

NCIT:C25690.label: Street Address
NCIT:C25690.definition: The street name and building number where a person or organization can be found.
